tksbrokerapi.TKSBrokerAPI

TKSBrokerAPI is a python API to work with some methods of Tinkoff Open API using REST protocol. It can view history, orders and market information. Also, you can open orders and trades.

If you run this module as CLI program then it realizes simple logic: receiving a lot of options and execute one command. See examples: https://tim55667757.github.io/TKSBrokerAPI/#Usage-examples

Used constants are in the TKSEnums module: https://tim55667757.github.io/TKSBrokerAPI/docs/tksbrokerapi/TKSEnums.html

About Tinkoff Invest API: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/

Tinkoff Invest API documentation: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/

   4"""
   5**TKSBrokerAPI** is a python API to work with some methods of Tinkoff Open API using REST protocol.
   6It can view history, orders and market information. Also, you can open orders and trades.
   7
   8If you run this module as CLI program then it realizes simple logic: receiving a lot of options and execute one command.
   9**See examples**: https://tim55667757.github.io/TKSBrokerAPI/#Usage-examples
  10
  11**Used constants are in the TKSEnums module**: https://tim55667757.github.io/TKSBrokerAPI/docs/tksbrokerapi/TKSEnums.html
  12
  13About Tinkoff Invest API: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/
  14
  15Tinkoff Invest API documentation: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/

  58uLogger.level = 10  # debug level by default
  59uLogger.handlers[0].level = 20  # info level by default for STDOUT

  61CPU_COUNT = cpu_count()  # host's real CPU count
  62CPU_USAGES = CPU_COUNT - 1 if CPU_COUNT > 1 else 1  # how many CPUs will be used for parallel calculations
  63uLogger.debug("Host CPU count: [{}]".format(CPU_COUNT))

  65# --- Main constants:
  66
  67NANO = 0.000000001  # SI-constant nano = 10^-9
  68
  69
  70def NanoToFloat(units: str, nano: int) -> float:
  71    """
  72    Convert number in nano-view mode with string parameter `units` and integer parameter `nano` to float view. Examples:
  73
  74    `NanoToFloat(units="2", nano=500000000) -> 2.5`
  75
  76    `NanoToFloat(units="0", nano=50000000) -> 0.05`
  77
  78    :param units: integer string or integer parameter that represents the integer part of number
  79    :param nano: integer string or integer parameter that represents the fractional part of number
  80    :return: float view of number
  81    """
  82    return int(units) + int(nano) * NANO
  83
  84
  85def FloatToNano(number: float) -> dict:
  86    """
  87    Convert float number to nano-type view: dictionary with string `units` and integer `nano` parameters `{"units": "string", "nano": integer}`. Examples:
  88
  89    `FloatToNano(number=2.5) -> {"units": "2", "nano": 500000000}`
  90
  91    `FloatToNano(number=0.05) -> {"units": "0", "nano": 50000000}`
  92
  93    :param number: float number
  94    :return: nano-type view of number: `{"units": "string", "nano": integer}`
  95    """
  96    splitByPoint = str(number).split(".")
  97    frac = 0
  98
  99    if len(splitByPoint) > 1:
 100        if len(splitByPoint[1]) <= 9:
 101            frac = int("{}{}".format(
 102                int(splitByPoint[1]),
 103                "0" * (9 - len(splitByPoint[1])),
 104            ))
 105
 106    if (number < 0) and (frac > 0):
 107        frac = -frac
 108
 109    return {"units": str(int(number)), "nano": frac}

 112def GetDatesAsString(start: str = None, end: str = None) -> tuple:
 113    """
 114    If `start=None`, `end=None` then return dates from yesterday to current time.
 115    If `start=some_date_1`, `end=None` then return dates from `some_date_1` to current time.
 116    If `start=some_date_1`, `end=some_date_2` then return dates from `some_date_1` to `some_date_2`.
 117    Start day may be negative integer numbers: `-1`, `-2`, `-3` - how many days ago.
 118
 119    Also, you can use keywords for start if `dateEnd=None`:
 120    `today` (from 00:00:00 to current time),
 121    `yesterday` (-1 day from 00:00:00 to 23:59:59),
 122    `week` (-7 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time),
 123    `month` (-30 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time),
 124    `year` (-365 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time),
 125
 126    User dates format must be like: `%Y-%m-%d`, e.g. `2020-02-03` (3 Feb, 2020).
 127
 128    :return: tuple with 2 strings `(start, end)` dates in UTC ISO time format `%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ` for OpenAPI.
 129             Example: `("2022-06-01T00:00:00Z", "2022-06-20T23:59:59Z")`
 130    """
 131    uLogger.debug("Input start day is [{}] (UTC), end day is [{}] (UTC)".format(start, end))
 132    now = datetime.now(tzutc())
 133
 134    # showing statistics between start of the current day and current time:
 135    if start is None or start.lower() == "today":
 136        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0)
 137        e = now
 138
 139    # from start of the last day to the end of the last day:
 140    elif start.lower() == "yesterday":
 141        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=1)
 142        e = now.replace(hour=23, minute=59, second=59, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=1)
 143
 144    # week (-7 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time):
 145    elif start.lower() == "week":
 146        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=7)
 147        e = now
 148
 149    # month (-30 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time):
 150    elif start.lower() == "month":
 151        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=30)
 152        e = now
 153
 154    # year (-365 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time):
 155    elif start.lower() == "year":
 156        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=365)
 157        e = now
 158
 159    # showing statistics from -N days ago to current date and time:
 160    elif start.startswith('-') and start[1:].isdigit():
 161        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=abs(int(start)))
 162        e = now
 163
 164    # showing statistics between start day at 00:00:00 and the end day at 23:59:59:
 165    else:
 166        s = datetime.strptime(start, "%Y-%m-%d").replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0, tzinfo=tzutc())
 167        e = datetime.strptime(end, "%Y-%m-%d").replace(hour=23, minute=59, second=59, microsecond=0, tzinfo=tzutc()) if end is not None else now
 168
 169    # converting to UTC ISO time formatted with Z suffix for Tinkoff Open API:
 170    s = s.strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ")
 171    e = e.strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ")
 172
 173    uLogger.debug("Tinkoff Open API uses this start day (converted to UTC ISO format, with Z): [{}], and the end day: [{}]".format(s, e))
 174
 175    return s, e
 176
 177
 178class TinkoffBrokerServer:
 179    """
 180    This class implements methods to work with Tinkoff broker server.
 181
 182    Examples to work with API: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/
 183
 184    Where is `token`: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/token/
 185    """
 186    def __init__(self, token: str, iList: dict = None, accountId: str = None) -> None:
 187        """
 188        Main class init.
 189
 190        :param token: Bearer token for Tinkoff Invest API. It can be set from environment variable `TKS_API_TOKEN`.
 191        :param iList: dictionary of dictionaries with instrument's data.
 192        :param accountId: string with user's numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker. It can be found in broker's reports.
 193                          Also, this variable can be set from environment variable `TKS_ACCOUNT_ID`.
 194        """
 195        if token is None or not token:
 196            try:
 197                self.token = r"{}".format(os.environ["TKS_API_TOKEN"])
 198                uLogger.debug("Bearer token for Tinkoff OpenApi set up from environment variable `TKS_API_TOKEN`. See https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/token/")
 199
 200            except KeyError:
 201                raise Exception("`--token` key or environment variable `TKS_API_TOKEN` is required! See https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/token/")
 202
 203        else:
 204            self.token = token  # highly priority than environment variable 'TKS_API_TOKEN'
 205            uLogger.debug("Bearer token for Tinkoff OpenApi set up from class variable `token`")
 206
 207        if accountId is None or not accountId:
 208            try:
 209                self.accountId = r"{}".format(os.environ["TKS_ACCOUNT_ID"])
 210                uLogger.debug("String with user's numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker set up from environment variable `TKS_ACCOUNT_ID`")
 211
 212            except KeyError:
 213                uLogger.warning("`--account-id` key or environment variable `TKS_ACCOUNT_ID` undefined! Some of operations may be unavailable (overview, trading etc).")
 214
 215        else:
 216            self.accountId = accountId  # highly priority than environment variable 'TKS_ACCOUNT_ID'
 217            uLogger.debug("String with user's numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker set up from class variable `accountId`")
 218
 219        self.aliases = TKS_TICKER_ALIASES
 220        """Some aliases instead official tickers. See `TKSEnums.TKS_TICKER_ALIASES`"""
 221
 222        self.aliasesKeys = self.aliases.keys()  # re-calc only first time at class init
 223        self.exclude = TKS_TICKERS_OR_FIGI_EXCLUDED  # some of tickets or FIGIs raised exception earlier when it sends to server, that is why we exclude there
 224
 225        self.ticker = ""
 226        """String with ticker, e.g. `GOOGL`. Use alias for `USD000UTSTOM` simple as `USD`, `EUR_RUB__TOM` as `EUR` etc. More tickers aliases here: `TKSEnums.TKS_TICKER_ALIASES`."""
 227
 228        self.figi = ""
 229        """String with FIGI, e.g. ticker `GOOGL` has FIGI `BBG009S39JX6`"""
 230
 231        self.depth = 1
 232        """Depth of Market (DOM) can be >= 1. Default: 1. It used with `--price` key to showing DOM with current prices for givens ticker or FIGI."""
 233
 234        self.server = r"https://invest-public-api.tinkoff.ru/rest"
 235        """Tinkoff REST API server for real trade operations. Default: https://invest-public-api.tinkoff.ru/rest
 236
 237        See: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/#tinkoff-invest-api_1
 238        """
 239
 240        uLogger.debug("Broker API server: {}".format(self.server))
 241
 242        self.timeout = 15
 243        """Server operations timeout in seconds. Default: 15"""
 244
 245        self.headers = {"Content-Type": "application/json", "accept": "application/json", "Authorization": "Bearer {}".format(self.token)}
 246        """Headers which send in every request to broker server. Default: `{"Content-Type": "application/json", "accept": "application/json", "Authorization": "Bearer {token}"}`"""
 247
 248        self.body = None
 249        """Request body which send to broker server. Default: `None`"""
 250
 251        self.historyLength = 24
 252        """How many candles returns if candles history request. For example, if `historyInterval="hour"` and `historyLength=24` it means: "give me last 24 hours". Must be >=1. Default: 24"""
 253
 254        self.historyInterval = "hour"
 255        """Interval string for Tinkoff API (see: `TKSEnums.TKS_TIMEFRAMES`). Available values are `"1min"`, `"2min"`, `"3min"`, `"5min"`, `"10min"`, `"15min"`, `"30min"`, `"hour"`, `"day"`, `"week"`, `"month"`. Default: `"hour"`"""
 256
 257        self.iList = iList if iList is not None else self.Listing()
 258        """Dictionary with raw data about stocks, currencies, bonds, etfs and futures from broker server.
 259        At first time, when class init, `Listing()` method auto-update this variable.
 260        For future use, you can save this variable and substitute it in the `iList` to avoid permanent downloads from the server.
 261        """
 262
 263        self.pricesList = {}  # You can request all current prices with `ShowAllPrices()` method. WARNING! This is too long operation!
 264
 265        self.instrumentsFile = "instruments.md"
 266        """Filename where full broker's instruments list will be saved. Default: `"instruments.md"`"""
 267
 268        self.pricesFile = "prices.md"
 269        """Filename where prices of selected instruments will be saved. Default: `"prices.md"`"""
 270
 271        self.overviewFile = "overview.md"
 272        """Filename where current portfolio, open trades and orders will be saved. Default: `"overview.md"`"""
 273
 274        self.reportFile = "report.md"
 275        """Filename where history of deals and trade statistics will be saved. Default: `"report.md"`"""
 276
 277        self.historyFile = None
 278        """Full path to .csv output file where history candles will be saved. Default: `None`, mean that returns only pandas dataframe."""
 279
 280    @staticmethod
 281    def _ParseJSON(rawData="{}", debug: bool = False) -> dict:
 282        """
 283        Parse JSON from response string.
 284
 285        :param rawData: this is a string with JSON-formatted text.
 286        :param debug: if `True` then print more debug information.
 287        :return: JSON (dictionary), parsed from server response string.
 288        """
 289        if debug:
 290            uLogger.debug("Raw text body:")
 291            uLogger.debug(rawData)
 292
 293        responseJSON = json.loads(rawData, encoding="UTF-8") if rawData else {}
 294
 295        if debug:
 296            uLogger.debug("JSON formatted:")
 297            for jsonLine in json.dumps(responseJSON, indent=4).split('\n'):
 298                uLogger.debug(jsonLine)
 299
 300        return responseJSON
 301
 302    def SendAPIRequest(self, url: str, reqType: str = "GET", retry: int = 3, pause: int = 5, debug: bool = False) -> dict:
 303        """
 304        Send GET or POST request to broker server and receive JSON object.
 305
 306        self.header: must be define with dictionary of headers.
 307        self.body: if define then used as request body. None by default.
 308        self.timeout: global request timeout, 15 seconds by default.
 309        :param url: url with REST request.
 310        :param reqType: send "GET" or "POST" request. "GET" by default.
 311        :param retry: how many times retry after first request if an error occurred.
 312        :param pause: sleep time in seconds between retries.
 313        :param debug: if `True` then print more debug information.
 314        :return: response JSON (dictionary) from broker.
 315        """
 316        if reqType not in ("GET", "POST"):
 317            raise Exception("You can define request type: 'GET' or 'POST'!")
 318
 319        if debug:
 320            uLogger.debug("Request parameters:")
 321            uLogger.debug("    - REST API URL: {}".format(url))
 322            uLogger.debug("    - request type: {}".format(reqType))
 323            uLogger.debug("    - headers: {}".format(str(self.headers).replace(self.token, "*** request token ***")))
 324            uLogger.debug("    - body: {}".format(self.body))
 325
 326        # fast hack to avoid all operations with some tickers/FIGI
 327        responseJSON = {}
 328        oK = True
 329        for item in self.exclude:
 330            if item in url:
 331                if debug:
 332                    uLogger.warning("Do not execute operations with list of this tickers/FIGI: {}".format(str(self.exclude)))
 333
 334                oK = False
 335                break
 336
 337        if oK:
 338            counter = 0
 339            response = None
 340            errMsg = ""
 341
 342            while not response and counter <= retry:
 343                if reqType == "GET":
 344                    response = requests.get(url, headers=self.headers, data=self.body, timeout=self.timeout)
 345
 346                if reqType == "POST":
 347                    response = requests.post(url, headers=self.headers, data=self.body, timeout=self.timeout)
 348
 349                if debug:
 350                    uLogger.debug("Response:")
 351                    uLogger.debug("    - status code: {}".format(response.status_code))
 352                    uLogger.debug("    - reason: {}".format(response.reason))
 353                    uLogger.debug("    - body length: {}".format(len(response.text)))
 354
 355                # Error status codes: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_HTTP_status_codes
 356                if 400 <= response.status_code < 600:
 357                    errMsg = "[{}] {}".format(response.status_code, response.text)
 358                    uLogger.debug("    - not oK status code received: {}".format(errMsg))
 359                    counter += 1
 360
 361                    if counter <= retry:
 362                        uLogger.debug("Retry: [{}]. Wait until {} sec. and try again...".format(counter, pause))
 363                        sleep(pause)
 364
 365            responseJSON = self._ParseJSON(response.text)
 366
 367            if errMsg:
 368                uLogger.error("Not `oK` status received from broker server!")
 369                uLogger.error("    - message: {}".format(errMsg))
 370                # raise Exception("Server returned an error! See full debug log. Also you can set debug=True in SendAPIRequest() and _ParseJSON() methods.")
 371
 372        return responseJSON
 373
 374    def _IUpdater(self, iType: str) -> tuple:
 375        """
 376        Request instrument by type from server. See available API methods for instruments:
 377        Currencies: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService/InstrumentsService_Currencies
 378        Shares: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService/InstrumentsService_Shares
 379        Bonds: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService/InstrumentsService_Bonds
 380        Etfs: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService/InstrumentsService_Etfs
 381        Futures: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService/InstrumentsService_Futures
 382
 383        :param iType: type of the instrument, it must be one of supported types in TKS_INSTRUMENTS list.
 384        :return: tuple with iType name and list of available instruments of current type for defined user token.
 385        """
 386        result = []
 387
 388        if iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
 389            uLogger.debug("Requesting available [{}] list. Wait, please...".format(iType))
 390
 391            # all instruments have the same body in API v2 requests:
 392            self.body = str({"instrumentStatus": "INSTRUMENT_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED"})  # Enum: [INSTRUMENT_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED, INSTRUMENT_STATUS_BASE, INSTRUMENT_STATUS_ALL]
 393            instrumentURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.InstrumentsService/{}".format(iType)
 394            result = self.SendAPIRequest(instrumentURL, reqType="POST", debug=False)["instruments"]
 395
 396        return iType, result
 397
 398    def _IWrapper(self, kwargs):
 399        """
 400        Wrapper runs instrument's update method self._IUpdater().
 401        It's a workaround for using multiprocessing with kwargs. See: https://stackoverflow.com/a/36799206
 402        """
 403        return self._IUpdater(**kwargs)
 404
 405    def Listing(self) -> dict:
 406        """
 407        Gets JSON with raw data about stocks, currencies, bonds, etfs and futures from broker server.
 408
 409        :return: Dictionary with all available broker instruments: currencies, stocks, bonds, etfs and futures.
 410        """
 411        uLogger.debug("Requesting all available instruments from broker for current user token. Wait, please...")
 412        uLogger.debug("CPU usages for parallel requests: [{}]".format(CPU_USAGES))
 413
 414        # this parameters insert to requests: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService
 415        # iType is type of instrument, it must be one of supported types in TKS_INSTRUMENTS list.
 416        iParams = [{"iType": iType} for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS]
 417
 418        poolUpdater = ThreadPool(processes=CPU_USAGES)  # create pool for update instruments in parallel mode
 419        listing = poolUpdater.map(self._IWrapper, iParams)  # execute update operations
 420        poolUpdater.close()
 421
 422        # Dictionary with all broker instruments: stocks, currencies, bonds, etfs and futures.
 423        # Next in this code: item[0] is "iType" and item[1] is list of available instruments from the result of _IUpdater() method
 424        iList = {item[0]: {instrument["ticker"]: instrument for instrument in item[1]} for item in listing}
 425
 426        # calculate minimum price increment (step) for all instruments and set up instrument's type:
 427        for iType in iList.keys():
 428            for ticker in iList[iType]:
 429                iList[iType][ticker]["type"] = iType
 430
 431                if "minPriceIncrement" in iList[iType][ticker].keys():
 432                    iList[iType][ticker]["step"] = NanoToFloat(
 433                        iList[iType][ticker]["minPriceIncrement"]["units"],
 434                        iList[iType][ticker]["minPriceIncrement"]["nano"],
 435                    )
 436
 437                else:
 438                    iList[iType][ticker]["step"] = 0  # hack to avoid empty value in some instruments, e.g. futures
 439
 440        return iList
 441
 442    @staticmethod
 443    def ShowInstrumentInfo(iJSON: dict, printInfo: bool = False) -> str:
 444        """
 445        Show information about instrument defined by json and print in Markdown format.
 446
 447        :param iJSON: json data of instrument, e.g. in code `iJSON = self.iList["Shares"][self.ticker]`
 448        :param printInfo: if `True` then also printing information about instrument and its current price.
 449        :return: text in Markdown format with information about instrument.
 450        """
 451        infoText = ""
 452        if iJSON is not None and iJSON and isinstance(iJSON, dict):
 453            info = [
 454                "# Information is actual at: [{}] (UTC)\n\n".format(datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")),
 455                "| Parameters                                              | Values\n",
 456                "|---------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------\n",
 457                "| Stock ticker:                                           | {}\n".format(iJSON["ticker"]),
 458                "| Full name:                                              | {}\n".format(iJSON["name"]),
 459            ]
 460
 461            if "sector" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["sector"]:
 462                info.append("| Sector:                                                 | {}\n".format(iJSON["sector"]))
 463
 464            info.append("| Country of instrument:                                  | {}{}\n".format(
 465                "({}) ".format(iJSON["countryOfRisk"]) if "countryOfRisk" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["countryOfRisk"] else "",
 466                iJSON["countryOfRiskName"] if "countryOfRiskName" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["countryOfRiskName"] else "",
 467            ))
 468
 469            info.extend([
 470                "|                                                         |\n",
 471                "| FIGI (Financial Instrument Global Identifier):          | {}\n".format(iJSON["figi"]),
 472                "| Exchange:                                               | {}\n".format(iJSON["exchange"]),
 473            ])
 474
 475            if "isin" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["isin"]:
 476                info.append("| ISIN (International Securities Identification Number):  | {}\n".format(iJSON["isin"]))
 477
 478            if "classCode" in iJSON.keys():
 479                info.append("| Class Code:                                             | {}\n".format(iJSON["classCode"]))
 480
 481            info.extend([
 482                "|                                                         |\n",
 483                "| Current broker security trading status:                 | {}\n".format(TKS_TRADING_STATUSES[iJSON["tradingStatus"]]),
 484                "| Buy operations allowed:                                 | {}\n".format("Yes" if iJSON["buyAvailableFlag"] else "No"),
 485                "| Sale operations allowed:                                | {}\n".format("Yes" if iJSON["sellAvailableFlag"] else "No"),
 486                "| Short positions allowed:                                | {}\n".format("Yes" if iJSON["shortEnabledFlag"] else "No"),
 487            ])
 488
 489            info.append("|                                                         |\n")
 490
 491            if "type" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["type"]:
 492                info.append("| Type of the instrument:                                 | {}\n".format(iJSON["type"]))
 493
 494            if "futuresType" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["futuresType"]:
 495                info.append("| Futures type:                                           | {}\n".format(iJSON["futuresType"]))
 496
 497            if "ipoDate" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["ipoDate"]:
 498                info.append("| IPO date:                                               | {}\n".format(iJSON["ipoDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "")))
 499
 500            if "releasedDate" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["releasedDate"]:
 501                info.append("| Released date:                                          | {}\n".format(iJSON["releasedDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "")))
 502
 503            if "rebalancingFreq" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["rebalancingFreq"]:
 504                info.append("| Rebalancing frequency:                                  | {}\n".format(iJSON["rebalancingFreq"]))
 505
 506            if "focusType" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["focusType"]:
 507                info.append("| Focusing type:                                          | {}\n".format(iJSON["focusType"]))
 508
 509            if "assetType" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["assetType"]:
 510                info.append("| Asset type:                                             | {}\n".format(iJSON["assetType"]))
 511
 512            if "basicAsset" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["basicAsset"]:
 513                info.append("| Basic asset:                                            | {}\n".format(iJSON["basicAsset"]))
 514
 515            if "basicAssetSize" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["basicAssetSize"]:
 516                info.append("| Basic asset size:                                       | {}\n".format(NanoToFloat(int(iJSON["basicAssetSize"]["units"]), iJSON["basicAssetSize"]["nano"])))
 517
 518            if "isoCurrencyName" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["isoCurrencyName"]:
 519                info.append("| ISO currency name:                                      | {}\n".format(iJSON["isoCurrencyName"]))
 520
 521            if "currency" in iJSON.keys():
 522                info.append("| Payment currency:                                       | {}\n".format(iJSON["currency"]))
 523
 524            if "firstTradeDate" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["firstTradeDate"] != 0:
 525                info.append("| First trade date:                                       | {}\n".format(iJSON["firstTradeDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "")))
 526
 527            if "lastTradeDate" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["lastTradeDate"] != 0:
 528                info.append("| Last trade date:                                        | {}\n".format(iJSON["lastTradeDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "")))
 529
 530            if "expirationDate" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["expirationDate"] != 0:
 531                info.append("| Date of expiration:                                     | {}\n".format(iJSON["expirationDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "")))
 532
 533            if "stateRegDate" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["stateRegDate"] != 0:
 534                info.append("| State registration date:                                | {}\n".format(iJSON["stateRegDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "")))
 535
 536            if "placementDate" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["placementDate"] != 0:
 537                info.append("| Placement date:                                         | {}\n".format(iJSON["placementDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "")))
 538
 539            if "maturityDate" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["maturityDate"] != 0:
 540                info.append("| Maturity date:                                          | {}\n".format(iJSON["maturityDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "")))
 541
 542            if "perpetualFlag" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["perpetualFlag"]:
 543                info.append("| Perpetual bond:                                         | Yes\n")
 544
 545            if "otcFlag" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["otcFlag"]:
 546                info.append("| Over-the-counter (OTC) securities:                      | Yes\n")
 547
 548            if iJSON["type"] == "Bond":
 549                info.append("| Bond issue (size / plan):                               | {} / {}\n".format(iJSON["issueSize"], iJSON["issueSizePlan"]))
 550
 551                info.append("| Nominal price (100%):                                   | {} {}\n".format(
 552                    NanoToFloat(int(iJSON["nominal"]["units"]), iJSON["nominal"]["nano"]),
 553                    iJSON["nominal"]["currency"],
 554                ))
 555
 556                if "floatingCouponFlag" in iJSON.keys():
 557                    info.append("| Floating coupon:                                        | {}\n".format("Yes" if iJSON["floatingCouponFlag"] else "No"))
 558
 559                if "amortizationFlag" in iJSON.keys():
 560                    info.append("| Amortization:                                           | {}\n".format("Yes" if iJSON["amortizationFlag"] else "No"))
 561
 562                if "couponQuantityPerYear" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["couponQuantityPerYear"]:
 563                    info.append("| Number of coupon payments per year:                     | {}\n".format(iJSON["couponQuantityPerYear"]))
 564
 565                if "aciValue" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["aciValue"]:
 566                    info.append("| Current ACI (Accrued Interest):                         | {} {}\n".format(
 567                        NanoToFloat(int(iJSON["aciValue"]["units"]), iJSON["aciValue"]["nano"]),
 568                        iJSON["aciValue"]["currency"]
 569                    ))
 570
 571            if "currentPrice" in iJSON.keys():
 572                info.append("|                                                         |\n")
 573
 574                info.extend([
 575                    "| Previous close price of the instrument:                 | {}{}\n".format(
 576                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] is not None else "N/A",
 577                        "% of nominal price" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else " {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 578                    ),
 579                    "| Last deal price of the instrument:                      | {}{}\n".format(
 580                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] is not None else "N/A",
 581                        "% of nominal price" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else " {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 582                    ),
 583                    "| Changes between last deal price and last close  %       | {:.2f}%\n".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"]),
 584                    "| Current limit price, min / max:                         | {}{} / {}{}\n".format(
 585                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["limitDown"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["limitDown"] is not None else "N/A",
 586                        "%" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else " {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 587                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["limitUp"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["limitUp"] is not None else "N/A",
 588                        "%" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else " {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 589                    ),
 590                    "| Actual price, sell / buy:                               | {}{} / {}{}\n".format(
 591                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["sell"][0]["price"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["sell"] else "N/A",
 592                        "%" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else " {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 593                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["buy"][0]["price"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["buy"] else "N/A",
 594                        "%" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else" {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 595                    ),
 596                ])
 597
 598            if "lot" in iJSON.keys():
 599                info.append("| Minimum lot to buy:                                     | {}\n".format(iJSON["lot"]))
 600
 601            if "step" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["step"] != 0:
 602                info.append("| Minimum price increment (step):                         | {}\n".format(iJSON["step"]))
 603
 604            infoText += "".join(info)
 605
 606            if printInfo:
 607                uLogger.info("Information about instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}]\n{}".format(iJSON["ticker"], iJSON["figi"], infoText))
 608
 609            else:
 610                uLogger.debug("Information about instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}]\n{}".format(iJSON["ticker"], iJSON["figi"], infoText))
 611
 612        return infoText
 613
 614    def SearchByTicker(self, requestPrice: bool = False, showInfo: bool = False, debug: bool = False) -> dict:
 615        """
 616        Search and return raw broker's information about instrument by it's ticker.
 617        `ticker` must be define! If debug=True then print all debug messages.
 618
 619        :param requestPrice: if `False` then do not request current price of instrument (because this is long operation).
 620        :param showInfo: if `False` then do not run `ShowInstrumentInfo()` method and do not print info to the console.
 621        :param debug: if `True` then print all debug console messages.
 622        :return: JSON formatted data with information about instrument.
 623        """
 624        tickerJSON = {}
 625        if debug:
 626            uLogger.debug("Searching information about instrument by it's ticker [{}] ...".format(self.ticker))
 627
 628        if not self.ticker:
 629            uLogger.warning("self.ticker variable is not be empty!")
 630
 631        else:
 632            if not self.iList:
 633                self.iList = self.Listing()
 634
 635            if self.ticker in self.iList["Shares"].keys():
 636                tickerJSON = self.iList["Shares"][self.ticker]
 637                if debug:
 638                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in stocks list".format(self.ticker))
 639
 640            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Currencies"].keys():
 641                tickerJSON = self.iList["Currencies"][self.ticker]
 642                if debug:
 643                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in currencies list".format(self.ticker))
 644
 645            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Bonds"].keys():
 646                tickerJSON = self.iList["Bonds"][self.ticker]
 647                if debug:
 648                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in bonds list".format(self.ticker))
 649
 650            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Etfs"].keys():
 651                tickerJSON = self.iList["Etfs"][self.ticker]
 652                if debug:
 653                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in etfs list".format(self.ticker))
 654
 655            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Futures"].keys():
 656                tickerJSON = self.iList["Futures"][self.ticker]
 657                if debug:
 658                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in futures list".format(self.ticker))
 659
 660        if tickerJSON:
 661            self.figi = tickerJSON["figi"]
 662
 663            if requestPrice:
 664                tickerJSON["currentPrice"] = self.GetCurrentPrices(showPrice=False)
 665
 666                if tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] is not None and tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] != 0 and tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] is not None:
 667                    tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 100 * (tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] - tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]) / tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]
 668
 669                else:
 670                    tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 0
 671
 672            if showInfo:
 673                self.ShowInstrumentInfo(iJSON=tickerJSON, printInfo=True)  # print info as Markdown text
 674
 675        else:
 676            if showInfo:
 677                uLogger.warning("Ticker [{}] not found in available broker instrument's list!".format(self.ticker))
 678
 679        return tickerJSON
 680
 681    def SearchByFIGI(self, requestPrice: bool = False, showInfo: bool = False, debug: bool = False) -> dict:
 682        """
 683        Search and return raw broker's information about instrument by it's FIGI.
 684        `figi` must be define! If debug=True then print all debug messages.
 685
 686        :param requestPrice: if `False` then do not request current price of instrument (it's long operation).
 687        :param showInfo: if `False` then do not run `ShowInstrumentInfo()` method and do not print info to the console.
 688        :param debug: if `True` then print all debug console messages.
 689        :return: JSON formatted data with information about instrument.
 690        """
 691        figiJSON = {}
 692        if debug:
 693            uLogger.debug("Searching information about instrument by it's FIGI [{}] ...".format(self.figi))
 694
 695        if not self.figi:
 696            uLogger.warning("self.figi variable is not be empty!")
 697
 698        else:
 699            if not self.iList:
 700                self.iList = self.Listing()
 701
 702            for item in self.iList["Shares"].keys():
 703                if self.figi == self.iList["Shares"][item]["figi"]:
 704                    figiJSON = self.iList["Shares"][item]
 705
 706                    if debug:
 707                        uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in stocks list".format(self.figi))
 708
 709                    break
 710
 711            if not figiJSON:
 712                for item in self.iList["Currencies"].keys():
 713                    if self.figi == self.iList["Currencies"][item]["figi"]:
 714                        figiJSON = self.iList["Currencies"][item]
 715
 716                        if debug:
 717                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in currencies list".format(self.figi))
 718
 719                        break
 720
 721            if not figiJSON:
 722                for item in self.iList["Bonds"].keys():
 723                    if self.figi == self.iList["Bonds"][item]["figi"]:
 724                        figiJSON = self.iList["Bonds"][item]
 725
 726                        if debug:
 727                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in bonds list".format(self.figi))
 728
 729                        break
 730
 731            if not figiJSON:
 732                for item in self.iList["Etfs"].keys():
 733                    if self.figi == self.iList["Etfs"][item]["figi"]:
 734                        figiJSON = self.iList["Etfs"][item]
 735
 736                        if debug:
 737                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in etfs list".format(self.figi))
 738
 739                        break
 740
 741            if not figiJSON:
 742                for item in self.iList["Futures"].keys():
 743                    if self.figi == self.iList["Futures"][item]["figi"]:
 744                        figiJSON = self.iList["Futures"][item]
 745
 746                        if debug:
 747                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in futures list".format(self.figi))
 748
 749                        break
 750
 751        if figiJSON:
 752            self.figi = figiJSON["figi"]
 753            self.ticker = figiJSON["ticker"]
 754
 755            if requestPrice:
 756                figiJSON["currentPrice"] = self.GetCurrentPrices(showPrice=False)
 757
 758                if figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] is not None and figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] != 0 and figiJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] is not None:
 759                    figiJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 100 * (figiJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] - figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]) / figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]
 760
 761                else:
 762                    figiJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 0
 763
 764            if showInfo:
 765                self.ShowInstrumentInfo(iJSON=figiJSON, printInfo=True)  # print info as Markdown text
 766
 767        else:
 768            if showInfo:
 769                uLogger.warning("FIGI [{}] not found in available broker instrument's list!".format(self.figi))
 770
 771        return figiJSON
 772
 773    def GetCurrentPrices(self, showPrice: bool = False) -> dict:
 774        """
 775        Get and show Depth of Market with current prices of the instrument. If an error occurred then returns an empty record:
 776        `{"buy": [], "sell": [], "limitUp": None, "limitDown": None, "lastPrice": None, "closePrice": None}`.
 777
 778        :param showPrice: if `True` then print DOM.
 779        :return: dict with Depth of Market (DOM): `{"buy": [{"price": x1, "quantity": y1, ...}], "sell": [....]}` with list of current prices.
 780        """
 781        prices = {"buy": [], "sell": [], "limitUp": 0, "limitDown": 0, "lastPrice": 0, "closePrice": 0}
 782
 783        if self.depth < 1:
 784            raise Exception("Depth of Market (DOM) must be >=1!")
 785
 786        if not (self.ticker or self.figi):
 787            raise Exception("self.ticker or self.figi variables must be defined!")
 788
 789        if self.ticker and not self.figi:
 790            instrumentByTicker = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=False)  # WARNING! requestPrice=False to avoid recursion!
 791            self.figi = instrumentByTicker["figi"] if instrumentByTicker else ""
 792
 793        if not self.ticker and self.figi:
 794            instrumentByFigi = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=False)  # WARNING! requestPrice=False to avoid recursion!
 795            self.ticker = instrumentByFigi["ticker"] if instrumentByFigi else ""
 796
 797        if self.figi:
 798            uLogger.debug("Requesting current prices for instrument with ticker [{}] and FIGI [{}]...".format(self.ticker, self.figi))
 799
 800            # REST API for request: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/MarketDataService/MarketDataService_GetOrderBook
 801            priceURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.MarketDataService/GetOrderBook"
 802            self.body = str({"figi": self.figi, "depth": self.depth})
 803            pricesResponse = self.SendAPIRequest(priceURL, reqType="POST")
 804
 805            if pricesResponse:
 806                # list of dicts with sellers orders:
 807                prices["buy"] = [{"price": NanoToFloat(item["price"]["units"], item["price"]["nano"]), "quantity": int(item["quantity"])} for item in pricesResponse["asks"]]
 808
 809                # list of dicts with buyers orders:
 810                prices["sell"] = [{"price": NanoToFloat(item["price"]["units"], item["price"]["nano"]), "quantity": int(item["quantity"])} for item in pricesResponse["bids"]]
 811
 812                # max price of instrument at this time:
 813                prices["limitUp"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["limitUp"]["units"], pricesResponse["limitUp"]["nano"]) if "limitUp" in pricesResponse.keys() else None
 814
 815                # min price of instrument at this time:
 816                prices["limitDown"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["limitDown"]["units"], pricesResponse["limitDown"]["nano"]) if "limitDown" in pricesResponse.keys() else None
 817
 818                # last price of deal with instrument:
 819                prices["lastPrice"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["lastPrice"]["units"], pricesResponse["lastPrice"]["nano"]) if "lastPrice" in pricesResponse.keys() else 0
 820
 821                # last close price of instrument:
 822                prices["closePrice"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["closePrice"]["units"], pricesResponse["closePrice"]["nano"]) if "closePrice" in pricesResponse.keys() else 0
 823
 824            else:
 825                uLogger.warning("Server return an empty or error response! See full log. Instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}]".format(self.ticker, self.figi))
 826                uLogger.debug("Server response: {}".format(pricesResponse))
 827
 828            if showPrice:
 829                if prices["buy"] or prices["sell"]:
 830                    info = [
 831                        "Orders book actual at [{}] (UTC)\nTicker: [{}], FIGI: [{}], Depth of Market: [{}]\n".format(
 832                            datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"),
 833                            self.ticker,
 834                            self.figi,
 835                            self.depth,
 836                        ),
 837                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
 838                        " Orders of Buyers   | Orders of Sellers\n",
 839                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
 840                        " Sell prices (vol.) | Buy prices (vol.)\n",
 841                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
 842                    ]
 843
 844                    if not prices["buy"]:
 845                        info.append("                    | No orders!\n")
 846                        sumBuy = 0
 847
 848                    else:
 849                        sumBuy = sum([x["quantity"] for x in prices["buy"]])
 850                        maxMinSorted = sorted(prices["buy"], key=lambda k: k["price"], reverse=True)
 851                        for item in maxMinSorted:
 852                            info.append("                    | {} ({})\n".format(item["price"], item["quantity"]))
 853
 854                    if not prices["sell"]:
 855                        info.append("No orders!          |\n")
 856                        sumSell = 0
 857
 858                    else:
 859                        sumSell = sum([x["quantity"] for x in prices["sell"]])
 860                        for item in prices["sell"]:
 861                            info.append("{:>19} |\n".format("{} ({})".format(item["price"], item["quantity"])))
 862
 863                    info.extend([
 864                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
 865                        "{:>19} | {}\n".format("Total sell: {}".format(sumSell), "Total buy: {}".format(sumBuy)),
 866                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
 867                    ])
 868
 869                    infoText = "".join(info)
 870
 871                    uLogger.info("Current prices in order book:\n\n{}".format(infoText))
 872
 873                else:
 874                    uLogger.warning("Orders book is empty at this time! Instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}]".format(self.ticker, self.figi))
 875
 876        else:
 877            uLogger.error("FIGI is not defined!")
 878
 879        return prices
 880
 881    def ShowInstrumentsInfo(self, showInstruments: bool = False) -> str:
 882        """
 883        This method get and show information about all available broker instruments.
 884        If `instrumentsFile` string is not empty then also save information to this file.
 885
 886        :param showInstruments: if `True` then print to console, if `False` - print only to file.
 887        :return: multi-string with all available broker instruments
 888        """
 889        if not self.iList:
 890            self.iList = self.Listing()
 891
 892        info = [
 893            "# All available instruments from Tinkoff Broker server for current user token\n\n",
 894            "* **Actual on date:** [{}] (UTC)\n".format(datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")),
 895        ]
 896
 897        # add instruments count by type:
 898        for iType in self.iList.keys():
 899            info.append("* **{}:** [{}]\n".format(iType, len(self.iList[iType])))
 900
 901        headerLine = "| Ticker       | Full name                                                      | FIGI         | Cur | Lot    | Step\n"
 902        splitLine = "|--------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|--------------|-----|--------|---------\n"
 903
 904        # generate info tables with all instruments by type:
 905        for iType in self.iList.keys():
 906            info.extend(["\n\n## {} available. Total: [{}]\n\n".format(iType, len(self.iList[iType])), headerLine, splitLine])
 907
 908            for instrument in self.iList[iType].keys():
 909                iName = self.iList[iType][instrument]["name"]  # instrument's name
 910                if len(iName) > 63:
 911                    iName = "{}...".format(iName[:60])  # right trim for a long string
 912    
 913                info.append("| {:<12} | {:<63}| {:<13}| {:<4}| {:<7}| {}\n".format(
 914                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["ticker"],
 915                    iName,
 916                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["figi"],
 917                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["currency"],
 918                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["lot"],
 919                    str(self.iList[iType][instrument]["step"]).rstrip("0"),
 920                ))
 921
 922        infoText = "".join(info)
 923
 924        if showInstruments:
 925            uLogger.info(infoText)
 926
 927        if self.instrumentsFile:
 928            with open(self.instrumentsFile, "w", encoding="UTF-8") as fH:
 929                fH.write(infoText)
 930
 931            uLogger.info("All available instruments are saved to file: [{}]".format(os.path.abspath(self.instrumentsFile)))
 932
 933        return infoText
 934
 935    def GetListOfPrices(self, instruments: list = None, showPrices: bool = False) -> list:
 936        """
 937        This method get, maybe show and return prices of list of instruments. WARNING! This is potential long operation!
 938        See limits: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/limits/
 939        If `pricesFile` string is not empty then also save information to this file.
 940
 941        :param instruments: list of tickers or FIGIs.
 942        :param showPrices: if `True` then print to console, if `False` - print only to file.
 943        :return: list of instruments looks like this: `iList = [{some ticker info, "currentPrice": {current prices}}, {...}, ...]`
 944                 One item is dict returned by `SearchByTicker()` or `SearchByFIGI()` methods.
 945        """
 946        if instruments is None or not instruments:
 947            raise Exception("You must define some of tickers or FIGIs to request it's actual prices!")
 948
 949        uLogger.debug("Requesting current prices of list of instruments from Tinkoff Broker server...")
 950
 951        iList = []
 952        for iName in instruments:
 953            if iName not in self.aliases.keys():
 954                iList.append(iName)
 955
 956            else:
 957                iList.append(self.aliases[iName])
 958
 959        unique = set()  # create list with every figi only one time with the same order position:
 960        tempNames = [item for item in iList if not (item in unique or unique.add(item))]
 961
 962        uLogger.debug("Ordered input list of instruments without duplicates of names: {}".format(tempNames))
 963
 964        iList = []  # try to get info about all unique instruments:
 965        for iName in tempNames:
 966            self.ticker = iName
 967            iData = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=True)
 968
 969            if not iData:
 970                self.ticker = ""
 971                self.figi = iName
 972
 973                iData = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True)
 974
 975                if not iData:
 976                    self.figi = ""
 977                    uLogger.warning("Instrument [{}] not in list of available instruments for current token!".format(iName))
 978
 979            if iData:
 980                isUnique = True
 981                for item in iList:
 982                    if item["figi"] == iData["figi"] or item["ticker"] == iData["ticker"]:
 983                        isUnique = False
 984                        break
 985
 986                if isUnique:
 987                    iList.append(iData)
 988
 989        if showPrices:
 990            info = [
 991                "# Actual prices at: [{} UTC]\n\n".format(datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")),
 992                "| Ticker       | FIGI         | Type       | Prev. close | Last price  | Chg. %   | Day limits min/max  | Actual sell / buy   | Curr.\n",
 993                "|--------------|--------------|------------|-------------|-------------|----------|---------------------|---------------------|------\n",
 994            ]
 995
 996            for item in iList:
 997                info.append("| {:<12} | {:<12} | {:<10} | {:>11} | {:>11} | {:>7}% | {:>19} | {:>19} | {}\n".format(
 998                    item["ticker"],
 999                    item["figi"],
1000                    item["type"],
1001                    "{:.2f}".format(float(item["currentPrice"]["closePrice"])),
1002                    "{:.2f}".format(float(item["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"])),
1003                    "{}{:.2f}".format("+" if item["currentPrice"]["changes"] > 0 else "", float(item["currentPrice"]["changes"])),
1004                    "{} / {}".format(
1005                        item["currentPrice"]["limitDown"] if item["currentPrice"]["limitDown"] is not None else "N/A",
1006                        item["currentPrice"]["limitUp"] if item["currentPrice"]["limitUp"] is not None else "N/A",
1007                    ),
1008                    "{} / {}".format(
1009                        item["currentPrice"]["sell"][0]["price"] if item["currentPrice"]["sell"] else "N/A",
1010                        item["currentPrice"]["buy"][0]["price"] if item["currentPrice"]["buy"] else "N/A",
1011                    ),
1012                    item["currency"],
1013                ))
1014
1015            infoText = "".join(info)
1016
1017            if showPrices:
1018                uLogger.info("Only unique instruments are shown:\n{}".format(infoText))
1019
1020            if self.pricesFile:
1021                with open(self.pricesFile, "w", encoding="UTF-8") as fH:
1022                    fH.write(infoText)
1023
1024                uLogger.info("Price list for all instruments saved to file: [{}]".format(os.path.abspath(self.pricesFile)))
1025
1026        return iList
1027
1028    def RequestPortfolio(self) -> dict:
1029        """
1030        Requesting current actual user's portfolio.
1031        REST API for user portfolio: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/OperationsService/OperationsService_GetPortfolio
1032
1033        :return: dictionary with user's portfolio.
1034        """
1035        uLogger.debug("Requesting current actual user's portfolio. Wait, please...")
1036
1037        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId})
1038        portfolioURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OperationsService/GetPortfolio"
1039        rawPortfolio = self.SendAPIRequest(portfolioURL, reqType="POST")
1040
1041        uLogger.debug("Records about user's portfolio successfully received")
1042
1043        return rawPortfolio
1044
1045    def RequestPositions(self) -> dict:
1046        """
1047        Requesting current open positions in currencies and instruments.
1048        REST API for open positions: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/OperationsService/OperationsService_GetPositions
1049
1050        :return: dictionary with open positions by instruments.
1051        """
1052        uLogger.debug("Requesting current open positions in currencies and instruments. Wait, please...")
1053
1054        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId})
1055        positionsURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OperationsService/GetPositions"
1056        rawPositions = self.SendAPIRequest(positionsURL, reqType="POST")
1057
1058        uLogger.debug("Records about current open positions successfully received")
1059
1060        return rawPositions
1061
1062    def RequestPendingOrders(self) -> list:
1063        """
1064        Requesting current actual pending orders.
1065        REST API for pending (market) orders: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/OrdersService/OrdersService_GetOrders
1066
1067        :return: list of dictionaries with pending orders.
1068        """
1069        uLogger.debug("Requesting current actual pending orders. Wait, please...")
1070
1071        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId})
1072        ordersURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OrdersService/GetOrders"
1073        rawOrders = self.SendAPIRequest(ordersURL, reqType="POST")["orders"]
1074
1075        uLogger.debug("[{}] records about pending orders successfully received".format(len(rawOrders)))
1076
1077        return rawOrders
1078
1079    def RequestStopOrders(self) -> list:
1080        """
1081        Requesting current actual stop orders.
1082        REST API for opened stop-orders: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/StopOrdersService/StopOrdersService_GetStopOrders
1083
1084        :return: list of dictionaries with stop orders.
1085        """
1086        uLogger.debug("Requesting current actual stop orders. Wait, please...")
1087
1088        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId})
1089        ordersURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.StopOrdersService/GetStopOrders"

1091
