2146    def Trade(self, operation: str, lots: int = 1, tp: float = 0., sl: float = 0., expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2147        """
2148        Universal method to create market order and make deal at the current price. Returns JSON data with response.
2149        If `tp` or `sl` > 0, then in additional will opens stop-orders with "TP" and "SL" flags for `stopType` parameter.
2150
2151        See also: `Order()` docstring. More simple methods than `Trade()` are `Buy()` and `Sell()`.
2152
2153        :param operation: string "Buy" or "Sell".
2154        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2155        :param tp: float > 0, target price for stop-order with "TP" type. It used as take profit parameter `targetPrice` in `self.Order()`.
2156        :param sl: float > 0, target price for stop-order with "SL" type. It used as stop loss parameter `targetPrice` in `self.Order()`.
2157        :param expDate: string "Undefined" by default or local date in future,
2158                        it is a string with format `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2159        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2160        """
2161        if operation is None or not operation or operation not in ("Buy", "Sell"):
2162            raise Exception("You must define operation type only one of them: `Buy` or `Sell`!")
2163
2164        if lots is None or lots < 1:
2165            uLogger.warning("You must define trade volume > 0: integer count of lots! For current operation lots reset to 1.")
2166            lots = 1
2167
2168        if tp is None or tp < 0:
2169            tp = 0
2170
2171        if sl is None or sl < 0:
2172            sl = 0
2173
2174        if expDate is None or not expDate:
2175            expDate = "Undefined"
2176
2177        if not (self.ticker or self.figi):
2178            raise Exception("`self.ticker` or `self.figi` variables must be defined!")
2179
2180        instrument = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=True, debug=False) if self.ticker else self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True, debug=False)
2181        self.ticker = instrument["ticker"]
2182        self.figi = instrument["figi"]
2183
2184        uLogger.debug("Opening [{}] market order: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], lots [{}], TP [{:.4f}], SL [{:.4f}], expiration date of TP/SL orders [{}]. Wait, please...".format(operation, self.ticker, self.figi, lots, tp, sl, expDate))
2185
2186        openTradeURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OrdersService/PostOrder"
2187        self.body = str({
2188            "figi": self.figi,
2189            "quantity": str(lots),
2190            "direction": "ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY" if operation == "Buy" else "ORDER_DIRECTION_SELL",  # see: TKS_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
2191            "accountId": str(self.accountId),
2192            "orderType": "ORDER_TYPE_MARKET",  # see: TKS_ORDER_TYPES
2193        })
2194        response = self.SendAPIRequest(openTradeURL, reqType="POST", retry=0, debug=False)
2195
2196        if "orderId" in response.keys():
2197            uLogger.info("[{}] market order [{}] was executed: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], lots [{}]. Total order price: [{:.4f} {}] (with commission: [{:.2f} {}]). Average price of lot: [{:.2f} {}]".format(
2198                operation, response["orderId"],
2199                self.ticker, self.figi, lots,
2200                NanoToFloat(response["totalOrderAmount"]["units"], response["totalOrderAmount"]["nano"]), response["totalOrderAmount"]["currency"],
2201                NanoToFloat(response["initialCommission"]["units"], response["initialCommission"]["nano"]), response["initialCommission"]["currency"],
2202                NanoToFloat(response["executedOrderPrice"]["units"], response["executedOrderPrice"]["nano"]), response["executedOrderPrice"]["currency"],
2203            ))
2204
2205        else:
2206            uLogger.warning("Not `oK` status received! Market order not created. See full debug log or try again and open order later.")
2207
2208        if tp > 0:
2209            self.Order(operation="Sell" if operation == "Buy" else "Buy", orderType="Stop", lots=lots, targetPrice=tp, limitPrice=tp, stopType="TP", expDate=expDate)
2210
2211        if sl > 0:
2212            self.Order(operation="Sell" if operation == "Buy" else "Buy", orderType="Stop", lots=lots, targetPrice=sl, limitPrice=sl, stopType="SL", expDate=expDate)
2213
2214        return response
2215
2216    def Buy(self, lots: int = 1, tp: float = 0., sl: float = 0., expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2217        """
2218        More simple method than `Trade()`. Create `Buy` market order and make deal at the current price. Returns JSON data with response.
2219        If `tp` or `sl` > 0, then in additional will opens stop-orders with "TP" and "SL" flags for `stopType` parameter.
2220
2221        See also: `Order()` and `Trade()` docstrings.
2222
2223        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2224        :param tp: float > 0, take profit price of stop-order.
2225        :param sl: float > 0, stop loss price of stop-order.
2226        :param expDate: it's a local date in future.
2227                        String has a format like this: `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2228        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2229        """
2230        return self.Trade(operation="Buy", lots=lots, tp=tp, sl=sl, expDate=expDate)
2231
2232    def Sell(self, lots: int = 1, tp: float = 0., sl: float = 0., expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2233        """
2234        More simple method than `Trade()`. Create `Sell` market order and make deal at the current price. Returns JSON data with response.
2235        If `tp` or `sl` > 0, then in additional will opens stop-orders with "TP" and "SL" flags for `stopType` parameter.
2236
2237        See also: `Order()` and `Trade()` docstrings.
2238
2239        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2240        :param tp: float > 0, take profit price of stop-order.
2241        :param sl: float > 0, stop loss price of stop-order.
2242        :param expDate: it's a local date in future.
2243                        String has a format like this: `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2244        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2245        """
2246        return self.Trade(operation="Sell", lots=lots, tp=tp, sl=sl, expDate=expDate)
2247
2248    def CloseTrades(self, tickers: list, overview: dict = None) -> None:
2249        """
2250        Close position of given instruments.
2251
2252        :param tickers: tickers list of instruments that must be closed.
2253        :param overview: pre-received dictionary with open trades, returned by `Overview()` method.
2254                         This avoids unnecessary downloading data from the server.
2255        """
2256        if not tickers:
2257            uLogger.info("Tickers list empty, nothing to close.")
2258
2259        else:
2260            if overview is None or not overview:
2261                overview = self.Overview(showStatistics=False)
2262
2263            allOpenedTickers = [item["ticker"] for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS for item in overview["stat"][iType]]
2264            uLogger.debug("All opened instruments by it's tickers names: {}".format(allOpenedTickers))
2265
2266            for ticker in tickers:
2267                if not ticker in allOpenedTickers:
2268                    uLogger.warning("Instrument with ticker [{}] not in open positions list!".format(ticker))
2269                    continue
2270
2271                # search open trade info about instrument by ticker:
2272                instrument = {}
2273                for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
2274                    if instrument:
2275                        break
2276
2277                    for item in overview["stat"][iType]:
2278                        if item["ticker"] == ticker:
2279                            instrument = item
2280                            break
2281
2282                if instrument:
2283                    self.ticker = ticker
2284                    self.figi = instrument["figi"]
2285
2286                    uLogger.debug("Closing trade of instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI[{}], lots [{}]{}. Wait, please...".format(
2287                        self.ticker,
2288                        self.figi,
2289                        int(instrument["volume"]),
2290                        ", blocked [{}]".format(instrument["blocked"]) if instrument["blocked"] > 0 else "",
2291                    ))
2292
2293                    tradeLots = abs(instrument["lots"]) - instrument["blocked"]  # available volumes in lots for close operation
2294
2295                    if tradeLots > 0:
2296                        if instrument["blocked"] > 0:
2297                            uLogger.warning("Just for your information: there are [{}] lots blocked for instrument [{}]! Available only [{}] lots to closing trade.".format(
2298                                instrument["blocked"],
2299                                self.ticker,
2300                                tradeLots,
2301                            ))
2302
2303                        # if direction is "Long" then we need sell, if direction is "Short" then we need buy:
2304                        self.Trade(operation="Sell" if instrument["direction"] == "Long" else "Buy", lots=tradeLots)
2305
2306                    else:
2307                        uLogger.warning("There are no available lots for instrument [{}] to closing trade at this moment! Try again later or cancel some orders.".format(self.ticker))
2308
2309    def CloseAllTrades(self, iType: str, overview: dict = None) -> None:
2310        """
2311        Close all positions of given instruments with defined type.
2312
2313        :param iType: type of the instruments that be closed, it must be one of supported types in TKS_INSTRUMENTS list.
2314        :param overview: pre-received dictionary with open trades, returned by `Overview()` method.
2315                         This avoids unnecessary downloading data from the server.
2316        """
2317        if iType not in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
2318            uLogger.warning("Type of the instrument must be one of supported types: {}. Given: [{}]".format(", ".join(TKS_INSTRUMENTS), iType))
2319
2320        else:
2321            if overview is None or not overview:
2322                overview = self.Overview(showStatistics=False)
2323
2324            tickers = [item["ticker"] for item in overview["stat"][iType]]
2325            uLogger.debug("Instrument tickers with type [{}] that will be closed: {}".format(iType, tickers))
2326
2327            if tickers and overview:
2328                self.CloseTrades(tickers, overview)
2329
2330            else:
2331                uLogger.info("Instrument tickers with type [{}] not found, nothing to close.".format(iType))
2332
2333    def Order(self, operation: str, orderType: str, lots: int, targetPrice: float, limitPrice: float = 0., stopType: str = "Limit", expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2334        """
2335        Universal method to create market or limit orders with all available parameters.
2336        See more simple methods: `BuyLimit()`, `BuyStop()`, `SellLimit()`, `SellStop()`.
2337
2338        If orderType is "Limit" then create pending limit-order below current price if operation is "Buy" and above
2339        current price if operation is "Sell". A limit order has no expiration date, it lasts until the end of the trading day.
2340
2341        Warning! If you try to create limit-order above current price if "Buy" or below current price if "Sell"
2342        then broker immediately open market order as you can do simple --buy or --sell operations!
2343
2344        If orderType is "Stop" then creates stop-order with any direction "Buy" or "Sell".
2345        When current price will go up or down to target price value then broker opens a limit order.
2346        Stop-order is opened with unlimited expiration date by default, or you can define expiration date with expDate parameter.
2347
2348        Only one attempt and no retry for opens order. If network issue occurred you can create new request.
2349
2350        :param operation: string "Buy" or "Sell".
2351        :param orderType: string "Limit" or "Stop".
2352        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2353        :param targetPrice: target price > 0. This is open trade price for limit order.
2354        :param limitPrice: limit price >= 0. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order. If limitPrice = 0, then it set as targetPrice.
2355                           Broker will creates limit-order with price equal to limitPrice, when current price goes to target price of stop-order.
2356        :param stopType: string "Limit" by default. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order. There are 3 stop-order types
2357                         "SL", "TP", "Limit" for "Stop loss", "Take profit" and "Stop limit" types accordingly.
2358                         Stop loss order always executed by market price.
2359        :param expDate: string "Undefined" by default or local date in future.
2360                        String has a format like this: `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2361                        This date is converting to UTC format for server. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order.
2362                        A limit order has no expiration date, it lasts until the end of the trading day.
2363        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2364        """
2365        if operation is None or not operation or operation not in ("Buy", "Sell"):
2366            raise Exception("You must define operation type only one of them: `Buy` or `Sell`!")
2367
2368        if orderType is None or not orderType or orderType not in ("Limit", "Stop"):
2369            raise Exception("You must define order type only one of them: `Limit` or `Stop`!")
2370
2371        if lots is None or lots < 1:
2372            raise Exception("You must define trade volume > 0: integer count of lots!")
2373
2374        if targetPrice is None or targetPrice <= 0:
2375            raise Exception("Target price for limit-order must be greater than 0!")
2376
2377        if limitPrice is None or limitPrice <= 0:
2378            limitPrice = targetPrice
2379
2380        if stopType is None or not stopType or stopType not in ("SL", "TP", "Limit"):
2381            stopType = "Limit"
2382
2383        if expDate is None or not expDate:
2384            expDate = "Undefined"
2385
2386        if not (self.ticker or self.figi):
2387            raise Exception("`self.ticker` or `self.figi` variables must be defined!")
2388
2389        response = {}
2390        instrument = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=True, debug=False) if self.ticker else self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True, debug=False)
2391        self.ticker = instrument["ticker"]
2392        self.figi = instrument["figi"]
2393
2394        if orderType == "Limit":
2395            uLogger.debug(
2396                "Creating pending limit-order: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}] and the target price [{:.2f} {}]. Wait, please...".format(
2397                    self.ticker, self.figi,
2398                    operation, lots, targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2399                ))
2400
2401            openOrderURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OrdersService/PostOrder"
2402            self.body = str({
2403                "figi": self.figi,
2404                "quantity": str(lots),
2405                "price": FloatToNano(targetPrice),
2406                "direction": "ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY" if operation == "Buy" else "ORDER_DIRECTION_SELL",  # see: TKS_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
2407                "accountId": str(self.accountId),
2408                "orderType": "ORDER_TYPE_LIMIT",  # see: TKS_ORDER_TYPES
2409            })
2410            response = self.SendAPIRequest(openOrderURL, reqType="POST", retry=0, debug=False)
2411
2412            if "orderId" in response.keys():
2413                uLogger.info(
2414                    "Limit-order [{}] was created: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}], target price [{:.2f} {}]".format(
2415                        response["orderId"],
2416                        self.ticker, self.figi,
2417                        operation, lots, targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2418                    ))
2419
2420                if "lastPrice" in instrument["currentPrice"].keys() and instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2421                    if operation == "Buy" and targetPrice > instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2422                        uLogger.warning("Your order was executed as a market order, not as a limit order! Comment: because your target price [{:.2f} {}] was higher than current price [{:.2f} {}] broker immediately opened `Buy` market order, such as if you did simple `--buy` operation.".format(
2423                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2424                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2425                        ))
2426
2427                    if operation == "Sell" and targetPrice < instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2428                        uLogger.warning("Your order was executed as a market order, not as a limit order! Comment: because your target price [{:.2f} {}] was lower than current price [{:.2f} {}] broker immediately opened `Sell` market order, such as if you did simple `--sell` operation.".format(
2429                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2430                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2431                        ))
2432
2433            else:
2434                uLogger.warning("Not `oK` status received! Limit order not opened. See full debug log or try again and open order later.")
2435
2436        if orderType == "Stop":
2437            uLogger.debug(
2438                "Creating stop-order: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}], target price [{:.2f} {}], limit price [{:.2f} {}], stop-order type [{}] and local expiration date [{}]. Wait, please...".format(
2439                    self.ticker, self.figi,
2440                    operation, lots,
2441                    targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2442                    limitPrice, instrument["currency"],
2443                    stopType, expDate,
2444                ))
2445
2446            openOrderURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.StopOrdersService/PostStopOrder"
2447            expDateUTC = "" if expDate == "Undefined" else datetime.strptime(expDate, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S").replace(tzinfo=tzlocal()).astimezone(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%fZ")
2448            stopOrderType = "STOP_ORDER_TYPE_STOP_LOSS" if stopType == "SL" else "STOP_ORDER_TYPE_TAKE_PROFIT" if stopType == "TP" else "STOP_ORDER_TYPE_STOP_LIMIT"
2449
2450            body = {
2451                "figi": self.figi,
2452                "quantity": str(lots),
2453                "price": FloatToNano(limitPrice),
2454                "stopPrice": FloatToNano(targetPrice),
2455                "direction": "STOP_ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY" if operation == "Buy" else "STOP_ORDER_DIRECTION_SELL",  # see: TKS_STOP_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
2456                "accountId": str(self.accountId),
2457                "expirationType": "STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_GOOD_TILL_DATE" if expDateUTC else "STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_GOOD_TILL_CANCEL",  # see: TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES
2458                "stopOrderType": stopOrderType,  # see: TKS_STOP_ORDER_TYPES
2459            }
2460
2461            if expDateUTC:
2462                body["expireDate"] = expDateUTC
2463
2464            self.body = str(body)
2465            response = self.SendAPIRequest(openOrderURL, reqType="POST", retry=0, debug=False)
2466
2467            if "stopOrderId" in response.keys():
2468                uLogger.info(
2469                    "Stop-order [{}] was created: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}], target price [{:.2f} {}], limit price [{:.2f} {}], stop-order type [{}] and expiration date in UTC [{}]".format(
2470                    response["stopOrderId"],
2471                    self.ticker, self.figi,
2472                    operation, lots,
2473                    targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2474                    limitPrice, instrument["currency"],
2475                    TKS_STOP_ORDER_TYPES[stopOrderType],
2476                    datetime.strptime(expDateUTC, "%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%fZ").replace(tzinfo=tzutc()).astimezone(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S") if expDateUTC else TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES["STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED"],
2477                ))
2478
2479                if "lastPrice" in instrument["currentPrice"].keys() and instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2480                    if operation == "Buy" and targetPrice < instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] and stopType != "TP":
2481                        uLogger.warning("The broker will cancel this order after some time. Comment: you placed the wrong stop order because the target buy price [{:.2f} {}] is lower than the current price [{:.2f} {}]. Also try to set up order type as `TP` if you want to place stop order at that price.".format(
2482                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2483                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2484                        ))
2485
2486                    if operation == "Sell" and targetPrice > instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] and stopType != "TP":
2487                        uLogger.warning("The broker will cancel this order after some time. Comment: you placed the wrong stop order because the target sell price [{:.2f} {}] is higher than the current price [{:.2f} {}]. Also try to set up order type as `TP` if you want to place stop order at that price.".format(
2488                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2489                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2490                        ))
2491
2492            else:
2493                uLogger.warning("Not `oK` status received! Stop order not opened. See full debug log or try again and open order later.")
2494
2495        return response
2496
2497    def BuyLimit(self, lots: int, targetPrice: float) -> dict:
2498        """
2499        Create pending `Buy` limit-order (below current price). You must specify only 2 parameters:
2500        `lots` and `target price` to open buy limit-order. If you try to create buy limit-order above current price then
2501        broker immediately open `Buy` market order, such as if you do simple `--buy` operation!
2502        See also: `Order()` docstring.
2503
2504        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2505        :param targetPrice: target price > 0. This is open trade price for limit order.
2506        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2507        """
2508        return self.Order(operation="Buy", orderType="Limit", lots=lots, targetPrice=targetPrice)
2509
2510    def BuyStop(self, lots: int, targetPrice: float, limitPrice: float = 0., stopType: str = "Limit", expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2511        """
2512        Create `Buy` stop-order. You must specify at least 2 parameters: `lots` `target price` to open buy stop-order.
2513        In additional you can specify 3 parameters for buy stop-order: `limit price` >=0, `stop type` = Limit|SL|TP,
2514        `expiration date` = Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`. When current price will go up or down to
2515        target price value then broker opens a limit order. See also: `Order()` docstring.
2516
2517        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2518        :param targetPrice: target price > 0. This is trigger price for buy stop-order.
2519        :param limitPrice: limit price >= 0 (limitPrice = targetPrice if limitPrice is 0). Broker will creates limit-order
2520                           with price equal to limitPrice, when current price goes to target price of buy stop-order.
2521        :param stopType: string "Limit" by default. There are 3 stop-order types "SL", "TP", "Limit"
2522                         for "Stop loss", "Take profit" and "Stop limit" types accordingly.
2523        :param expDate: string "Undefined" by default or local date in future.
2524                        String has a format like this: `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2525                        This date is converting to UTC format for server.
2526        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2527        """
2528        return self.Order(operation="Buy", orderType="Stop", lots=lots, targetPrice=targetPrice, limitPrice=limitPrice, stopType=stopType, expDate=expDate)
2529

2563    def CloseOrders(self, orderIDs: list, allOrdersIDs: list = None, allStopOrdersIDs: list = None) -> None:
2564        """
2565        Cancel order or list of orders by its `orderId` or `stopOrderId`.
2566
2567        :param orderIDs: list of integers with `orderId` or `stopOrderId`.
2568        :param allOrdersIDs: pre-received lists of all active pending orders.
2569                             This avoids unnecessary downloading data from the server.
2570        :param allStopOrdersIDs: pre-received lists of all active stop orders.
2571        """
2572        if orderIDs:
2573            if allOrdersIDs is None or not allOrdersIDs:
2574                rawOrders = self.RequestPendingOrders()
2575                allOrdersIDs = [item["orderId"] for item in rawOrders]  # all pending orders ID
2576
2577            if allStopOrdersIDs is None or not allStopOrdersIDs:
2578                rawStopOrders = self.RequestStopOrders()
2579                allStopOrdersIDs = [item["stopOrderId"] for item in rawStopOrders]  # all stop orders ID
2580
2581            for orderID in orderIDs:
2582                idInPendingOrders = orderID in allOrdersIDs
2583                idInStopOrders = orderID in allStopOrdersIDs
2584
2585                if not (idInPendingOrders or idInStopOrders):
2586                    uLogger.warning("Order not found by ID: [{}]. Maybe cancelled already? Check it with `--overview` key.".format(orderID))
2587                    continue
2588
2589                else:
2590                    if idInPendingOrders:
2591                        uLogger.debug("Cancelling pending order with ID: [{}]. Wait, please...".format(orderID))
2592
2593                        # REST API for request: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/OrdersService/OrdersService_CancelOrder
2594                        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId, "orderId": orderID})
2595                        closeURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OrdersService/CancelOrder"
2596                        responseJSON = self.SendAPIRequest(closeURL, reqType="POST")
2597
2598                        if responseJSON and "time" in responseJSON.keys() and responseJSON["time"]:
2599                            uLogger.debug("Success time marker received from server: [{}] (UTC)".format(responseJSON["time"]))
2600                            uLogger.info("Pending order with ID [{}] successfully cancel".format(orderID))
2601
2602                        else:
2603                            uLogger.warning("Unknown issue occurred when cancelling pending order with ID: [{}]. Check ID and try again.".format(orderID))
2604
2605                    elif idInStopOrders:
2606                        uLogger.debug("Cancelling stop order with ID: [{}]. Wait, please...".format(orderID))
2607
2608                        # REST API for request: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/StopOrdersService/StopOrdersService_CancelStopOrder
2609                        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId, "stopOrderId": orderID})
2610                        closeURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.StopOrdersService/CancelStopOrder"
2611                        responseJSON = self.SendAPIRequest(closeURL, reqType="POST")
2612
2613                        if responseJSON and "time" in responseJSON.keys() and responseJSON["time"]:
2614                            uLogger.debug("Success time marker received from server: [{}] (UTC)".format(responseJSON["time"]))
2615                            uLogger.info("Stop order with ID [{}] successfully cancel".format(orderID))
2616
2617                        else:
2618                            uLogger.warning("Unknown issue occurred when cancelling stop order with ID: [{}]. Check ID and try again.".format(orderID))
2619
2620                    else:
2621                        continue
2622
2623    def CloseAllOrders(self) -> None:
2624        """
2625        Gets a list of open pending and stop orders and cancel it all.
2626        """
2627        rawOrders = self.RequestPendingOrders()
2628        allOrdersIDs = [item["orderId"] for item in rawOrders]  # all pending orders ID
2629        lenOrders = len(allOrdersIDs)
2630
2631        rawStopOrders = self.RequestStopOrders()
2632        allStopOrdersIDs = [item["stopOrderId"] for item in rawStopOrders]  # all stop orders ID
2633        lenSOrders = len(allStopOrdersIDs)
2634
2635        if lenOrders > 0 or lenSOrders > 0:
2636            uLogger.info("Found: [{}] opened pending and [{}] stop orders. Let's trying to cancel it all. Wait, please...".format(lenOrders, lenSOrders))
2637
2638            self.CloseOrders(allOrdersIDs + allStopOrdersIDs, allOrdersIDs, allStopOrdersIDs)
2639
2640        else:
2641            uLogger.info("Orders not found, nothing to cancel.")
2642
2643    def CloseAll(self, *args) -> None:
2644        """
2645        Close all available (not blocked) opened trades and orders.
2646
2647        Also you can select one or more keywords case insensitive:
2648        `orders`, `shares`, `bonds`, `etfs` and `futures` from `TKS_INSTRUMENTS` enum to specify trades type.
2649
2650        Currency positions you must closes manually using buy or sell operations, `CloseTrades()` or `CloseAllTrades()` methods.
2651        """
2652        overview = self.Overview(showStatistics=False)  # get all open trades info
2653
2654        if len(args) == 0:
2655            uLogger.debug("Closing all available (not blocked) opened trades and orders. Currency positions you must closes manually using buy or sell operations! Wait, please...")
2656            self.CloseAllOrders()  # close all pending and stop orders
2657
2658            for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
2659                if iType != "Currencies":
2660                    self.CloseAllTrades(iType, overview)  # close all positions of instruments with same type without currencies
2661
2662        else:
2663            uLogger.debug("Closing all available {}. Currency positions you must closes manually using buy or sell operations! Wait, please...".format(list(args)))
2664            lowerArgs = [x.lower() for x in args]
2665
2666            if "orders" in lowerArgs:
2667                self.CloseAllOrders()  # close all pending and stop orders
2668
2669            for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
2670                if iType.lower() in lowerArgs and iType != "Currencies":
2671                    self.CloseAllTrades(iType, overview)  # close all positions of instruments with same type without currencies
2672
2673    @staticmethod
2674    def ParseOrderParameters(operation, **inputParameters):
2675        """
2676        Parse input dictionary of strings with order parameters and return dictionary with parameters to open all orders.
2677
2678        :param operation: string "Buy" or "Sell".
2679        :param inputParameters: this is dict of strings that looks like this
2680               `{"lots": "L_int,...", "prices": "P_float,..."}` where
2681               "lots" key: one or more lot values (integer numbers) to open with every limit-order
2682               "prices" key: one or more prices to open limit-orders
2683               Counts of values in lots and prices lists must be equals!
2684        :return: list of dictionaries with all lots and prices to open orders that looks like this `[{"lot": lots_1, "price": price_1}, {...}, ...]`
2685        """
2686        # TODO: update order grid work with api v2
2687        pass
2688        # uLogger.debug("Input parameters: {}".format(inputParameters))
2689        #
2690        # if operation is None or not operation or operation not in ("Buy", "Sell"):
2691        #     raise Exception("You must define operation type: 'Buy' or 'Sell'!")
2692        #
2693        # if "l" in inputParameters.keys():
2694        #     inputParameters["lots"] = inputParameters.pop("l")
2695        #
2696        # if "p" in inputParameters.keys():
2697        #     inputParameters["prices"] = inputParameters.pop("p")
2698        #
2699        # if "lots" not in inputParameters.keys() or "prices" not in inputParameters.keys():

2730def ParseArgs():
2731    """
2732    Function get and parse command line keys. See examples: https://tim55667757.github.io/TKSBrokerAPI/
2733    """
2734    parser = ArgumentParser()  # command-line string parser
2735
2736    parser.description = "TKSBrokerAPI is a python API to work with some methods of Tinkoff Open API using REST protocol. It can view history, orders and market information. Also, you can open orders and trades. See examples: https://tim55667757.github.io/TKSBrokerAPI/#Usage-examples"
2737    parser.usage = "python TKSBrokerAPI.py [some options] [one command]"
2738
2739    # --- options:
2740
2741    parser.add_argument("--token", type=str, help="Option: Tinkoff service's api key. If not set then used environment variable `TKS_API_TOKEN`. See how to use: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/token/")
2742    parser.add_argument("--account-id", type=str, help="Option: string with an user numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker. It can be found in any broker's reports (see the contract number). Also, this variable can be set from environment variable `TKS_ACCOUNT_ID`.")
2743    parser.add_argument("--ticker", "-t", type=str, help="Option: instrument's ticker, e.g. `IBM`, `YNDX`, `GOOGL` etc. Use alias for `USD000UTSTOM` simple as `USD`, `EUR_RUB__TOM` as `EUR`.")
2744    parser.add_argument("--figi", "-f", type=str, help="Option: instrument's FIGI, e.g. `BBG006L8G4H1` (for `YNDX`).")
2745    parser.add_argument("--depth", type=int, default=1, help="Option: Depth of Market (DOM) can be >=1, 1 by default.")
2746
2747    parser.add_argument("--output", type=str, default=None, help="Option: replace default paths to output files for some commands. If None then used default files.")
2748
2749    # parser.add_argument("--length", type=int, default=24, help="Option: how many last candles returns for history. Used only with --history key.")
2750    # parser.add_argument("--interval", type=str, default="60", help="Option: available values are 1min, 2min, 3min, 5min, 10min, 15min, 30min, hour, day, week, month. Used only with --history key. This is time period used in 'interval' api parameter. Default: --interval=60 that means 60 min for every history candles.")
2751    # parser.add_argument("--only-missing", action="store_true", default=False, help="Option: if history file define by --output key then add only last missing candles, do not request all history length. False by default.")
2752
2753    parser.add_argument("--debug-level", "--verbosity", "-v", type=int, default=20, help="Option: showing STDOUT messages of minimal debug level, e.g. 10 = DEBUG, 20 = INFO, 30 = WARNING, 40 = ERROR, 50 = CRITICAL. INFO (20) by default.")
2754
2755    # --- commands:
2756
2757    parser.add_argument("--list", "-l", action="store_true", help="Action: get and print all available instruments and some information from broker server. Also, you can define --output key to save list of instruments to file, default: instruments.md.")
2758    parser.add_argument("--info", "-i", action="store_true", help="Action: get information from broker server about instrument by it's ticker or FIGI. `--ticker` key or `--figi` key must be defined!")
2759    parser.add_argument("--price", action="store_true", help="Action: show actual price list for current instrument. Also, you can use --depth key. `--ticker` key or `--figi` key must be defined!")
2760    parser.add_argument("--prices", "-p", type=str, nargs="+", help="Action: get and print current prices for list of given instruments (by it's tickers or by FIGIs. WARNING! This is too long operation if you request a lot of instruments! Also, you can define --output key to save list of prices to file, default: prices.md.")
2761
2762    parser.add_argument("--overview", "-o", action="store_true", help="Action: show all open positions, orders and some statistics. Also, you can define --output key to save this information to file, default: overview.md.")
2763    parser.add_argument("--deals", "-d", type=str, nargs="*", help="Action: show all deals between two given dates. Start day may be an integer number: -1, -2, -3 days ago. Also, you can use keywords: `today`, `yesterday` (-1), `week` (-7), `month` (-30), `year` (-365). Dates format must be: `%%Y-%%m-%%d`, e.g. 2020-02-03. Also, you can define `--output` key to save all deals to file, default: report.md.")
2764    # parser.add_argument("--history", action="store_true", help="Action: get last (--length) history candles from past to current time with (--interval) values. Also, you can define --output key to save history candles to .csv-file.")
2765
2766    parser.add_argument("--trade", nargs="*", help="Action: universal action to open market position for defined ticker or FIGI. You must specify 1-5 parameters: [direction `Buy` or `Sell`] [lots, >= 1] [take profit, >= 0] [stop loss, >= 0] [expiration date for TP/SL orders, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`]. See examples in readme.")
2767    parser.add_argument("--buy", nargs="*", help="Action: immediately open BUY market position at the current price for defined ticker or FIGI. You must specify 0-4 parameters: [lots, >= 1] [take profit, >= 0] [stop loss, >= 0] [expiration date for TP/SL orders, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`].")
2768    parser.add_argument("--sell", nargs="*", help="Action: immediately open SELL market position at the current price for defined ticker or FIGI. You must specify 0-4 parameters: [lots, >= 1] [take profit, >= 0] [stop loss, >= 0] [expiration date for TP/SL orders, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`].")
2769
2770    parser.add_argument("--order", nargs="*", help="Action: universal action to open limit or stop-order in any directions. You must specify 4-7 parameters: [direction `Buy` or `Sell`] [order type `Limit` or `Stop`] [lots] [target price] [maybe for stop-order: [limit price, >= 0] [stop type, Limit|SL|TP] [expiration date, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`]]. See examples in readme.")
2771    parser.add_argument("--buy-limit", type=float, nargs=2, help="Action: open pending BUY limit-order (below current price). You must specify only 2 parameters: [lots] [target price] to open BUY limit-order. If you try to create `Buy` limit-order above current price then broker immediately open `Buy` market order, such as if you do simple `--buy` operation!")
2772    parser.add_argument("--sell-limit", type=float, nargs=2, help="Action: open pending SELL limit-order (above current price). You must specify only 2 parameters: [lots] [target price] to open SELL limit-order. If you try to create `Sell` limit-order below current price then broker immediately open `Sell` market order, such as if you do simple `--sell` operation!")
2773    parser.add_argument("--buy-stop", nargs="*", help="Action: open BUY stop-order. You must specify at least 2 parameters: [lots] [target price] to open BUY stop-order. In additional you can specify 3 parameters for stop-order: [limit price, >= 0] [stop type, Limit|SL|TP] [expiration date, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`]. When current price will go up or down to target price value then broker opens a limit order. Stop loss order always executed by market price.")
2774    parser.add_argument("--sell-stop", nargs="*", help="Action: open SELL stop-order. You must specify at least 2 parameters: [lots] [target price] to open SELL stop-order. In additional you can specify 3 parameters for stop-order: [limit price, >= 0] [stop type, Limit|SL|TP] [expiration date, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`]. When current price will go up or down to target price value then broker opens a limit order. Stop loss order always executed by market price.")
2775    # parser.add_argument("--buy-limit-order-grid", type=str, nargs="*", help="Action: open grid of pending BUY limit-orders (below current price). Parameters format: l(ots)=[L_int,...] p(rices)=[P_float,...]. Counts of values in lots and prices lists must be equals!")
2776    # parser.add_argument("--sell-limit-order-grid", type=str, nargs="*", help="Action: open grid of pending SELL limit-orders (above current price). Parameters format: l(ots)=[L_int,...] p(rices)=[P_float,...]. Counts of values in lots and prices lists must be equals!")
2777
2778    parser.add_argument("--close-order", "--cancel-order", type=str, nargs=1, help="Action: close only one order by it's `orderId` or `stopOrderId`. You can find out the meaning of these IDs using the key `--overview`")
2779    parser.add_argument("--close-orders", "--cancel-orders", type=str, nargs="+", help="Action: close one or list of orders by it's `orderId` or `stopOrderId`. You can find out the meaning of these IDs using the key `--overview`")
2780    parser.add_argument("--close-trade", "--cancel-trade", action="store_true", help="Action: close only one position for instrument defined by `--ticker` key, including for currencies tickers.")
2781    parser.add_argument("--close-trades", "--cancel-trades", type=str, nargs="+", help="Action: close positions for list of tickers, including for currencies tickers.")
2782    parser.add_argument("--close-all", "--cancel-all", type=str, nargs="*", help="Action: close all available (not blocked) opened trades and orders, excluding for currencies. Also you can select one or more keywords case insensitive to specify trades type: `orders`, `shares`, `bonds`, `etfs` and `futures`, but not `currencies`. Currency positions you must closes manually using `--buy`, `--sell`, `--close-trade` or `--close-trades` operations.")
2783
2784    cmdArgs = parser.parse_args()
2785    return cmdArgs

2788def Main(**kwargs):
2789    """
2790    Main function for work with Tinkoff Open API service. It realize simple logic: get a lot of options and execute one command.
2791
2792    See examples: https://tim55667757.github.io/TKSBrokerAPI/
2793    """
2794    args = Args(**kwargs) if kwargs else ParseArgs()  # get and parse command-line parameters or use **kwarg parameters
2795
2796    if args.debug_level:
2797        uLogger.level = 10  # always debug level by default
2798        uLogger.handlers[0].level = args.debug_level  # level for STDOUT
2799
2800    exitCode = 0
2801    start = datetime.now(tzutc())
2802    uLogger.debug("TKSBrokerAPI module started at: [{}] (UTC), it is [{}] local time".format(
2803        start.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"),
2804        start.astimezone(tzlocal()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"),
2805    ))
2806
2807    instruments = kwargs["instruments"] if kwargs else None  # try to decrease requests to server count if class init many times
2808    server = TinkoffBrokerServer(args.token, iList=instruments)  # Init class for trading with Tinkoff Broker
2809
2810    try:
2811        # --- set some options:
2812
2813        if args.account_id:
2814            server.accountId = args.account_id
2815
2816        if args.ticker:
2817            if args.ticker in server.aliasesKeys:
2818                server.ticker = server.aliases[args.ticker]  # Replace some tickers with it's aliases
2819
2820            else:
2821                server.ticker = args.ticker
2822
2823        if args.figi:
2824            server.figi = args.figi
2825
2826        if args.depth is not None:
2827            server.depth = args.depth
2828
2829        # if args.length is not None:
2830        #     server.historyLength = args.length
2831        #
2832        # if args.interval is not None:
2833        #     server.historyInterval = args.interval
2834
2835        # --- do one of commands:
2836
2837        if args.info:
2838            if not (args.ticker or args.figi):
2839                raise Exception("`--ticker` key or `--figi` key is required for this operation!")
2840
2841            if args.ticker:
2842                server.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=True, showInfo=True, debug=False)  # show info and current prices by ticker name
2843
2844            else:
2845                server.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True, showInfo=True, debug=False)  # show info and current prices by FIGI id
2846
2847        elif args.list:
2848            if args.output is not None:
2849                server.instrumentsFile = args.output
2850
2851            server.ShowInstrumentsInfo(showInstruments=True)
2852
2853        elif args.price:
2854            if not (args.ticker or args.figi):
2855                raise Exception("`--ticker` key or `--figi` key is required for this operation!")
2856
2857            server.GetCurrentPrices(showPrice=True)
2858
2859        elif args.prices is not None:
2860            if args.output is not None:
2861                server.pricesFile = args.output
2862
2863            server.GetListOfPrices(instruments=args.prices, showPrices=True)  # WARNING: too long wait for a lot of instruments prices
2864
2865        elif args.overview:
2866            if args.output is not None:
2867                server.overviewFile = args.output
2868
2869            server.Overview(showStatistics=True)
2870
2871        elif args.deals is not None:
2872            if args.output is not None:
2873                server.reportFile = args.output
2874
2875            if 0 <= len(args.deals) < 3:
2876                server.Deals(
2877                    start=args.deals[0] if len(args.deals) >= 1 else None,
2878                    end=args.deals[1] if len(args.deals) == 2 else None,
2879                    printDeals=True,
2880                )
2881
2882            else:
2883                raise Exception("You must specify 0-2 parameters: [DATE_START] [DATE_END]")
2884
2885        # TODO: implement history download and view
2886        # elif args.history:
2887        #     if args.output is not None:
2888        #         server.historyFile = args.output
2889        #
2890        #     server.History(onlyMissing=args.only_missing)
2891
2892        elif args.trade is not None:
2893            if 1 <= len(args.trade) <= 5:
2894                server.Trade(
2895                    operation=args.trade[0],
2896                    lots=int(args.trade[1]) if len(args.trade) >= 2 else 1,
2897                    tp=float(args.trade[2]) if len(args.trade) >= 3 else 0.,
2898                    sl=float(args.trade[3]) if len(args.trade) >= 4 else 0.,
2899                    expDate=args.trade[4] if len(args.trade) == 5 else "Undefined",
2900                )
2901
2902            else:
2903                uLogger.error("You must specify 1-5 parameters to open trade: [direction `Buy` or `Sell`] [lots, >= 1] [take profit, >= 0] [stop loss, >= 0] [expiration date for TP/SL orders, Undefined|`%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`]. See: `python TKSBrokerAPI.py --help`")
2904
2905        elif args.buy is not None:
2906            if 0 <= len(args.buy) <= 4:
2907                server.Buy(
2908                    lots=int(args.buy[0]) if len(args.buy) >= 1 else 1,
2909                    tp=float(args.buy[1]) if len(args.buy) >= 2 else 0.,
2910                    sl=float(args.buy[2]) if len(args.buy) >= 3 else 0.,
2911                    expDate=args.buy[3] if len(args.buy) == 4 else "Undefined",
2912                )
2913
2914            else:
2915                uLogger.error("You must specify 0-4 parameters to open buy position: [lots, >= 1] [take profit, >= 0] [stop loss, >= 0] [expiration date for TP/SL orders, Undefined|`%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`]. See: `python TKSBrokerAPI.py --help`")
2916
2917        elif args.sell is not None:
2918            if 0 <= len(args.sell) <= 4:
2919                server.Sell(
2920                    lots=int(args.sell[0]) if len(args.sell) >= 1 else 1,
2921                    tp=float(args.sell[1]) if len(args.sell) >= 2 else 0.,
2922                    sl=float(args.sell[2]) if len(args.sell) >= 3 else 0.,
2923                    expDate=args.sell[3] if len(args.sell) == 4 else "Undefined",
2924                )
2925
2926            else:
2927                uLogger.error("You must specify 0-4 parameters to open sell position: [lots, >= 1] [take profit, >= 0] [stop loss, >= 0] [expiration date for TP/SL orders, Undefined|`%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`]. See: `python TKSBrokerAPI.py --help`")
2928
2929        elif args.order:
2930            if 4 <= len(args.order) <= 7:
2931                server.Order(
2932                    operation=args.order[0],
2933                    orderType=args.order[1],
2934                    lots=int(args.order[2]),
2935                    targetPrice=float(args.order[3]),
2936                    limitPrice=float(args.order[4]) if len(args.order) >= 5 else 0.,
2937                    stopType=args.order[5] if len(args.order) >= 6 else "Limit",
2938                    expDate=args.order[6] if len(args.order) == 7 else "Undefined",
2939                )
2940
2941            else:
2942                uLogger.error("You must specify 4-7 parameters to open order: [direction `Buy` or `Sell`] [order type `Limit` or `Stop`] [lots] [target price] [maybe for stop-order: [limit price, >= 0] [stop type, Limit|SL|TP] [expiration date, Undefined|`%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`]]. See: `python TKSBrokerAPI.py --help`")
2943
2944        elif args.buy_limit:
2945            server.BuyLimit(lots=int(args.buy_limit[0]), targetPrice=args.buy_limit[1])
2946
2947        elif args.sell_limit:
2948            server.SellLimit(lots=int(args.sell_limit[0]), targetPrice=args.sell_limit[1])
2949
2950        elif args.buy_stop:
2951            if 2 <= len(args.buy_stop) <= 7:
2952                server.BuyStop(
2953                    lots=int(args.buy_stop[0]),
2954                    targetPrice=float(args.buy_stop[1]),
2955                    limitPrice=float(args.buy_stop[2]) if len(args.buy_stop) >= 3 else 0.,
2956                    stopType=args.buy_stop[3] if len(args.buy_stop) >= 4 else "Limit",
2957                    expDate=args.buy_stop[4] if len(args.buy_stop) == 5 else "Undefined",
2958                )
2959
2960            else:
2961                uLogger.error("You must specify 2-5 parameters for buy stop-order: [lots] [target price] [limit price, >= 0] [stop type, Limit|SL|TP] [expiration date, Undefined|`%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`]. See: `python TKSBrokerAPI.py --help`")
2962
2963        elif args.sell_stop:
2964            if 2 <= len(args.sell_stop) <= 7:
2965                server.SellStop(
2966                    lots=int(args.sell_stop[0]),
2967                    targetPrice=float(args.sell_stop[1]),
2968                    limitPrice=float(args.sell_stop[2]) if len(args.sell_stop) >= 3 else 0.,
2969                    stopType=args.sell_stop[3] if len(args.sell_stop) >= 4 else "Limit",
2970                    expDate=args.sell_stop[4] if len(args.sell_stop) == 5 else "Undefined",
2971                )
2972
2973            else:
2974                uLogger.error("You must specify 2-5 parameters for sell stop-order: [lots] [target price] [limit price, >= 0] [stop type, Limit|SL|TP] [expiration date, Undefined|`%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`]. See: python TKSBrokerAPI.py --help")
2975
2976        # elif args.buy_order_grid is not None:
2977        #     # TODO: update order grid work with api v2
2978        #     if len(args.buy_order_grid) == 2:
2979        #         orderParams = server.ParseOrderParameters(operation="Buy", **dict(kw.split('=') for kw in args.buy_order_grid))
2980        #
2981        #         for order in orderParams:
2982        #             server.Order(operation="Buy", lots=order["lot"], price=order["price"])
2983        #
2984        #     else:
2985        #         uLogger.error("To open grid of pending BUY limit-orders (below current price) you must specified 2 parameters: l(ots)=[L_int,...] p(rices)=[P_float,...]. See: `python TKSBrokerAPI.py --help`")
2986        #
2987        # elif args.sell_order_grid is not None:
2988        #     # TODO: update order grid work with api v2
2989        #     if len(args.sell_order_grid) >= 2:
2990        #         orderParams = server.ParseOrderParameters(operation="Sell", **dict(kw.split('=') for kw in args.sell_order_grid))
2991        #
2992        #         for order in orderParams:
2993        #             server.Order(operation="Sell", lots=order["lot"], price=order["price"])
2994        #
2995        #     else:
2996        #         uLogger.error("To open grid of pending SELL limit-orders (above current price) you must specified 2 parameters: l(ots)=[L_int,...] p(rices)=[P_float,...]. See: `python TKSBrokerAPI.py --help`")
2997
2998        elif args.close_order is not None:
2999            server.CloseOrders(args.close_order)  # close only one order
3000
3001        elif args.close_orders is not None:
3002            server.CloseOrders(args.close_orders)  # close list of orders
3003
3004        elif args.close_trade:
3005            if not args.ticker:
3006                raise Exception("`--ticker` key is required for this operation!")
3007
3008            server.CloseTrades([args.ticker])  # close only one trade
3009
3010        elif args.close_trades is not None:
3011            server.CloseTrades(args.close_trades)  # close trades for list of tickers
3012
3013        elif args.close_all is not None:
3014            server.CloseAll(*args.close_all)
3015
3016        else:
3017            uLogger.error("There is no command to execute! One of the possible commands must be selected. See: `python TKSBrokerAPI.py --help`")
3018            raise Exception("There is no command to execute!")
3019
3020    except Exception:
3021        exc = tb.format_exc().split("\n")
3022
3023        for line in exc:
3024            if line:
3025                uLogger.debug(line)
3026
3027        uLogger.debug("Unknown error occurred, open a ticket for this issue, please! https://github.com/Tim55667757/TKSBrokerAPI/issues")
3028        exitCode = 255  # unknown error occurred, must be open a ticket for this issue
3029
3030    finally:
3031        finish = datetime.now(tzutc())
3032
3033        if exitCode == 0:
3034            uLogger.debug("All operations with Tinkoff Server using Open API are finished success (summary code is 0).")
3035
3036        else:
3037            uLogger.error("TKSBrokerAPI module returns an error! See full debug log with key in run command `--debug-level 10`. Summary code: {}".format(exitCode))
3038
3039        uLogger.debug("TKSBrokerAPI module work duration: [{}]".format(finish - start))
3040        uLogger.debug("TKSBrokerAPI module finished: [{}] (UTC), it is [{}] local time".format(
3041            finish.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"),
3042            finish.astimezone(tzlocal()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"),
3043        ))
3044
3045        if not kwargs:
3046            sys.exit(exitCode)
3047
3048        else:
3049            return exitCode

3053    Main()
def NanoToFloat(units: str, nano: int) -> float: 
71def NanoToFloat(units: str, nano: int) -> float:
72    """
73    Convert number in nano-view mode with string parameter `units` and integer parameter `nano` to float view. Examples:
74
75    `NanoToFloat(units="2", nano=500000000) -> 2.5`
76
77    `NanoToFloat(units="0", nano=50000000) -> 0.05`
78
79    :param units: integer string or integer parameter that represents the integer part of number
80    :param nano: integer string or integer parameter that represents the fractional part of number
81    :return: float view of number
82    """
83    return int(units) + int(nano) * NANO

Convert number in nano-view mode with string parameter units and integer parameter nano to float view. Examples:

NanoToFloat(units="2", nano=500000000) -> 2.5

NanoToFloat(units="0", nano=50000000) -> 0.05

Parameters
  • units: integer string or integer parameter that represents the integer part of number
  • nano: integer string or integer parameter that represents the fractional part of number
Returns

float view of number

def FloatToNano(number: float) -> dict: 
 86def FloatToNano(number: float) -> dict:
 87    """
 88    Convert float number to nano-type view: dictionary with string `units` and integer `nano` parameters `{"units": "string", "nano": integer}`. Examples:
 89
 90    `FloatToNano(number=2.5) -> {"units": "2", "nano": 500000000}`
 91
 92    `FloatToNano(number=0.05) -> {"units": "0", "nano": 50000000}`
 93
 94    :param number: float number
 95    :return: nano-type view of number: `{"units": "string", "nano": integer}`
 96    """
 97    splitByPoint = str(number).split(".")
 98    frac = 0
 99
100    if len(splitByPoint) > 1:
101        if len(splitByPoint[1]) <= 9:
102            frac = int("{}{}".format(
103                int(splitByPoint[1]),
104                "0" * (9 - len(splitByPoint[1])),
105            ))
106
107    if (number < 0) and (frac > 0):
108        frac = -frac
109
110    return {"units": str(int(number)), "nano": frac}

Convert float number to nano-type view: dictionary with string units and integer nano parameters {"units": "string", "nano": integer}. Examples:

FloatToNano(number=2.5) -> {"units": "2", "nano": 500000000}

FloatToNano(number=0.05) -> {"units": "0", "nano": 50000000}

Parameters
  • number: float number
Returns

nano-type view of number: {"units": "string", "nano": integer}

def GetDatesAsString(start: str = None, end: str = None) -> tuple: 
113def GetDatesAsString(start: str = None, end: str = None) -> tuple:
114    """
115    If `start=None`, `end=None` then return dates from yesterday to current time.
116    If `start=some_date_1`, `end=None` then return dates from `some_date_1` to current time.
117    If `start=some_date_1`, `end=some_date_2` then return dates from `some_date_1` to `some_date_2`.
118    Start day may be negative integer numbers: `-1`, `-2`, `-3` - how many days ago.
119
120    Also, you can use keywords for start if `dateEnd=None`:
121    `today` (from 00:00:00 to current time),
122    `yesterday` (-1 day from 00:00:00 to 23:59:59),
123    `week` (-7 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time),
124    `month` (-30 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time),
125    `year` (-365 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time),
126
127    User dates format must be like: `%Y-%m-%d`, e.g. `2020-02-03` (3 Feb, 2020).
128
129    :return: tuple with 2 strings `(start, end)` dates in UTC ISO time format `%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ` for OpenAPI.
130             Example: `("2022-06-01T00:00:00Z", "2022-06-20T23:59:59Z")`
131    """
132    uLogger.debug("Input start day is [{}] (UTC), end day is [{}] (UTC)".format(start, end))
133    now = datetime.now(tzutc())
134
135    # showing statistics between start of the current day and current time:
136    if start is None or start.lower() == "today":
137        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0)
138        e = now
139
140    # from start of the last day to the end of the last day:
141    elif start.lower() == "yesterday":
142        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=1)
143        e = now.replace(hour=23, minute=59, second=59, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=1)
144
145    # week (-7 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time):
146    elif start.lower() == "week":
147        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=7)
148        e = now
149
150    # month (-30 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time):
151    elif start.lower() == "month":
152        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=30)
153        e = now
154
155    # year (-365 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time):
156    elif start.lower() == "year":
157        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=365)
158        e = now
159
160    # showing statistics from -N days ago to current date and time:
161    elif start.startswith('-') and start[1:].isdigit():
162        s = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0) - timedelta(days=abs(int(start)))
163        e = now
164
165    # showing statistics between start day at 00:00:00 and the end day at 23:59:59:
166    else:
167        s = datetime.strptime(start, "%Y-%m-%d").replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0, tzinfo=tzutc())
168        e = datetime.strptime(end, "%Y-%m-%d").replace(hour=23, minute=59, second=59, microsecond=0, tzinfo=tzutc()) if end is not None else now
169
170    # converting to UTC ISO time formatted with Z suffix for Tinkoff Open API:
171    s = s.strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ")
172    e = e.strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ")
173
174    uLogger.debug("Tinkoff Open API uses this start day (converted to UTC ISO format, with Z): [{}], and the end day: [{}]".format(s, e))
175
176    return s, e

If start=None, end=None then return dates from yesterday to current time. If start=some_date_1, end=None then return dates from some_date_1 to current time. If start=some_date_1, end=some_date_2 then return dates from some_date_1 to some_date_2. Start day may be negative integer numbers: -1, -2, -3 - how many days ago.

Also, you can use keywords for start if dateEnd=None: today (from 00:00:00 to current time), yesterday (-1 day from 00:00:00 to 23:59:59), week (-7 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time), month (-30 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time), year (-365 day from 00:00:00 to current date and time),

User dates format must be like: %Y-%m-%d, e.g. 2020-02-03 (3 Feb, 2020).

Returns

tuple with 2 strings (start, end) dates in UTC ISO time format %Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ for OpenAPI. Example: ("2022-06-01T00:00:00Z", "2022-06-20T23:59:59Z")

class TinkoffBrokerServer: 
 179class TinkoffBrokerServer:
 180    """
 181    This class implements methods to work with Tinkoff broker server.
 182
 183    Examples to work with API: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/
 184
 185    Where is `token`: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/token/
 186    """
 187    def __init__(self, token: str, iList: dict = None, accountId: str = None) -> None:
 188        """
 189        Main class init.
 190
 191        :param token: Bearer token for Tinkoff Invest API. It can be set from environment variable `TKS_API_TOKEN`.
 192        :param iList: dictionary of dictionaries with instrument's data.
 193        :param accountId: string with user's numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker. It can be found in broker's reports.
 194                          Also, this variable can be set from environment variable `TKS_ACCOUNT_ID`.
 195        """
 196        if token is None or not token:
 197            try:
 198                self.token = r"{}".format(os.environ["TKS_API_TOKEN"])
 199                uLogger.debug("Bearer token for Tinkoff OpenApi set up from environment variable `TKS_API_TOKEN`. See https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/token/")
 200
 201            except KeyError:
 202                raise Exception("`--token` key or environment variable `TKS_API_TOKEN` is required! See https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/token/")
 203
 204        else:
 205            self.token = token  # highly priority than environment variable 'TKS_API_TOKEN'
 206            uLogger.debug("Bearer token for Tinkoff OpenApi set up from class variable `token`")
 207
 208        if accountId is None or not accountId:
 209            try:
 210                self.accountId = r"{}".format(os.environ["TKS_ACCOUNT_ID"])
 211                uLogger.debug("String with user's numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker set up from environment variable `TKS_ACCOUNT_ID`")
 212
 213            except KeyError:
 214                uLogger.warning("`--account-id` key or environment variable `TKS_ACCOUNT_ID` undefined! Some of operations may be unavailable (overview, trading etc).")
 215
 216        else:
 217            self.accountId = accountId  # highly priority than environment variable 'TKS_ACCOUNT_ID'
 218            uLogger.debug("String with user's numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker set up from class variable `accountId`")
 219
 220        self.aliases = TKS_TICKER_ALIASES
 221        """Some aliases instead official tickers. See `TKSEnums.TKS_TICKER_ALIASES`"""
 222
 223        self.aliasesKeys = self.aliases.keys()  # re-calc only first time at class init
 224        self.exclude = TKS_TICKERS_OR_FIGI_EXCLUDED  # some of tickets or FIGIs raised exception earlier when it sends to server, that is why we exclude there
 225
 226        self.ticker = ""
 227        """String with ticker, e.g. `GOOGL`. Use alias for `USD000UTSTOM` simple as `USD`, `EUR_RUB__TOM` as `EUR` etc. More tickers aliases here: `TKSEnums.TKS_TICKER_ALIASES`."""
 228
 229        self.figi = ""
 230        """String with FIGI, e.g. ticker `GOOGL` has FIGI `BBG009S39JX6`"""
 231
 232        self.depth = 1
 233        """Depth of Market (DOM) can be >= 1. Default: 1. It used with `--price` key to showing DOM with current prices for givens ticker or FIGI."""
 234
 235        self.server = r"https://invest-public-api.tinkoff.ru/rest"
 236        """Tinkoff REST API server for real trade operations. Default: https://invest-public-api.tinkoff.ru/rest
 237
 238        See: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/#tinkoff-invest-api_1
 239        """
 240
 241        uLogger.debug("Broker API server: {}".format(self.server))
 242
 243        self.timeout = 15
 244        """Server operations timeout in seconds. Default: 15"""
 245
 246        self.headers = {"Content-Type": "application/json", "accept": "application/json", "Authorization": "Bearer {}".format(self.token)}
 247        """Headers which send in every request to broker server. Default: `{"Content-Type": "application/json", "accept": "application/json", "Authorization": "Bearer {token}"}`"""
 248
 249        self.body = None
 250        """Request body which send to broker server. Default: `None`"""
 251
 252        self.historyLength = 24
 253        """How many candles returns if candles history request. For example, if `historyInterval="hour"` and `historyLength=24` it means: "give me last 24 hours". Must be >=1. Default: 24"""
 254
 255        self.historyInterval = "hour"
 256        """Interval string for Tinkoff API (see: `TKSEnums.TKS_TIMEFRAMES`). Available values are `"1min"`, `"2min"`, `"3min"`, `"5min"`, `"10min"`, `"15min"`, `"30min"`, `"hour"`, `"day"`, `"week"`, `"month"`. Default: `"hour"`"""
 257
 258        self.iList = iList if iList is not None else self.Listing()
 259        """Dictionary with raw data about stocks, currencies, bonds, etfs and futures from broker server.
 260        At first time, when class init, `Listing()` method auto-update this variable.
 261        For future use, you can save this variable and substitute it in the `iList` to avoid permanent downloads from the server.
 262        """
 263
 264        self.pricesList = {}  # You can request all current prices with `ShowAllPrices()` method. WARNING! This is too long operation!
 265
 266        self.instrumentsFile = "instruments.md"
 267        """Filename where full broker's instruments list will be saved. Default: `"instruments.md"`"""
 268
 269        self.pricesFile = "prices.md"
 270        """Filename where prices of selected instruments will be saved. Default: `"prices.md"`"""
 271
 272        self.overviewFile = "overview.md"
 273        """Filename where current portfolio, open trades and orders will be saved. Default: `"overview.md"`"""
 274
 275        self.reportFile = "report.md"
 276        """Filename where history of deals and trade statistics will be saved. Default: `"report.md"`"""
 277
 278        self.historyFile = None

 281    @staticmethod
 282    def _ParseJSON(rawData="{}", debug: bool = False) -> dict:
 283        """
 284        Parse JSON from response string.
 285
 286        :param rawData: this is a string with JSON-formatted text.
 287        :param debug: if `True` then print more debug information.
 288        :return: JSON (dictionary), parsed from server response string.
 289        """
 290        if debug:
 291            uLogger.debug("Raw text body:")
 292            uLogger.debug(rawData)
 293
 294        responseJSON = json.loads(rawData, encoding="UTF-8") if rawData else {}
 295
 296        if debug:
 297            uLogger.debug("JSON formatted:")
 298            for jsonLine in json.dumps(responseJSON, indent=4).split('\n'):
 299                uLogger.debug(jsonLine)
 300
 301        return responseJSON
 302
 303    def SendAPIRequest(self, url: str, reqType: str = "GET", retry: int = 3, pause: int = 5, debug: bool = False) -> dict:
 304        """
 305        Send GET or POST request to broker server and receive JSON object.
 306
 307        self.header: must be define with dictionary of headers.
 308        self.body: if define then used as request body. None by default.
 309        self.timeout: global request timeout, 15 seconds by default.
 310        :param url: url with REST request.
 311        :param reqType: send "GET" or "POST" request. "GET" by default.
 312        :param retry: how many times retry after first request if an error occurred.
 313        :param pause: sleep time in seconds between retries.
 314        :param debug: if `True` then print more debug information.
 315        :return: response JSON (dictionary) from broker.
 316        """
 317        if reqType not in ("GET", "POST"):
 318            raise Exception("You can define request type: 'GET' or 'POST'!")
 319
 320        if debug:
 321            uLogger.debug("Request parameters:")
 322            uLogger.debug("    - REST API URL: {}".format(url))
 323            uLogger.debug("    - request type: {}".format(reqType))
 324            uLogger.debug("    - headers: {}".format(str(self.headers).replace(self.token, "*** request token ***")))
 325            uLogger.debug("    - body: {}".format(self.body))
 326
 327        # fast hack to avoid all operations with some tickers/FIGI
 328        responseJSON = {}
 329        oK = True
 330        for item in self.exclude:
 331            if item in url:
 332                if debug:
 333                    uLogger.warning("Do not execute operations with list of this tickers/FIGI: {}".format(str(self.exclude)))
 334
 335                oK = False
 336                break
 337
 338        if oK:
 339            counter = 0
 340            response = None
 341            errMsg = ""
 342
 343            while not response and counter <= retry:
 344                if reqType == "GET":
 345                    response = requests.get(url, headers=self.headers, data=self.body, timeout=self.timeout)
 346
 347                if reqType == "POST":
 348                    response = requests.post(url, headers=self.headers, data=self.body, timeout=self.timeout)
 349
 350                if debug:
 351                    uLogger.debug("Response:")
 352                    uLogger.debug("    - status code: {}".format(response.status_code))
 353                    uLogger.debug("    - reason: {}".format(response.reason))
 354                    uLogger.debug("    - body length: {}".format(len(response.text)))
 355
 356                # Error status codes: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_HTTP_status_codes
 357                if 400 <= response.status_code < 600:
 358                    errMsg = "[{}] {}".format(response.status_code, response.text)
 359                    uLogger.debug("    - not oK status code received: {}".format(errMsg))
 360                    counter += 1
 361
 362                    if counter <= retry:
 363                        uLogger.debug("Retry: [{}]. Wait until {} sec. and try again...".format(counter, pause))
 364                        sleep(pause)
 365
 366            responseJSON = self._ParseJSON(response.text)
 367
 368            if errMsg:
 369                uLogger.error("Not `oK` status received from broker server!")
 370                uLogger.error("    - message: {}".format(errMsg))
 371                # raise Exception("Server returned an error! See full debug log. Also you can set debug=True in SendAPIRequest() and _ParseJSON() methods.")
 372
 373        return responseJSON
 374
 375    def _IUpdater(self, iType: str) -> tuple:
 376        """
 377        Request instrument by type from server. See available API methods for instruments:
 378        Currencies: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService/InstrumentsService_Currencies
 379        Shares: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService/InstrumentsService_Shares
 380        Bonds: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService/InstrumentsService_Bonds
 381        Etfs: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService/InstrumentsService_Etfs
 382        Futures: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService/InstrumentsService_Futures
 383
 384        :param iType: type of the instrument, it must be one of supported types in TKS_INSTRUMENTS list.
 385        :return: tuple with iType name and list of available instruments of current type for defined user token.
 386        """
 387        result = []
 388
 389        if iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
 390            uLogger.debug("Requesting available [{}] list. Wait, please...".format(iType))
 391
 392            # all instruments have the same body in API v2 requests:
 393            self.body = str({"instrumentStatus": "INSTRUMENT_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED"})  # Enum: [INSTRUMENT_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED, INSTRUMENT_STATUS_BASE, INSTRUMENT_STATUS_ALL]
 394            instrumentURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.InstrumentsService/{}".format(iType)
 395            result = self.SendAPIRequest(instrumentURL, reqType="POST", debug=False)["instruments"]
 396
 397        return iType, result
 398
 399    def _IWrapper(self, kwargs):
 400        """
 401        Wrapper runs instrument's update method self._IUpdater().
 402        It's a workaround for using multiprocessing with kwargs. See: https://stackoverflow.com/a/36799206
 403        """
 404        return self._IUpdater(**kwargs)
 405
 406    def Listing(self) -> dict:
 407        """
 408        Gets JSON with raw data about stocks, currencies, bonds, etfs and futures from broker server.
 409
 410        :return: Dictionary with all available broker instruments: currencies, stocks, bonds, etfs and futures.
 411        """
 412        uLogger.debug("Requesting all available instruments from broker for current user token. Wait, please...")
 413        uLogger.debug("CPU usages for parallel requests: [{}]".format(CPU_USAGES))
 414
 415        # this parameters insert to requests: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService
 416        # iType is type of instrument, it must be one of supported types in TKS_INSTRUMENTS list.
 417        iParams = [{"iType": iType} for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS]
 418
 419        poolUpdater = ThreadPool(processes=CPU_USAGES)  # create pool for update instruments in parallel mode
 420        listing = poolUpdater.map(self._IWrapper, iParams)  # execute update operations
 421        poolUpdater.close()
 422
 423        # Dictionary with all broker instruments: stocks, currencies, bonds, etfs and futures.
 424        # Next in this code: item[0] is "iType" and item[1] is list of available instruments from the result of _IUpdater() method
 425        iList = {item[0]: {instrument["ticker"]: instrument for instrument in item[1]} for item in listing}
 426
 427        # calculate minimum price increment (step) for all instruments and set up instrument's type:
 428        for iType in iList.keys():
 429            for ticker in iList[iType]:
 430                iList[iType][ticker]["type"] = iType
 431
 432                if "minPriceIncrement" in iList[iType][ticker].keys():
 433                    iList[iType][ticker]["step"] = NanoToFloat(
 434                        iList[iType][ticker]["minPriceIncrement"]["units"],
 435                        iList[iType][ticker]["minPriceIncrement"]["nano"],
 436                    )
 437
 438                else:
 439                    iList[iType][ticker]["step"] = 0  # hack to avoid empty value in some instruments, e.g. futures
 440
 441        return iList

 539
 540            if "maturityDate" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["maturityDate"] != 0:
 541                info.append("| Maturity date:                                          | {}\n".format(iJSON["maturityDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "")))
 542
 543            if "perpetualFlag" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["perpetualFlag"]:
 544                info.append("| Perpetual bond:                                         | Yes\n")
 545
 546            if "otcFlag" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["otcFlag"]:
 547                info.append("| Over-the-counter (OTC) securities:                      | Yes\n")
 548
 549            if iJSON["type"] == "Bond":
 550                info.append("| Bond issue (size / plan):                               | {} / {}\n".format(iJSON["issueSize"], iJSON["issueSizePlan"]))
 551
 552                info.append("| Nominal price (100%):                                   | {} {}\n".format(
 553                    NanoToFloat(int(iJSON["nominal"]["units"]), iJSON["nominal"]["nano"]),
 554                    iJSON["nominal"]["currency"],
 555                ))
 556
 557                if "floatingCouponFlag" in iJSON.keys():
 558                    info.append("| Floating coupon:                                        | {}\n".format("Yes" if iJSON["floatingCouponFlag"] else "No"))
 559
 560                if "amortizationFlag" in iJSON.keys():
 561                    info.append("| Amortization:                                           | {}\n".format("Yes" if iJSON["amortizationFlag"] else "No"))
 562
 563                if "couponQuantityPerYear" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["couponQuantityPerYear"]:
 564                    info.append("| Number of coupon payments per year:                     | {}\n".format(iJSON["couponQuantityPerYear"]))
 565
 566                if "aciValue" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["aciValue"]:
 567                    info.append("| Current ACI (Accrued Interest):                         | {} {}\n".format(
 568                        NanoToFloat(int(iJSON["aciValue"]["units"]), iJSON["aciValue"]["nano"]),
 569                        iJSON["aciValue"]["currency"]
 570                    ))
 571
 572            if "currentPrice" in iJSON.keys():
 573                info.append("|                                                         |\n")
 574
 575                info.extend([
 576                    "| Previous close price of the instrument:                 | {}{}\n".format(
 577                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] is not None else "N/A",
 578                        "% of nominal price" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else " {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 579                    ),
 580                    "| Last deal price of the instrument:                      | {}{}\n".format(
