 581                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] is not None else "N/A",
 582                        "% of nominal price" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else " {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 583                    ),
 584                    "| Changes between last deal price and last close  %       | {:.2f}%\n".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"]),
 585                    "| Current limit price, min / max:                         | {}{} / {}{}\n".format(
 586                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["limitDown"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["limitDown"] is not None else "N/A",
 587                        "%" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else " {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 588                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["limitUp"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["limitUp"] is not None else "N/A",
 589                        "%" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else " {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 590                    ),
 591                    "| Actual price, sell / buy:                               | {}{} / {}{}\n".format(
 592                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["sell"][0]["price"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["sell"] else "N/A",
 593                        "%" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else " {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 594                        "{}".format(iJSON["currentPrice"]["buy"][0]["price"]).rstrip("0") if iJSON["currentPrice"]["buy"] else "N/A",
 595                        "%" if iJSON["type"] == "Bond" else" {}".format(iJSON["currency"] if "currency" in iJSON.keys() else ""),
 596                    ),
 597                ])
 598
 599            if "lot" in iJSON.keys():
 600                info.append("| Minimum lot to buy:                                     | {}\n".format(iJSON["lot"]))
 601
 602            if "step" in iJSON.keys() and iJSON["step"] != 0:
 603                info.append("| Minimum price increment (step):                         | {}\n".format(iJSON["step"]))
 604
 605            infoText += "".join(info)
 606
 607            if printInfo:
 608                uLogger.info("Information about instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}]\n{}".format(iJSON["ticker"], iJSON["figi"], infoText))
 609
 610            else:
 611                uLogger.debug("Information about instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}]\n{}".format(iJSON["ticker"], iJSON["figi"], infoText))
 612
 613        return infoText
 614
 615    def SearchByTicker(self, requestPrice: bool = False, showInfo: bool = False, debug: bool = False) -> dict:
 616        """
 617        Search and return raw broker's information about instrument by it's ticker.
 618        `ticker` must be define! If debug=True then print all debug messages.
 619
 620        :param requestPrice: if `False` then do not request current price of instrument (because this is long operation).
 621        :param showInfo: if `False` then do not run `ShowInstrumentInfo()` method and do not print info to the console.
 622        :param debug: if `True` then print all debug console messages.
 623        :return: JSON formatted data with information about instrument.
 624        """
 625        tickerJSON = {}
 626        if debug:
 627            uLogger.debug("Searching information about instrument by it's ticker [{}] ...".format(self.ticker))
 628
 629        if not self.ticker:
 630            uLogger.warning("self.ticker variable is not be empty!")
 631
 632        else:
 633            if not self.iList:
 634                self.iList = self.Listing()
 635
 636            if self.ticker in self.iList["Shares"].keys():
 637                tickerJSON = self.iList["Shares"][self.ticker]
 638                if debug:
 639                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in stocks list".format(self.ticker))
 640
 641            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Currencies"].keys():
 642                tickerJSON = self.iList["Currencies"][self.ticker]
 643                if debug:
 644                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in currencies list".format(self.ticker))
 645
 646            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Bonds"].keys():
 647                tickerJSON = self.iList["Bonds"][self.ticker]
 648                if debug:
 649                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in bonds list".format(self.ticker))
 650
 651            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Etfs"].keys():
 652                tickerJSON = self.iList["Etfs"][self.ticker]
 653                if debug:
 654                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in etfs list".format(self.ticker))
 655
 656            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Futures"].keys():
 657                tickerJSON = self.iList["Futures"][self.ticker]
 658                if debug:
 659                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in futures list".format(self.ticker))
 660
 661        if tickerJSON:
 662            self.figi = tickerJSON["figi"]
 663
 664            if requestPrice:
 665                tickerJSON["currentPrice"] = self.GetCurrentPrices(showPrice=False)
 666
 667                if tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] is not None and tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] != 0 and tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] is not None:
 668                    tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 100 * (tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] - tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]) / tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]
 669
 670                else:
 671                    tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 0
 672
 673            if showInfo:
 674                self.ShowInstrumentInfo(iJSON=tickerJSON, printInfo=True)  # print info as Markdown text
 675
 676        else:
 677            if showInfo:
 678                uLogger.warning("Ticker [{}] not found in available broker instrument's list!".format(self.ticker))
 679
 680        return tickerJSON
 681
 682    def SearchByFIGI(self, requestPrice: bool = False, showInfo: bool = False, debug: bool = False) -> dict:
 683        """
 684        Search and return raw broker's information about instrument by it's FIGI.
 685        `figi` must be define! If debug=True then print all debug messages.
 686
 687        :param requestPrice: if `False` then do not request current price of instrument (it's long operation).
 688        :param showInfo: if `False` then do not run `ShowInstrumentInfo()` method and do not print info to the console.
 689        :param debug: if `True` then print all debug console messages.
 690        :return: JSON formatted data with information about instrument.
 691        """
 692        figiJSON = {}
 693        if debug:
 694            uLogger.debug("Searching information about instrument by it's FIGI [{}] ...".format(self.figi))
 695
 696        if not self.figi:
 697            uLogger.warning("self.figi variable is not be empty!")
 698
 699        else:
 700            if not self.iList:
 701                self.iList = self.Listing()
 702
 703            for item in self.iList["Shares"].keys():
 704                if self.figi == self.iList["Shares"][item]["figi"]:
 705                    figiJSON = self.iList["Shares"][item]
 706
 707                    if debug:
 708                        uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in stocks list".format(self.figi))
 709
 710                    break
 711
 712            if not figiJSON:
 713                for item in self.iList["Currencies"].keys():
 714                    if self.figi == self.iList["Currencies"][item]["figi"]:
 715                        figiJSON = self.iList["Currencies"][item]
 716
 717                        if debug:
 718                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in currencies list".format(self.figi))
 719
 720                        break
 721
 722            if not figiJSON:
 723                for item in self.iList["Bonds"].keys():
 724                    if self.figi == self.iList["Bonds"][item]["figi"]:
 725                        figiJSON = self.iList["Bonds"][item]
 726
 727                        if debug:
 728                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in bonds list".format(self.figi))
 729
 730                        break
 731
 732            if not figiJSON:
 733                for item in self.iList["Etfs"].keys():
 734                    if self.figi == self.iList["Etfs"][item]["figi"]:
 735                        figiJSON = self.iList["Etfs"][item]
 736
 737                        if debug:
 738                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in etfs list".format(self.figi))
 739
 740                        break
 741
 742            if not figiJSON:
 743                for item in self.iList["Futures"].keys():
 744                    if self.figi == self.iList["Futures"][item]["figi"]:
 745                        figiJSON = self.iList["Futures"][item]
 746
 747                        if debug:
 748                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in futures list".format(self.figi))
 749
 750                        break
 751
 752        if figiJSON:
 753            self.figi = figiJSON["figi"]
 754            self.ticker = figiJSON["ticker"]
 755
 756            if requestPrice:
 757                figiJSON["currentPrice"] = self.GetCurrentPrices(showPrice=False)
 758
 759                if figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] is not None and figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] != 0 and figiJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] is not None:
 760                    figiJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 100 * (figiJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] - figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]) / figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]
 761
 762                else:
 763                    figiJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 0
 764
 765            if showInfo:
 766                self.ShowInstrumentInfo(iJSON=figiJSON, printInfo=True)  # print info as Markdown text
 767
 768        else:
 769            if showInfo:
 770                uLogger.warning("FIGI [{}] not found in available broker instrument's list!".format(self.figi))
 771
 772        return figiJSON
 773
 774    def GetCurrentPrices(self, showPrice: bool = False) -> dict:
 775        """
 776        Get and show Depth of Market with current prices of the instrument. If an error occurred then returns an empty record:
 777        `{"buy": [], "sell": [], "limitUp": None, "limitDown": None, "lastPrice": None, "closePrice": None}`.
 778
 779        :param showPrice: if `True` then print DOM.
 780        :return: dict with Depth of Market (DOM): `{"buy": [{"price": x1, "quantity": y1, ...}], "sell": [....]}` with list of current prices.
 781        """
 782        prices = {"buy": [], "sell": [], "limitUp": 0, "limitDown": 0, "lastPrice": 0, "closePrice": 0}
 783
 784        if self.depth < 1:
 785            raise Exception("Depth of Market (DOM) must be >=1!")
 786
 787        if not (self.ticker or self.figi):
 788            raise Exception("self.ticker or self.figi variables must be defined!")
 789
 790        if self.ticker and not self.figi:
 791            instrumentByTicker = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=False)  # WARNING! requestPrice=False to avoid recursion!
 792            self.figi = instrumentByTicker["figi"] if instrumentByTicker else ""
 793
 794        if not self.ticker and self.figi:
 795            instrumentByFigi = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=False)  # WARNING! requestPrice=False to avoid recursion!
 796            self.ticker = instrumentByFigi["ticker"] if instrumentByFigi else ""
 797
 798        if self.figi:
 799            uLogger.debug("Requesting current prices for instrument with ticker [{}] and FIGI [{}]...".format(self.ticker, self.figi))
 800
 801            # REST API for request: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/MarketDataService/MarketDataService_GetOrderBook
 802            priceURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.MarketDataService/GetOrderBook"
 803            self.body = str({"figi": self.figi, "depth": self.depth})
 804            pricesResponse = self.SendAPIRequest(priceURL, reqType="POST")
 805
 806            if pricesResponse:
 807                # list of dicts with sellers orders:
 808                prices["buy"] = [{"price": NanoToFloat(item["price"]["units"], item["price"]["nano"]), "quantity": int(item["quantity"])} for item in pricesResponse["asks"]]
 809
 810                # list of dicts with buyers orders:
 811                prices["sell"] = [{"price": NanoToFloat(item["price"]["units"], item["price"]["nano"]), "quantity": int(item["quantity"])} for item in pricesResponse["bids"]]
 812
 813                # max price of instrument at this time:
 814                prices["limitUp"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["limitUp"]["units"], pricesResponse["limitUp"]["nano"]) if "limitUp" in pricesResponse.keys() else None
 815
 816                # min price of instrument at this time:
 817                prices["limitDown"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["limitDown"]["units"], pricesResponse["limitDown"]["nano"]) if "limitDown" in pricesResponse.keys() else None
 818
 819                # last price of deal with instrument:
 820                prices["lastPrice"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["lastPrice"]["units"], pricesResponse["lastPrice"]["nano"]) if "lastPrice" in pricesResponse.keys() else 0
 821
 822                # last close price of instrument:
 823                prices["closePrice"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["closePrice"]["units"], pricesResponse["closePrice"]["nano"]) if "closePrice" in pricesResponse.keys() else 0
 824
 825            else:
 826                uLogger.warning("Server return an empty or error response! See full log. Instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}]".format(self.ticker, self.figi))
 827                uLogger.debug("Server response: {}".format(pricesResponse))
 828
 829            if showPrice:
 830                if prices["buy"] or prices["sell"]:
 831                    info = [
 832                        "Orders book actual at [{}] (UTC)\nTicker: [{}], FIGI: [{}], Depth of Market: [{}]\n".format(
 833                            datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"),
 834                            self.ticker,
 835                            self.figi,
 836                            self.depth,
 837                        ),
 838                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
 839                        " Orders of Buyers   | Orders of Sellers\n",
 840                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
 841                        " Sell prices (vol.) | Buy prices (vol.)\n",
 842                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
 843                    ]
 844
 845                    if not prices["buy"]:
 846                        info.append("                    | No orders!\n")
 847                        sumBuy = 0
 848
 849                    else:
 850                        sumBuy = sum([x["quantity"] for x in prices["buy"]])
 851                        maxMinSorted = sorted(prices["buy"], key=lambda k: k["price"], reverse=True)
 852                        for item in maxMinSorted:
 853                            info.append("                    | {} ({})\n".format(item["price"], item["quantity"]))
 854
 855                    if not prices["sell"]:
 856                        info.append("No orders!          |\n")
 857                        sumSell = 0
 858
 859                    else:
 860                        sumSell = sum([x["quantity"] for x in prices["sell"]])
 861                        for item in prices["sell"]:
 862                            info.append("{:>19} |\n".format("{} ({})".format(item["price"], item["quantity"])))
 863
 864                    info.extend([
 865                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
 866                        "{:>19} | {}\n".format("Total sell: {}".format(sumSell), "Total buy: {}".format(sumBuy)),
 867                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
 868                    ])
 869
 870                    infoText = "".join(info)
 871
 872                    uLogger.info("Current prices in order book:\n\n{}".format(infoText))
 873
 874                else:
 875                    uLogger.warning("Orders book is empty at this time! Instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}]".format(self.ticker, self.figi))
 876
 877        else:
 878            uLogger.error("FIGI is not defined!")
 879
 880        return prices
 881
 882    def ShowInstrumentsInfo(self, showInstruments: bool = False) -> str:
 883        """
 884        This method get and show information about all available broker instruments.
 885        If `instrumentsFile` string is not empty then also save information to this file.
 886
 887        :param showInstruments: if `True` then print to console, if `False` - print only to file.
 888        :return: multi-string with all available broker instruments
 889        """
 890        if not self.iList:
 891            self.iList = self.Listing()
 892
 893        info = [
 894            "# All available instruments from Tinkoff Broker server for current user token\n\n",
 895            "* **Actual on date:** [{}] (UTC)\n".format(datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")),
 896        ]
 897
 898        # add instruments count by type:
 899        for iType in self.iList.keys():
 900            info.append("* **{}:** [{}]\n".format(iType, len(self.iList[iType])))
 901
 902        headerLine = "| Ticker       | Full name                                                      | FIGI         | Cur | Lot    | Step\n"
 903        splitLine = "|--------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|--------------|-----|--------|---------\n"
 904
 905        # generate info tables with all instruments by type:
 906        for iType in self.iList.keys():
 907            info.extend(["\n\n## {} available. Total: [{}]\n\n".format(iType, len(self.iList[iType])), headerLine, splitLine])
 908
 909            for instrument in self.iList[iType].keys():
 910                iName = self.iList[iType][instrument]["name"]  # instrument's name
 911                if len(iName) > 63:
 912                    iName = "{}...".format(iName[:60])  # right trim for a long string
 913    
 914                info.append("| {:<12} | {:<63}| {:<13}| {:<4}| {:<7}| {}\n".format(
 915                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["ticker"],
 916                    iName,
 917                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["figi"],
 918                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["currency"],
 919                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["lot"],
 920                    str(self.iList[iType][instrument]["step"]).rstrip("0"),
 921                ))
 922
 923        infoText = "".join(info)
 924
 925        if showInstruments:
 926            uLogger.info(infoText)
 927
 928        if self.instrumentsFile:
 929            with open(self.instrumentsFile, "w", encoding="UTF-8") as fH:
 930                fH.write(infoText)
 931
 932            uLogger.info("All available instruments are saved to file: [{}]".format(os.path.abspath(self.instrumentsFile)))
 933
 934        return infoText
 935
 936    def GetListOfPrices(self, instruments: list = None, showPrices: bool = False) -> list:
 937        """
 938        This method get, maybe show and return prices of list of instruments. WARNING! This is potential long operation!
 939        See limits: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/limits/
 940        If `pricesFile` string is not empty then also save information to this file.
 941
 942        :param instruments: list of tickers or FIGIs.
 943        :param showPrices: if `True` then print to console, if `False` - print only to file.
 944        :return: list of instruments looks like this: `iList = [{some ticker info, "currentPrice": {current prices}}, {...}, ...]`
 945                 One item is dict returned by `SearchByTicker()` or `SearchByFIGI()` methods.
 946        """
 947        if instruments is None or not instruments:
 948            raise Exception("You must define some of tickers or FIGIs to request it's actual prices!")
 949
 950        uLogger.debug("Requesting current prices of list of instruments from Tinkoff Broker server...")
 951
 952        iList = []
 953        for iName in instruments:
 954            if iName not in self.aliases.keys():
 955                iList.append(iName)
 956
 957            else:
 958                iList.append(self.aliases[iName])
 959
 960        unique = set()  # create list with every figi only one time with the same order position:
 961        tempNames = [item for item in iList if not (item in unique or unique.add(item))]
 962
 963        uLogger.debug("Ordered input list of instruments without duplicates of names: {}".format(tempNames))
 964
 965        iList = []  # try to get info about all unique instruments:
 966        for iName in tempNames:
 967            self.ticker = iName
 968            iData = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=True)
 969
 970            if not iData:
 971                self.ticker = ""
 972                self.figi = iName
 973
 974                iData = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True)
 975
 976                if not iData:
 977                    self.figi = ""
 978                    uLogger.warning("Instrument [{}] not in list of available instruments for current token!".format(iName))
 979
 980            if iData:
 981                isUnique = True
 982                for item in iList:
 983                    if item["figi"] == iData["figi"] or item["ticker"] == iData["ticker"]:
 984                        isUnique = False
 985                        break
 986
 987                if isUnique:
 988                    iList.append(iData)
 989
 990        if showPrices:
 991            info = [
 992                "# Actual prices at: [{} UTC]\n\n".format(datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")),
 993                "| Ticker       | FIGI         | Type       | Prev. close | Last price  | Chg. %   | Day limits min/max  | Actual sell / buy   | Curr.\n",
 994                "|--------------|--------------|------------|-------------|-------------|----------|---------------------|---------------------|------\n",
 995            ]
 996
 997            for item in iList:
 998                info.append("| {:<12} | {:<12} | {:<10} | {:>11} | {:>11} | {:>7}% | {:>19} | {:>19} | {}\n".format(
 999                    item["ticker"],
1000                    item["figi"],
1001                    item["type"],
1002                    "{:.2f}".format(float(item["currentPrice"]["closePrice"])),
1003                    "{:.2f}".format(float(item["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"])),
1004                    "{}{:.2f}".format("+" if item["currentPrice"]["changes"] > 0 else "", float(item["currentPrice"]["changes"])),
1005                    "{} / {}".format(
1006                        item["currentPrice"]["limitDown"] if item["currentPrice"]["limitDown"] is not None else "N/A",
1007                        item["currentPrice"]["limitUp"] if item["currentPrice"]["limitUp"] is not None else "N/A",
1008                    ),
1009                    "{} / {}".format(
1010                        item["currentPrice"]["sell"][0]["price"] if item["currentPrice"]["sell"] else "N/A",
1011                        item["currentPrice"]["buy"][0]["price"] if item["currentPrice"]["buy"] else "N/A",
1012                    ),
1013                    item["currency"],
1014                ))
1015
1016            infoText = "".join(info)
1017
1018            if showPrices:
1019                uLogger.info("Only unique instruments are shown:\n{}".format(infoText))
1020
1021            if self.pricesFile:
1022                with open(self.pricesFile, "w", encoding="UTF-8") as fH:
1023                    fH.write(infoText)
1024
1025                uLogger.info("Price list for all instruments saved to file: [{}]".format(os.path.abspath(self.pricesFile)))
1026
1027        return iList
1028
1029    def RequestPortfolio(self) -> dict:
1030        """
1031        Requesting current actual user's portfolio.
1032        REST API for user portfolio: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/OperationsService/OperationsService_GetPortfolio
1033
1034        :return: dictionary with user's portfolio.
1035        """
1036        uLogger.debug("Requesting current actual user's portfolio. Wait, please...")
1037
1038        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId})
1039        portfolioURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OperationsService/GetPortfolio"
1040        rawPortfolio = self.SendAPIRequest(portfolioURL, reqType="POST")
1041
1042        uLogger.debug("Records about user's portfolio successfully received")
1043
1044        return rawPortfolio
1045
1046    def RequestPositions(self) -> dict:
1047        """
1048        Requesting current open positions in currencies and instruments.
1049        REST API for open positions: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/OperationsService/OperationsService_GetPositions
1050
1051        :return: dictionary with open positions by instruments.
1052        """
1053        uLogger.debug("Requesting current open positions in currencies and instruments. Wait, please...")
1054
1055        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId})
1056        positionsURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OperationsService/GetPositions"
1057        rawPositions = self.SendAPIRequest(positionsURL, reqType="POST")
1058
1059        uLogger.debug("Records about current open positions successfully received")
1060
1061        return rawPositions
1062
1063    def RequestPendingOrders(self) -> list:
1064        """
1065        Requesting current actual pending orders.
1066        REST API for pending (market) orders: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/OrdersService/OrdersService_GetOrders
1067
1068        :return: list of dictionaries with pending orders.
1069        """
1070        uLogger.debug("Requesting current actual pending orders. Wait, please...")
1071
1072        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId})
1073        ordersURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OrdersService/GetOrders"
1074        rawOrders = self.SendAPIRequest(ordersURL, reqType="POST")["orders"]
1075
1076        uLogger.debug("[{}] records about pending orders successfully received".format(len(rawOrders)))
1077
1078        return rawOrders
1079
1080    def RequestStopOrders(self) -> list:
1081        """
1082        Requesting current actual stop orders.
1083        REST API for opened stop-orders: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/StopOrdersService/StopOrdersService_GetStopOrders
1084
1085        :return: list of dictionaries with stop orders.
1086        """
1087        uLogger.debug("Requesting current actual stop orders. Wait, please...")
1088
1089        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId})
1090        ordersURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.StopOrdersService/GetStopOrders"
1091        rawStopOrders = self.SendAPIRequest(ordersURL, reqType="POST")["stopOrders"]
1092
1093        uLogger.debug("[{}] records about stop orders successfully received".format(len(rawStopOrders)))
1094
1095        return rawStopOrders
1096
1097    def Overview(self, showStatistics: bool = False) -> dict:
1098        """
1099        Get portfolio: all open positions, orders and some statistics for defined accountId.
1100        If `overviewFile` is define then also save information to file.
1101
1102        :param showStatistics: if `False` then only dictionary returns, if `True` then show more debug information.
1103        :return: dictionary with client's raw portfolio and some statistics.
1104        """
1105        view = {
1106            "raw": {  # --- raw portfolio responses from broker with user portfolio data:
1107                "headers": {},  # list of dictionaries, response headers without "positions" section
1108                "Currencies": [],  # list of dictionaries, open trades with currencies from "positions" section
1109                "Shares": [],  # list of dictionaries, open trades with stocks from "positions" section
1110                "Bonds": [],  # list of dictionaries, open trades with bonds from "positions" section
1111                "Etfs": [],  # list of dictionaries, open trades with etfs from "positions" section
1112                "Futures": [],  # list of dictionaries, open trades with futures from "positions" section
1113                "positions": {},  # raw response from broker: dictionary with current available or blocked currencies and instruments for client
1114                "orders": [],  # raw response from broker: list of dictionaries with all pending (market) orders
1115                "stopOrders": [],  # raw response from broker: list of dictionaries with all stop orders
1116                "currenciesCurrentPrices": {"rub": {"name": "Российский рубль", "currentPrice": 1.}},  # dict with prices of all currencies in RUB
1117            },
1118            "stat": {  # --- some statistics calculated using "raw" sections:
1119                "portfolioCostRUB": 0.,  # portfolio cost in RUB (Russian Rouble)
1120                "currentBlockedRUB": 0.,  # blocked sum in Russian Rouble
1121                "totalChangesRUB": 0.,  # changes for all open trades in RUB
1122                "totalChangesPercentRUB": 0.,  # changes for all open trades in percents
1123                "allCurrenciesCostRUB": 0.,  # costs of all currencies (include rubles) in RUB
1124                "availableRUB": 0.,  # available rubles (without other currencies)
1125                "stocksCostRUB": 0.,  # costs of all stocks in RUB
1126                "bondsCostRUB": 0.,  # costs of all bonds in RUB
1127                "etfsCostRUB": 0.,  # costs of all etfs in RUB
1128                "Currencies": [],  # list of dictionaries of all currencies statistics
1129                "Shares": [],  # list of dictionaries of all stocks statistics
1130                "Bonds": [],  # list of dictionaries of all bonds statistics
1131                "Etfs": [], # list of dictionaries of all etfs statistics
1132                "Futures": [], # list of dictionaries of all futures statistics
1133                "orders": [],  # list of dictionaries of all pending (market) orders and it's parameters
1134                "stopOrders": [],  # list of dictionaries of all stop orders and it's parameters
1135                "blockedCurrencies": {},  # dict with blocked instruments and currencies, e.g. {"rub": 1291.87, "usd": 6.21}
1136                "blockedInstruments": {},  # dict with blocked  by FIGI, e.g. {}
1137            },
1138            "analytics":{  # --- some analytics of portfolio:
1139                "distrByAssets": {},  # portfolio distribution by assets
1140                "distrByCompanies": {},  # portfolio distribution by companies
1141                "distrBySectors": {},  # portfolio distribution by sectors
1142                "distrByCurrencies": {},  # portfolio distribution by currencies
1143            }
1144        }
1145
1146        if showStatistics:
1147            uLogger.debug("Request portfolio of a client...")
1148
1149        portfolioResponse = self.RequestPortfolio()  # current user's portfolio (dict)
1150        view["raw"]["positions"] = self.RequestPositions()  # current open positions by instruments (dict)
1151        view["raw"]["orders"] = self.RequestPendingOrders()  # current actual pending orders (list)
1152        view["raw"]["stopOrders"] = self.RequestStopOrders()  # current actual stop orders (list)
1153
1154        # save response headers without "positions" section:
1155        for key in portfolioResponse.keys():
1156            if key != "positions":
1157                view["raw"]["headers"][key] = portfolioResponse[key]
1158
1159            else:
1160                continue
1161
1162        # Re-sorting and separating given raw instruments and currencies by type: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/operations/#operation
1163        # Type of instrument must be only one of supported types in TKS_INSTRUMENTS
1164        for item in portfolioResponse["positions"]:
1165            if item["instrumentType"] == "currency":
1166                self.figi = item["figi"]
1167                curr = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=False)
1168
1169                # current price of currency in RUB:
1170                view["raw"]["currenciesCurrentPrices"][curr["nominal"]["currency"]] = {
1171                    "name": curr["name"],
1172                    "currentPrice": NanoToFloat(
1173                        item["currentPrice"]["units"],
1174                        item["currentPrice"]["nano"]
1175                    ),
1176                }
1177
1178                view["raw"]["Currencies"].append(item)
1179
1180            elif item["instrumentType"] == "share":
1181                view["raw"]["Shares"].append(item)
1182
1183            elif item["instrumentType"] == "bond":
1184                view["raw"]["Bonds"].append(item)
1185
1186            elif item["instrumentType"] == "etf":
1187                view["raw"]["Etfs"].append(item)
1188
1189            elif item["instrumentType"] == "futures":
1190                view["raw"]["Futures"].append(item)
1191
1192            else:
1193                continue
1194
1195        # how many volume of currencies (by ISO currency name) are blocked:
1196        for item in view["raw"]["positions"]["blocked"]:
1197            blocked = NanoToFloat(item["units"], item["nano"])
1198            if blocked > 0:
1199                view["stat"]["blockedCurrencies"][item["currency"]] = blocked
1200
1201        # how many volume of instruments (by FIGI) are blocked:
1202        for item in view["raw"]["positions"]["securities"]:
1203            blocked = int(item["blocked"])
1204            if blocked > 0:
1205                view["stat"]["blockedInstruments"][item["figi"]] = blocked
1206
1207        allBlocked = {**view["stat"]["blockedCurrencies"], **view["stat"]["blockedInstruments"]}
1208
1209        if "rub" in allBlocked.keys():
1210            view["stat"]["currentBlockedRUB"] = allBlocked["rub"]  # blocked rubles
1211
1212        # --- saving current total amount in RUB of all currencies (with ruble), stocks, bonds, etfs, futures and currencies:
1213        view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"] = NanoToFloat(portfolioResponse["totalAmountCurrencies"]["units"], portfolioResponse["totalAmountCurrencies"]["nano"])
1214        view["stat"]["stocksCostRUB"] = NanoToFloat(portfolioResponse["totalAmountShares"]["units"], portfolioResponse["totalAmountShares"]["nano"])
1215        view["stat"]["bondsCostRUB"] = NanoToFloat(portfolioResponse["totalAmountBonds"]["units"], portfolioResponse["totalAmountBonds"]["nano"])
1216        view["stat"]["etfsCostRUB"] = NanoToFloat(portfolioResponse["totalAmountEtf"]["units"], portfolioResponse["totalAmountEtf"]["nano"])
1217        view["stat"]["futuresCostRUB"] = NanoToFloat(portfolioResponse["totalAmountFutures"]["units"], portfolioResponse["totalAmountFutures"]["nano"])
1218        view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] = sum([
1219            view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"],
1220            view["stat"]["stocksCostRUB"],
1221            view["stat"]["bondsCostRUB"],
1222            view["stat"]["etfsCostRUB"],
1223            view["stat"]["futuresCostRUB"],
1224        ])
1225
1226        # --- calculating some portfolio statistics:
1227        byComp = {}  # distribution by companies
1228        bySect = {}  # distribution by sectors
1229        byCurr = {}  # distribution by currencies (include RUB)
1230
1231        for item in portfolioResponse["positions"]:
1232            self.figi = item["figi"]
1233            instrument = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=False)  # full raw info about instrument by FIGI
1234
1235            if instrument:
1236                if item["instrumentType"] == "currency" and instrument["nominal"]["currency"] in allBlocked.keys():
1237                    blocked = allBlocked[instrument["nominal"]["currency"]]  # blocked volume of currency
1238
1239                elif item["instrumentType"] != "currency" and item["figi"] in allBlocked.keys():
1240                    blocked = allBlocked[item["figi"]]  # blocked volume of other instruments
1241
1242                else:
1243                    blocked = 0
1244
1245                volume = NanoToFloat(item["quantity"]["units"], item["quantity"]["nano"])  # available volume of instrument
1246                lots = NanoToFloat(item["quantityLots"]["units"], item["quantityLots"]["nano"])  # available volume in lots of instrument
1247                direction = "Long" if lots >= 0 else "Short"  # direction of an instrument's position: short or long
1248                curPrice = NanoToFloat(item["currentPrice"]["units"], item["currentPrice"]["nano"])  # current instrument's price
1249                average = NanoToFloat(item["averagePositionPriceFifo"]["units"], item["averagePositionPriceFifo"]["nano"])  # current average position price
1250                profit = NanoToFloat(item["expectedYield"]["units"], item["expectedYield"]["nano"])  # expected profit at current moment
1251                currency = instrument["currency"] if (item["instrumentType"] == "share" or item["instrumentType"] == "etf" or item["instrumentType"] == "future") else instrument["nominal"]["currency"]  # currency name rub, usd, eur etc.
1252                cost = (curPrice + NanoToFloat(item["currentNkd"]["units"], item["currentNkd"]["nano"])) * volume  # current cost of all volume of instrument in basic asset
1253                baseCurrencyName = item["currentPrice"]["currency"]  # name of base currency (rub)
1254                costRUB = cost if item["instrumentType"] == "currency" else cost * view["raw"]["currenciesCurrentPrices"][currency]["currentPrice"]  # cost in rubles
1255                percentCostRUB = 100 * costRUB / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.  # instrument's part in percent of full portfolio cost
1256
1257                statData = {
1258                    "figi": item["figi"],  # FIGI from REST API "GetPortfolio" method
1259                    "ticker": instrument["ticker"],  # ticker by FIGI
1260                    "currency": currency,  # currency name rub, usd, eur etc. for instrument price
1261                    "volume": volume,  # available volume of instrument
1262                    "lots": lots,  # volume in lots of instrument
1263                    "direction": direction,  # direction of an instrument's position: short or long
1264                    "blocked": blocked,  # blocked volume of currency or instrument
1265                    "currentPrice": curPrice,  # current instrument's price in basic asset
1266                    "average": average,  # current average position price
1267                    "cost": cost,  # current cost of all volume of instrument in basic asset
1268                    "baseCurrencyName": baseCurrencyName,  # name of base currency (rub)
1269                    "costRUB": costRUB,  # cost of instrument in ruble
1270                    "percentCostRUB": percentCostRUB,  # instrument's part in percent of full portfolio cost in RUB
1271                    "profit": profit,  # expected profit at current moment
1272                    "percentProfit": 100 * profit / (average * volume),  # expected percents of profit at current moment for this instrument
1273                    "sector": instrument["sector"] if "sector" in instrument.keys() and instrument["sector"] else "other",
1274                    "name": instrument["name"] if "name" in instrument.keys() else "",  # human-readable names of instruments
1275                    "isoCurrencyName": instrument["isoCurrencyName"] if "isoCurrencyName" in instrument.keys() else "",  # ISO name for currencies only
1276                }
1277
1278                if item["instrumentType"] != "currency":
1279                    # adding distribution by unique companies:
1280                    if statData["name"]:
1281                        if statData["name"] not in byComp.keys():
1282                            byComp[statData["name"]] = {"ticker": statData["ticker"], "cost": costRUB, "percent": percentCostRUB}
1283
1284                        else:
1285                            byComp[statData["name"]]["cost"] += costRUB
1286                            byComp[statData["name"]]["percent"] += percentCostRUB
1287
1288                    # adding distribution by unique sectors:
1289                    if statData["sector"] not in bySect.keys():
1290                        bySect[statData["sector"]] = {"cost": costRUB, "percent": percentCostRUB}
1291
1292                    else:
1293                        bySect[statData["sector"]]["cost"] += costRUB
1294                        bySect[statData["sector"]]["percent"] += percentCostRUB
1295
1296                # adding distribution by unique currencies:
1297                if currency not in byCurr.keys():
1298                    byCurr[currency] = {
1299                        "name": view["raw"]["currenciesCurrentPrices"][currency]["name"],
1300                        "cost": costRUB,
1301                        "percent": percentCostRUB
1302                    }
1303
1304                else:
1305                    byCurr[currency]["cost"] += costRUB
1306                    byCurr[currency]["percent"] += percentCostRUB
1307
1308                # saving statistics for every instruments:
1309                if item["instrumentType"] == "currency":
1310                    view["stat"]["Currencies"].append(statData)
1311
1312                elif item["instrumentType"] == "share":
1313                    view["stat"]["Shares"].append(statData)
1314
1315                elif item["instrumentType"] == "bond":
1316                    view["stat"]["Bonds"].append(statData)
1317
1318                elif item["instrumentType"] == "etf":
1319                    view["stat"]["Etfs"].append(statData)
1320
1321                elif item["instrumentType"] == "Futures":
1322                    view["stat"]["Futures"].append(statData)
1323
1324                else:
1325                    continue
1326
1327        # total changes:
1328        view["stat"]["availableRUB"] = view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"] - sum([item["cost"] for item in view["stat"]["Currencies"]])  # available RUB without other currencies
1329        view["stat"]["totalChangesPercentRUB"] = NanoToFloat(view["raw"]["headers"]["expectedYield"]["units"], view["raw"]["headers"]["expectedYield"]["nano"]) if "expectedYield" in view["raw"]["headers"].keys() else 0.
1330        startCost = view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] / (1 + view["stat"]["totalChangesPercentRUB"] / 100)
1331        view["stat"]["totalChangesRUB"] = view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] - startCost
1332
1333        # --- pending orders sector data:
1334        for item in view["raw"]["orders"]:
1335            self.figi = item["figi"]
1336            instrument = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True)  # full raw info about instrument by FIGI
1337
1338            if instrument:
1339                action = TKS_ORDER_DIRECTIONS[item["direction"]]
1340                orderType = TKS_ORDER_TYPES[item["orderType"]]
1341                orderState = TKS_ORDER_STATES[item["executionReportStatus"]]
1342                orderDate = item["orderDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "").split(".")[0]  # date in UTC format, e.g. "2022-12-31T23:59:59.123456Z"
1343
1344                # current instrument's price (last sellers order if buy, and last buyers order if sell):
1345                if item["direction"] == "ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY":
1346                    lastPrice = instrument["currentPrice"]["sell"][0]["price"] if instrument["currentPrice"]["sell"] else "N/A"
1347
1348                else:
1349                    lastPrice = instrument["currentPrice"]["buy"][0]["price"] if instrument["currentPrice"]["buy"] else "N/A"
1350
1351                # requested price for order execution:
1352                target = NanoToFloat(item["initialSecurityPrice"]["units"], item["initialSecurityPrice"]["nano"])
1353
1354                # necessary changes in percent to reach target from current price:
1355                changes = 100 * (lastPrice - target) / target if lastPrice != "N/A" and target > 0 else 0
1356
1357                view["stat"]["orders"].append({
1358                    "orderID": item["orderId"],  # orderId number parameter of current order
1359                    "figi": item["figi"],  # FIGI identification
1360                    "ticker": instrument["ticker"],  # ticker name by FIGI
1361                    "lotsRequested": item["lotsRequested"],  # requested lots value
1362                    "lotsExecuted": item["lotsExecuted"],  # how many lots are executed
1363                    "currentPrice": lastPrice,  # current instrument's price for defined action
1364                    "targetPrice": target,  # requested price for order execution in base currency
1365                    "baseCurrencyName": item["initialSecurityPrice"]["currency"],  # name of base currency
1366                    "percentChanges": changes,  # changes in percent to target from current price
1367                    "currency": item["currency"],  # instrument's currency name
1368                    "action": action,  # sell / buy / Unknown from TKS_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
1369                    "type": orderType,  # type of order from TKS_ORDER_TYPES
1370                    "status": orderState,  # order status from TKS_ORDER_STATES
1371                    "date": orderDate,  # string with order date and time from UTC format (without nano seconds part)
1372                })
1373
1374        # --- stop orders sector data:
1375        for item in view["raw"]["stopOrders"]:
1376            self.figi = item["figi"]
1377            instrument = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True)  # full raw info about instrument by FIGI
1378
1379            if instrument:
1380                action = TKS_STOP_ORDER_DIRECTIONS[item["direction"]]
1381                orderType = TKS_STOP_ORDER_TYPES[item["orderType"]]
1382                createDate = item["createDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "").split(".")[0]  # date in UTC format, e.g. "2022-12-31T23:59:59.123456Z"
1383
1384                # hack: server response can't contain "expirationTime" key if it is not "Until date" type of stop order
1385                if "expirationTime" in item.keys():
1386                    expType = TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES["STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_GOOD_TILL_DATE"]
1387                    expDate = item["expirationTime"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "").split(".")[0]
1388
1389                else:
1390                    expType = TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES["STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_GOOD_TILL_CANCEL"]
1391                    expDate = TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES["STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED"]
1392
1393                # current instrument's price (last sellers order if buy, and last buyers order if sell):
1394                if item["direction"] == "STOP_ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY":
1395                    lastPrice = instrument["currentPrice"]["sell"][0]["price"] if instrument["currentPrice"]["sell"] else "N/A"
1396
1397                else:
1398                    lastPrice = instrument["currentPrice"]["buy"][0]["price"] if instrument["currentPrice"]["buy"] else "N/A"
1399
1400                # requested price when stop-order executed:
1401                target = NanoToFloat(item["stopPrice"]["units"], item["stopPrice"]["nano"])
1402
1403                # price for limit-order, set up when stop-order executed:
1404                limit = NanoToFloat(item["price"]["units"], item["price"]["nano"])
1405
1406                # necessary changes in percent to reach target from current price:
1407                changes = 100 * (lastPrice - target) / target if lastPrice != "N/A" and target > 0 else 0
1408
1409                view["stat"]["stopOrders"].append({
1410                    "orderID": item["stopOrderId"],  # stopOrderId number parameter of current stop-order
1411                    "figi": item["figi"],  # FIGI identification
1412                    "ticker": instrument["ticker"],  # ticker name by FIGI
1413                    "lotsRequested": item["lotsRequested"],  # requested lots value
1414                    "currentPrice": lastPrice,  # current instrument's price for defined action
1415                    "targetPrice": target,  # requested price for stop-order execution in base currency
1416                    "limitPrice": limit,  # price for limit-order, set up when stop-order executed, 0 if market order
1417                    "baseCurrencyName": item["stopPrice"]["currency"],  # name of base currency
1418                    "percentChanges": changes,  # changes in percent to target from current price
1419                    "currency": item["currency"],  # instrument's currency name
1420                    "action": action,  # sell / buy / Unknown from TKS_STOP_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
1421                    "type": orderType,  # type of order from TKS_STOP_ORDER_TYPES
1422                    "expType": expType,  # expiration type of stop-order from TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES
1423                    "createDate": createDate,  # string with created order date and time from UTC format (without nano seconds part)
1424                    "expDate": expDate,  # string with expiration order date and time from UTC format (without nano seconds part)
1425                })
1426
1427        # --- calculating data for analytics section:
1428        # portfolio distribution by assets:
1429        view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"] = {
1430            "Ruble": {
1431                "uniques": 1,
1432                "cost": view["stat"]["availableRUB"],
1433                "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["availableRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1434            },
1435            "Currencies": {
1436                "uniques": len(view["stat"]["Currencies"]),  # all foreign currencies without RUB
1437                "cost": view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"] - view["stat"]["availableRUB"],
1438                "percent": 100 * (view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"] - view["stat"]["availableRUB"]) / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1439            },
1440            "Shares": {
1441                "uniques": len(view["stat"]["Shares"]),
1442                "cost": view["stat"]["stocksCostRUB"],
1443                "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["stocksCostRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1444            },
1445            "Bonds": {
1446                "uniques": len(view["stat"]["Bonds"]),
1447                "cost": view["stat"]["bondsCostRUB"],
1448                "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["bondsCostRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1449            },
1450            "Etfs": {
1451                "uniques": len(view["stat"]["Etfs"]),
1452                "cost": view["stat"]["etfsCostRUB"],
1453                "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["etfsCostRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1454            },
1455            "Futures": {
1456                "uniques": len(view["stat"]["Futures"]),
1457                "cost": view["stat"]["futuresCostRUB"],
1458                "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["futuresCostRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1459            },
1460        }
1461
1462        # portfolio distribution by companies:
1463        view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"]["All money cash"] = {
1464            "ticker": "",
1465            "cost": view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"],
1466            "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1467        }
1468        view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"].update(byComp)
1469
1470        # portfolio distribution by sectors:
1471        view["analytics"]["distrBySectors"]["All money cash"] = {
1472            "cost": view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"]["All money cash"]["cost"],
1473            "percent": view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"]["All money cash"]["percent"],
1474        }
1475        view["analytics"]["distrBySectors"].update(bySect)
1476
1477        # portfolio distribution by currencies:
1478        view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"].update(byCurr)
1479        view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"]["rub"]["cost"] += view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"]["Ruble"]["cost"]
1480        view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"]["rub"]["percent"] += view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"]["Ruble"]["percent"]
1481
1482        # --- Prepare text statistics overview in human-readable:
1483        if showStatistics:
1484            info = [
1485                "# Client's portfolio\n\n",
1486                "* **Actual date:** [{}] (UTC)\n".format(datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")),
1487                "* **Portfolio cost:** {:.2f} RUB\n".format(view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"]),
1488                "* **Changes:** {}{:.2f} RUB ({}{:.2f}%)\n\n".format(
1489                    "+" if view["stat"]["totalChangesRUB"] > 0 else "",
1490                    view["stat"]["totalChangesRUB"],
1491                    "+" if view["stat"]["totalChangesPercentRUB"] > 0 else "",
1492                    view["stat"]["totalChangesPercentRUB"],
1493                ),
1494                "## Open positions\n\n",
1495                "| Ticker [FIGI]               | Volume (blocked)                | Lots     | Curr. price  | Avg. price   | Current volume cost | Profit (%)\n",
1496                "|-----------------------------|---------------------------------|----------|--------------|--------------|---------------------|----------------------\n",
1497                "| Ruble                       | {:>31} |          |              |              |                     |\n".format(
1498                    "{:.2f} ({:.2f}) rub".format(
1499                        view["stat"]["availableRUB"],
1500                        view["stat"]["currentBlockedRUB"],
1501                    )
1502                )
1503            ]
1504
1505            def _SplitStr(CostRUB: float = 0, typeStr: str = "", noTradeStr: str = "") -> list:
1506                return [
1507                    "|                             |                                 |          |              |              |                     |\n",
1508                    "| {:<27} |                                 |          |              |              | {:>19} |\n".format(
1509                        noTradeStr if noTradeStr else typeStr,
1510                        "" if noTradeStr else "{:.2f} RUB".format(CostRUB),
1511                    ),
1512                ]
1513
1514            def _InfoStr(data: dict, showCurrencyName: bool = False) -> str:
1515                return "| {:<27} | {:>31} | {:<8} | {:>12} | {:>12} | {:>19} | {}\n".format(
1516                    "{} [{}]".format(data["ticker"], data["figi"]),
1517                    "{:.2f} ({:.2f}) {}".format(
1518                        data["volume"],
1519                        data["blocked"],
1520                        data["currency"],
1521                    ) if showCurrencyName else "{:.0f} ({:.0f})".format(
1522                        data["volume"],
1523                        data["blocked"],
1524                    ),
1525                    "{:.4f}".format(data["lots"]) if showCurrencyName else "{:.0f}".format(data["lots"]),
1526                    "{:.2f} {}".format(data["currentPrice"], data["baseCurrencyName"]) if data["currentPrice"] > 0 else "n/a",
1527                    "{:.2f} {}".format(data["average"], data["baseCurrencyName"]) if data["average"] > 0 else "n/a",
1528                    "{:.2f} {}".format(data["cost"], data["baseCurrencyName"]),
1529                    "{}{:.2f} {} ({}{:.2f}%)".format(
1530                        "+" if data["profit"] > 0 else "",
1531                        data["profit"], data["baseCurrencyName"],
1532                        "+" if data["percentProfit"] > 0 else "",
1533                        data["percentProfit"],
1534                    ),
1535                )
1536
1537            # --- Show currencies section:
1538            if view["stat"]["Currencies"]:
1539                info.extend(_SplitStr(CostRUB=view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"]["Currencies"]["cost"], typeStr="**Currencies:**"))
1540                for item in view["stat"]["Currencies"]:
1541                    info.append(_InfoStr(item, showCurrencyName=True))
1542
1543            else:
1544                info.extend(_SplitStr(noTradeStr="**Currencies:** no trades"))
1545
1546            # --- Show stocks section:
1547            if view["stat"]["Shares"]:
1548                info.extend(_SplitStr(CostRUB=view["stat"]["stocksCostRUB"], typeStr="**Stocks:**"))
1549
1550                for item in view["stat"]["Shares"]:
1551                    info.append(_InfoStr(item))
1552
1553            else:
1554                info.extend(_SplitStr(noTradeStr="**Stocks:** no trades"))
1555
1556            # --- Show bonds section:
1557            if view["stat"]["Bonds"]:
1558                info.extend(_SplitStr(CostRUB=view["stat"]["bondsCostRUB"], typeStr="**Bonds:**"))
1559
1560                for item in view["stat"]["Bonds"]:
1561                    info.append(_InfoStr(item))
1562
1563            else:
1564                info.extend(_SplitStr(noTradeStr="**Bonds:** no trades"))
1565
1566            # --- Show etfs section:
1567            if view["stat"]["Etfs"]:
1568                info.extend(_SplitStr(CostRUB=view["stat"]["etfsCostRUB"], typeStr="**Etfs:**"))
1569
1570                for item in view["stat"]["Etfs"]:
1571                    info.append(_InfoStr(item))
1572
1573            else:
1574                info.extend(_SplitStr(noTradeStr="**Etfs:** no trades"))
1575
1576            # --- Show futures section:
1577            if view["stat"]["Futures"]:
1578                info.extend(_SplitStr(CostRUB=view["stat"]["futuresCostRUB"], typeStr="**Futures:**"))
1579
1580                for item in view["stat"]["Futures"]:
1581                    info.append(_InfoStr(item))
1582
1583            else:
1584                info.extend(_SplitStr(noTradeStr="**Futures:** no trades"))
1585
1586            # --- Show pending orders section:
1587            if view["stat"]["orders"]:
1588                info.extend([
1589                    "\n## Opened pending limit-orders: {}\n".format(len(view["stat"]["orders"])),
1590                    "\n| Ticker [FIGI]               | Order ID       | Lots (exec.) | Current price (% delta) | Target price  | Action    | Type      | Create date (UTC)\n",
1591                    "|-----------------------------|----------------|--------------|-------------------------|---------------|-----------|-----------|---------------------\n",
1592                ])
1593                for item in view["stat"]["orders"]:
1594                    info.append("| {:<27} | {:<14} | {:<12} | {:>23} | {:>13} | {:<9} | {:<9} | {}\n".format(
1595                        "{} [{}]".format(item["ticker"], item["figi"]),
1596                        item["orderID"],
1597                        "{} ({})".format(item["lotsRequested"], item["lotsExecuted"]),
1598                        "{} {} ({}{:.2f}%)".format(
1599                            "{}".format(item["currentPrice"]) if isinstance(item["currentPrice"], str) else "{:.2f}".format(float(item["currentPrice"])),
1600                            item["baseCurrencyName"],
1601                            "+" if item["percentChanges"] > 0 else "",
1602                            float(item["percentChanges"]),
1603                        ),
1604                        "{:.2f} {}".format(float(item["targetPrice"]), item["baseCurrencyName"]),
1605                        item["action"],
1606                        item["type"],
1607                        item["date"],
1608                    ))
1609
1610            else:
1611                info.append("\n## Total pending limit-orders: 0\n")
1612
1613            # --- Show stop orders section:
1614            if view["stat"]["stopOrders"]:
1615                info.extend([
1616                    "\n## Opened stop-orders: {}\n".format(len(view["stat"]["stopOrders"])),
1617                    "\n| Ticker [FIGI]               | Stop order ID                        | Lots   | Current price (% delta) | Target price  | Limit price   | Action    | Type        | Expire type  | Create date (UTC)   | Expiration (UTC)\n",
1618                    "|-----------------------------|--------------------------------------|--------|-------------------------|---------------|---------------|-----------|-------------|--------------|---------------------|---------------------\n",
1619                ])
1620                for item in view["stat"]["stopOrders"]:
1621                    info.append("| {:<27} | {:<14} | {:<6} | {:>23} | {:>13} | {:>13} | {:<9} | {:<11} | {:<12} | {:<19} | {}\n".format(
1622                        "{} [{}]".format(item["ticker"], item["figi"]),
1623                        item["orderID"],
1624                        item["lotsRequested"],
1625                        "{} {} ({}{:.2f}%)".format(
1626                            "{}".format(item["currentPrice"]) if isinstance(item["currentPrice"], str) else "{:.2f}".format(float(item["currentPrice"])),
1627                            item["baseCurrencyName"],
1628                            "+" if item["percentChanges"] > 0 else "",
1629                            float(item["percentChanges"]),
1630                        ),
1631                        "{:.2f} {}".format(float(item["targetPrice"]), item["baseCurrencyName"]),
1632                        "{:.2f} {}".format(float(item["limitPrice"]), item["baseCurrencyName"]) if item["limitPrice"] and item["limitPrice"] != item["targetPrice"] else TKS_ORDER_TYPES["ORDER_TYPE_MARKET"],
1633                        item["action"],
1634                        item["type"],
1635                        item["expType"],
1636                        item["createDate"],
1637                        item["expDate"],
1638                    ))
1639
1640            else:
1641                info.append("\n## Total stop-orders: 0\n")
1642
1643            # -- Show analytics section:
1644            if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0:
1645                info.extend([
1646                    "\n# Analytics\n"
1647                    "\n* **Current total portfolio cost:** {:.2f} RUB\n".format(view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"]),
1648                    "* **Changes:** {}{:.2f} RUB ({}{:.2f}%)\n".format(
1649                        "+" if view["stat"]["totalChangesRUB"] > 0 else "",
1650                        view["stat"]["totalChangesRUB"],
1651                        "+" if view["stat"]["totalChangesPercentRUB"] > 0 else "",
1652                        view["stat"]["totalChangesPercentRUB"],
1653                    ),
1654                    "\n## Portfolio distribution by assets\n"
1655                    "\n| Type       | Uniques | Percent | Current cost\n",
1656                    "|------------|---------|---------|-----------------\n",
1657                ])
1658
1659                for key in view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"].keys():
1660                    if view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"][key]["cost"] > 0:
1661                        info.append("| {:<10} | {:<7} | {:<7} | {:.2f} rub\n".format(
1662                            key,
1663                            view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"][key]["uniques"],
1664                            "{:.2f}%".format(view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"][key]["percent"]),
1665                            view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"][key]["cost"],
1666                        ))
1667
1668                maxLenNames = 3 + max([len(company) + len(view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"][company]["ticker"]) for company in view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"].keys()])
1669                info.extend([
1670                    "\n## Portfolio distribution by companies\n"
1671                    "\n| Company{} | Percent | Current cost\n".format(" " * (maxLenNames - 7)),
1672                    "|--------{}-|---------|-----------------\n".format("-" * (maxLenNames - 7)),
1673                ])
1674
1675                for company in view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"].keys():
1676                    if view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"][company]["cost"] > 0:
1677                        nameLen = 3 + len(company) + len(view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"][company]["ticker"])
1678                        info.append("| {} | {:<7} | {:.2f} rub\n".format(
1679                            "{}{}{}".format(
1680                                "[{}] ".format(view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"][company]["ticker"]) if view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"][company]["ticker"] else "",
1681                                company,
1682                                "" if nameLen == maxLenNames else "{}".format(" " * (maxLenNames - nameLen) if view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"][company]["ticker"] else " " * (maxLenNames - nameLen + 3)),
1683                            ),
1684                            "{:.2f}%".format(view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"][company]["percent"]),
1685                            view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"][company]["cost"],
1686                        ))
1687
1688                maxLenSectors = max([len(sector) for sector in view["analytics"]["distrBySectors"].keys()])
1689                info.extend([
1690                    "\n## Portfolio distribution by sectors\n"
1691                    "\n| Sector{} | Percent | Current cost\n".format(" " * (maxLenSectors - 6)),
1692                    "|-------{}-|---------|-----------------\n".format("-" * (maxLenSectors - 6)),
1693                ])
1694
1695                for sector in view["analytics"]["distrBySectors"].keys():
1696                    if view["analytics"]["distrBySectors"][sector]["cost"] > 0:
1697                        info.append("| {}{} | {:<7} | {:.2f} rub\n".format(
1698                            sector,
1699                            "" if len(sector) == maxLenSectors else " " * (maxLenSectors - len(sector)),
1700                            "{:.2f}%".format(view["analytics"]["distrBySectors"][sector]["percent"]),
1701                            view["analytics"]["distrBySectors"][sector]["cost"],
1702                        ))
1703
1704                maxLenMoney = 3 + max([len(currency) + len(view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"][currency]["name"]) for currency in view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"].keys()])
1705                info.extend([
1706                    "\n## Portfolio distribution by currencies\n"
1707                    "\n| Instruments currencies{} | Percent | Current cost\n".format(" " * (maxLenMoney - 22)),
1708                    "|-----------------------{}-|---------|-----------------\n".format("-" * (maxLenMoney - 22)),
1709                ])
1710
1711                for curr in view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"].keys():
1712                    if view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"][curr]["cost"] > 0:
1713                        nameLen = 3 + len(curr) + len(view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"][curr]["name"])
1714                        info.append("| {} | {:<7} | {:.2f} rub\n".format(
1715                            "[{}] {}{}".format(
1716                                curr,
1717                                view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"][curr]["name"],
1718                                "" if nameLen == maxLenMoney else " " * (maxLenMoney - nameLen),
1719                            ),
1720                            "{:.2f}%".format(view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"][curr]["percent"]),
1721                            view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"][curr]["cost"],
1722                        ))
1723
1724            infoText = "".join(info)
1725
1726            if showStatistics:
1727                uLogger.info("Statistics of client's portfolio:\n{}".format(infoText))
1728
1729            if self.overviewFile:
1730                with open(self.overviewFile, "w", encoding="UTF-8") as fH:
1731                    fH.write(infoText)
1732
1733                uLogger.info("Client's portfolio is saved to file: [{}]".format(os.path.abspath(self.overviewFile)))
1734
1735        return view
1736
1737    def Deals(self, start: str = None, end: str = None, printDeals: bool = False) -> tuple:
1738        """
1739        Returns history operations between two given dates.
1740        If `reportFile` string is not empty then also save human-readable report.
1741        Shows some statistical data of closed positions.
1742
1743        :param start: see docstring in `GetDatesAsString()` method
1744        :param end: see docstring in `GetDatesAsString()` method
1745        :param printDeals: if `True` then also print all records to the console.
1746        :return: original list of dictionaries with history of deals records from API ("operations" key):
1747                 https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/OperationsService/OperationsService_GetOperations
1748                 and dictionary with custom stats: operations in different currencies, withdrawals, incomes etc.
1749        """
1750        startDate, endDate = GetDatesAsString(start, end)  # Example: ("2000-01-01T00:00:00Z", "2022-12-31T23:59:59Z")
1751
1752        uLogger.debug("Requesting history of a client's operations. Wait, please...")
1753
1754        # REST API for request: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/OperationsService/OperationsService_GetOperations
1755        dealsURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OperationsService/GetOperations"
1756        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId, "from": startDate, "to": endDate})
1757        ops = self.SendAPIRequest(dealsURL, reqType="POST")["operations"]  # list of dict: operations returns by broker
1758        customStat = {}  # custom statistics in additional to responseJSON
1759
1760        # --- output report in human-readable format:
1761        if printDeals or self.reportFile:
1762            splitLine1 = "|                            |                               |                              |                      |\n"  # Summary section
1763            splitLine2 = "|                     |              |              |            |           |                 |            |\n"  # Operations section
1764            nextDay = ""
1765
1766            info = ["# Client's operations\n\n* **Period:** from [{}] to [{}]\n\n## Summary (operations executed only)\n\n".format(startDate.split("T")[0], endDate.split("T")[0])]
1767
1768            if len(ops) > 0:
1769                customStat = {
1770                    "opsCount": 0,  # total operations count
1771                    "buyCount": 0,  # buy operations
1772                    "sellCount": 0,  # sell operations
1773                    "buyTotal": {"rub": 0.},  # Buy sums in different currencies
1774                    "sellTotal": {"rub": 0.},  # Sell sums in different currencies
1775                    "payIn": {"rub": 0.},  # Deposit brokerage account
1776                    "payOut": {"rub": 0.},  # Withdrawals
1777                    "divs": {"rub": 0.},  # Dividends income
1778                    "coupons": {"rub": 0.},  # Coupon's income
1779                    "brokerCom": {"rub": 0.},  # Service commissions
1780                    "serviceCom": {"rub": 0.},  # Service commissions
1781                    "marginCom": {"rub": 0.},  # Margin commissions
1782                    "allTaxes": {"rub": 0.},  # Sum of withholding taxes and corrections
1783                }
1784
1785                # --- calculating statistics depends on operations type in TKS_OPERATION_TYPES:
1786                for item in ops:
1787                    if item["state"] == "OPERATION_STATE_EXECUTED":
1788                        payment = NanoToFloat(item["payment"]["units"], item["payment"]["nano"])
1789
1790                        # count buy operations:
1791                        if "_BUY" in item["operationType"]:
1792                            customStat["buyCount"] += 1
1793
1794                            if item["payment"]["currency"] in customStat["buyTotal"].keys():
1795                                customStat["buyTotal"][item["payment"]["currency"]] += payment
1796
1797                            else:
1798                                customStat["buyTotal"][item["payment"]["currency"]] = payment
1799
1800                        # count sell operations:
1801                        elif "_SELL" in item["operationType"]:
1802                            customStat["sellCount"] += 1
1803
1804                            if item["payment"]["currency"] in customStat["sellTotal"].keys():
1805                                customStat["sellTotal"][item["payment"]["currency"]] += payment
1806
1807                            else:
1808                                customStat["sellTotal"][item["payment"]["currency"]] = payment
1809
1810                        # count incoming operations:
1811                        elif item["operationType"] in ["OPERATION_TYPE_INPUT"]:
1812                            if item["payment"]["currency"] in customStat["payIn"].keys():
1813                                customStat["payIn"][item["payment"]["currency"]] += payment
1814
1815                            else:
1816                                customStat["payIn"][item["payment"]["currency"]] = payment
1817
1818                        # count withdrawals operations:
1819                        elif item["operationType"] in ["OPERATION_TYPE_OUTPUT"]:
1820                            if item["payment"]["currency"] in customStat["payOut"].keys():
1821                                customStat["payOut"][item["payment"]["currency"]] += payment
1822
1823                            else:
1824                                customStat["payOut"][item["payment"]["currency"]] = payment
1825
1826                        # count dividends income:
1827                        elif item["operationType"] in ["OPERATION_TYPE_DIVIDEND", "OPERATION_TYPE_DIVIDEND_TRANSFER", "OPERATION_TYPE_DIV_EXT"]:
1828                            if item["payment"]["currency"] in customStat["divs"].keys():
1829                                customStat["divs"][item["payment"]["currency"]] += payment
1830
1831                            else:
1832                                customStat["divs"][item["payment"]["currency"]] = payment
1833
1834                        # count coupon's income:
1835                        elif item["operationType"] in ["OPERATION_TYPE_COUPON", "OPERATION_TYPE_BOND_REPAYMENT_FULL", "OPERATION_TYPE_BOND_REPAYMENT"]:
1836                            if item["payment"]["currency"] in customStat["coupons"].keys():
1837                                customStat["coupons"][item["payment"]["currency"]] += payment
1838
1839                            else:
1840                                customStat["coupons"][item["payment"]["currency"]] = payment
1841
1842                        # count broker commissions:
1843                        elif item["operationType"] in ["OPERATION_TYPE_BROKER_FEE", "OPERATION_TYPE_SUCCESS_FEE", "OPERATION_TYPE_TRACK_MFEE", "OPERATION_TYPE_TRACK_PFEE"]:
1844                            if item["payment"]["currency"] in customStat["brokerCom"].keys():
1845                                customStat["brokerCom"][item["payment"]["currency"]] += payment
1846
1847                            else:
1848                                customStat["brokerCom"][item["payment"]["currency"]] = payment
1849
1850                        # count service commissions:
1851                        elif item["operationType"] in ["OPERATION_TYPE_SERVICE_FEE"]:
1852                            if item["payment"]["currency"] in customStat["serviceCom"].keys():
1853                                customStat["serviceCom"][item["payment"]["currency"]] += payment
1854
1855                            else:
1856                                customStat["serviceCom"][item["payment"]["currency"]] = payment
1857
1858                        # count margin commissions:
1859                        elif item["operationType"] in ["OPERATION_TYPE_MARGIN_FEE"]:
1860                            if item["payment"]["currency"] in customStat["marginCom"].keys():
1861                                customStat["marginCom"][item["payment"]["currency"]] += payment
1862
1863                            else:
1864                                customStat["marginCom"][item["payment"]["currency"]] = payment
1865
1866                        # count withholding taxes:
1867                        elif "_TAX" in item["operationType"]:
1868                            if item["payment"]["currency"] in customStat["allTaxes"].keys():
1869                                customStat["allTaxes"][item["payment"]["currency"]] += payment
1870
1871                            else:
1872                                customStat["allTaxes"][item["payment"]["currency"]] = payment
1873
1874                        else:
1875                            continue
1876
1877                customStat["opsCount"] += customStat["buyCount"] + customStat["sellCount"]
1878
1879                # --- view "Actions" lines:
1880                info.extend([
1881                    "| 1                          | 2                             | 3                            | 4                    | 5\n",
1882                    "|----------------------------|-------------------------------|------------------------------|----------------------|------------------------\n",
1883                    "| **Actions:**               | Operations executed: {:<8} | Trading volumes:             |                      |\n".format(customStat["opsCount"]),
1884                    "|                            |   Buy: {:<22} | {:<28} |                      |\n".format(
1885                        "{} ({:.1f}%)".format(customStat["buyCount"], 100 * customStat["buyCount"] / customStat["opsCount"]) if customStat["opsCount"] != 0 else 0,
1886                        "  rub, buy: {:<16}".format("{:.2f}".format(customStat["buyTotal"]["rub"])) if customStat["buyTotal"]["rub"] != 0 else "  —",
1887                    ),
1888                    "|                            |   Sell: {:<21} | {:<28} |                      |\n".format(
1889                        "{} ({:.1f}%)".format(customStat["sellCount"], 100 * customStat["sellCount"] / customStat["opsCount"]) if customStat["opsCount"] != 0 else 0,
1890                        "  rub, sell: {:<13}".format("+{:.2f}".format(customStat["sellTotal"]["rub"])) if customStat["sellTotal"]["rub"] != 0 else "  —",
1891                    ),
1892                ])
1893
