1894                opsKeys = sorted(list(set(list(customStat["buyTotal"].keys()) + list(customStat["sellTotal"].keys()))))
1895                for key in opsKeys:
1896                    if key == "rub":
1897                        continue
1898
1899                    info.extend([
1900                        "|                            |                               | {:<28} |                      |\n".format(
1901                            "  {}, buy: {:<16}".format(key, "{:.2f}".format(customStat["buyTotal"][key]) if key and key in customStat["buyTotal"].keys() and customStat["buyTotal"][key] != 0 else 0)
1902                        ),
1903                        "|                            |                               | {:<28} |                      |\n".format(
1904                            "  {}, sell: {:<13}".format(key, "+{:.2f}".format(customStat["sellTotal"][key]) if key and key in customStat["sellTotal"].keys() and customStat["sellTotal"][key] != 0 else 0)
1905                        ),
1906                    ])
1907
1908                info.append(splitLine1)
1909
1910                def _InfoStr(data1: dict, data2: dict, data3: dict, data4: dict, cur: str = "") -> str:
1911                    return "|                            | {:<29} | {:<28} | {:<20} | {:<22}\n".format(
1912                            "  {}: {}{:.2f}".format(cur, "+" if data1[cur] > 0 else "", data1[cur]) if cur and cur in data1.keys() and data1[cur] != 0 else "  —",
1913                            "  {}: {}{:.2f}".format(cur, "+" if data2[cur] > 0 else "", data2[cur]) if cur and cur in data2.keys() and data2[cur] != 0 else "  —",
1914                            "  {}: {}{:.2f}".format(cur, "+" if data3[cur] > 0 else "", data3[cur]) if cur and cur in data3.keys() and data3[cur] != 0 else "  —",
1915                            "  {}: {}{:.2f}".format(cur, "+" if data4[cur] > 0 else "", data4[cur]) if cur and cur in data4.keys() and data4[cur] != 0 else "  —",
1916                    )
1917
1918                # --- view "Payments" lines:
1919                info.append("| **Payments:**              | Deposit on broker account:    | Withdrawals:                 | Dividends income:    | Coupons income:\n")
1920                paymentsKeys = sorted(list(set(list(customStat["payIn"].keys()) + list(customStat["payOut"].keys()) + list(customStat["divs"].keys()) + list(customStat["coupons"].keys()))))
1921
1922                for key in paymentsKeys:
1923                    info.append(_InfoStr(customStat["payIn"], customStat["payOut"], customStat["divs"], customStat["coupons"], key))
1924
1925                info.append(splitLine1)
1926
1927                # --- view "Commissions and taxes" lines:
1928                info.append("| **Commissions and taxes:** | Broker commissions:           | Service commissions:         | Margin commissions:  | All taxes/corrections:\n")
1929                comKeys = sorted(list(set(list(customStat["brokerCom"].keys()) + list(customStat["serviceCom"].keys()) + list(customStat["marginCom"].keys()) + list(customStat["allTaxes"].keys()))))
1930
1931                for key in comKeys:
1932                    info.append(_InfoStr(customStat["brokerCom"], customStat["serviceCom"], customStat["marginCom"], customStat["allTaxes"], key))
1933
1934                info.append(splitLine1)
1935
1936                info.extend([
1937                    "\n## All operations\n\n",
1938                    "| Date and time       | FIGI         | Ticker       | Asset      | Value     | Payment         | Status     | Operation type\n",
1939                    "|---------------------|--------------|--------------|------------|-----------|-----------------|------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
1940                ])
1941
1942            else:
1943                info.append("Broker returned no operations during this period\n")
1944
1945            # --- view "Operations" section:
1946            for item in ops:
1947                self.figi = item["figi"] if item["figi"] else ""
1948                payment = NanoToFloat(item["payment"]["units"], item["payment"]["nano"])
1949                instrument = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=False) if self.figi else {}
1950
1951                # group of deals during one day:
1952                if nextDay and item["date"].split("T")[0] != nextDay:
1953                    info.append(splitLine2)
1954                    nextDay = ""
1955
1956                else:
1957                    nextDay = item["date"].split("T")[0]  # saving current day for splitting
1958
1959                info.append("| {:<19} | {:<12} | {:<12} | {:<10} | {:<9} | {:>15} | {:<10} | {}\n".format(
1960                    item["date"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "").split(".")[0],
1961                    self.figi if self.figi else "—",
1962                    instrument["ticker"] if instrument else "—",
1963                    instrument["type"] if instrument else "—",
1964                    item["quantity"] if int(item["quantity"]) > 0 else "—",
1965                    "{}{:.2f} {}".format("+" if payment > 0 else "", payment, item["payment"]["currency"]) if payment != 0 else "—",
1966                    TKS_OPERATION_STATES[item["state"]],
1967                    TKS_OPERATION_TYPES[item["operationType"]],
1968                ))
1969
1970            infoText = "".join(info)
1971
1972            if printDeals:
1973                uLogger.info(infoText)
1974
1975            if self.reportFile:
1976                with open(self.reportFile, "w", encoding="UTF-8") as fH:
1977                    fH.write(infoText)
1978
1979                uLogger.info("History of a client's operations are saved to file: [{}]".format(os.path.abspath(self.reportFile)))
1980
1981        return ops, customStat
1982

2147    def Trade(self, operation: str, lots: int = 1, tp: float = 0., sl: float = 0., expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2148        """
2149        Universal method to create market order and make deal at the current price. Returns JSON data with response.
2150        If `tp` or `sl` > 0, then in additional will opens stop-orders with "TP" and "SL" flags for `stopType` parameter.
2151
2152        See also: `Order()` docstring. More simple methods than `Trade()` are `Buy()` and `Sell()`.
2153
2154        :param operation: string "Buy" or "Sell".
2155        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2156        :param tp: float > 0, target price for stop-order with "TP" type. It used as take profit parameter `targetPrice` in `self.Order()`.
2157        :param sl: float > 0, target price for stop-order with "SL" type. It used as stop loss parameter `targetPrice` in `self.Order()`.
2158        :param expDate: string "Undefined" by default or local date in future,
2159                        it is a string with format `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2160        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2161        """
2162        if operation is None or not operation or operation not in ("Buy", "Sell"):
2163            raise Exception("You must define operation type only one of them: `Buy` or `Sell`!")
2164
2165        if lots is None or lots < 1:
2166            uLogger.warning("You must define trade volume > 0: integer count of lots! For current operation lots reset to 1.")
2167            lots = 1
2168
2169        if tp is None or tp < 0:
2170            tp = 0
2171
2172        if sl is None or sl < 0:
2173            sl = 0
2174
2175        if expDate is None or not expDate:
2176            expDate = "Undefined"
2177
2178        if not (self.ticker or self.figi):
2179            raise Exception("`self.ticker` or `self.figi` variables must be defined!")
2180
2181        instrument = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=True, debug=False) if self.ticker else self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True, debug=False)
2182        self.ticker = instrument["ticker"]
2183        self.figi = instrument["figi"]
2184
2185        uLogger.debug("Opening [{}] market order: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], lots [{}], TP [{:.4f}], SL [{:.4f}], expiration date of TP/SL orders [{}]. Wait, please...".format(operation, self.ticker, self.figi, lots, tp, sl, expDate))
2186
2187        openTradeURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OrdersService/PostOrder"
2188        self.body = str({
2189            "figi": self.figi,
2190            "quantity": str(lots),
2191            "direction": "ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY" if operation == "Buy" else "ORDER_DIRECTION_SELL",  # see: TKS_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
2192            "accountId": str(self.accountId),
2193            "orderType": "ORDER_TYPE_MARKET",  # see: TKS_ORDER_TYPES
2194        })
2195        response = self.SendAPIRequest(openTradeURL, reqType="POST", retry=0, debug=False)
2196
2197        if "orderId" in response.keys():
2198            uLogger.info("[{}] market order [{}] was executed: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], lots [{}]. Total order price: [{:.4f} {}] (with commission: [{:.2f} {}]). Average price of lot: [{:.2f} {}]".format(
2199                operation, response["orderId"],
2200                self.ticker, self.figi, lots,
2201                NanoToFloat(response["totalOrderAmount"]["units"], response["totalOrderAmount"]["nano"]), response["totalOrderAmount"]["currency"],
2202                NanoToFloat(response["initialCommission"]["units"], response["initialCommission"]["nano"]), response["initialCommission"]["currency"],
2203                NanoToFloat(response["executedOrderPrice"]["units"], response["executedOrderPrice"]["nano"]), response["executedOrderPrice"]["currency"],
2204            ))
2205
2206        else:
2207            uLogger.warning("Not `oK` status received! Market order not created. See full debug log or try again and open order later.")
2208
2209        if tp > 0:
2210            self.Order(operation="Sell" if operation == "Buy" else "Buy", orderType="Stop", lots=lots, targetPrice=tp, limitPrice=tp, stopType="TP", expDate=expDate)
2211
2212        if sl > 0:
2213            self.Order(operation="Sell" if operation == "Buy" else "Buy", orderType="Stop", lots=lots, targetPrice=sl, limitPrice=sl, stopType="SL", expDate=expDate)
2214
2215        return response
2216
2217    def Buy(self, lots: int = 1, tp: float = 0., sl: float = 0., expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2218        """
2219        More simple method than `Trade()`. Create `Buy` market order and make deal at the current price. Returns JSON data with response.
2220        If `tp` or `sl` > 0, then in additional will opens stop-orders with "TP" and "SL" flags for `stopType` parameter.
2221
2222        See also: `Order()` and `Trade()` docstrings.
2223
2224        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2225        :param tp: float > 0, take profit price of stop-order.
2226        :param sl: float > 0, stop loss price of stop-order.
2227        :param expDate: it's a local date in future.
2228                        String has a format like this: `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2229        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2230        """
2231        return self.Trade(operation="Buy", lots=lots, tp=tp, sl=sl, expDate=expDate)
2232
2233    def Sell(self, lots: int = 1, tp: float = 0., sl: float = 0., expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2234        """
2235        More simple method than `Trade()`. Create `Sell` market order and make deal at the current price. Returns JSON data with response.
2236        If `tp` or `sl` > 0, then in additional will opens stop-orders with "TP" and "SL" flags for `stopType` parameter.
2237
2238        See also: `Order()` and `Trade()` docstrings.
2239
2240        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2241        :param tp: float > 0, take profit price of stop-order.
2242        :param sl: float > 0, stop loss price of stop-order.
2243        :param expDate: it's a local date in future.
2244                        String has a format like this: `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2245        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2246        """
2247        return self.Trade(operation="Sell", lots=lots, tp=tp, sl=sl, expDate=expDate)

2249    def CloseTrades(self, tickers: list, overview: dict = None) -> None:
2250        """
2251        Close position of given instruments.
2252
2253        :param tickers: tickers list of instruments that must be closed.
2254        :param overview: pre-received dictionary with open trades, returned by `Overview()` method.
2255                         This avoids unnecessary downloading data from the server.
2256        """
2257        if not tickers:
2258            uLogger.info("Tickers list empty, nothing to close.")
2259
2260        else:
2261            if overview is None or not overview:
2262                overview = self.Overview(showStatistics=False)
2263
2264            allOpenedTickers = [item["ticker"] for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS for item in overview["stat"][iType]]
2265            uLogger.debug("All opened instruments by it's tickers names: {}".format(allOpenedTickers))
2266
2267            for ticker in tickers:
2268                if not ticker in allOpenedTickers:
2269                    uLogger.warning("Instrument with ticker [{}] not in open positions list!".format(ticker))
2270                    continue
2271
2272                # search open trade info about instrument by ticker:
2273                instrument = {}
2274                for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
2275                    if instrument:
2276                        break
2277
2278                    for item in overview["stat"][iType]:
2279                        if item["ticker"] == ticker:
2280                            instrument = item
2281                            break
2282
2283                if instrument:
2284                    self.ticker = ticker
2285                    self.figi = instrument["figi"]
2286
2287                    uLogger.debug("Closing trade of instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI[{}], lots [{}]{}. Wait, please...".format(
2288                        self.ticker,
2289                        self.figi,
2290                        int(instrument["volume"]),
2291                        ", blocked [{}]".format(instrument["blocked"]) if instrument["blocked"] > 0 else "",
2292                    ))
2293
2294                    tradeLots = abs(instrument["lots"]) - instrument["blocked"]  # available volumes in lots for close operation
2295
2296                    if tradeLots > 0:
2297                        if instrument["blocked"] > 0:
2298                            uLogger.warning("Just for your information: there are [{}] lots blocked for instrument [{}]! Available only [{}] lots to closing trade.".format(
2299                                instrument["blocked"],
2300                                self.ticker,
2301                                tradeLots,
2302                            ))
2303
2304                        # if direction is "Long" then we need sell, if direction is "Short" then we need buy:
2305                        self.Trade(operation="Sell" if instrument["direction"] == "Long" else "Buy", lots=tradeLots)
2306
2307                    else:
2308                        uLogger.warning("There are no available lots for instrument [{}] to closing trade at this moment! Try again later or cancel some orders.".format(self.ticker))
2309
2310    def CloseAllTrades(self, iType: str, overview: dict = None) -> None:
2311        """
2312        Close all positions of given instruments with defined type.
2313
2314        :param iType: type of the instruments that be closed, it must be one of supported types in TKS_INSTRUMENTS list.
2315        :param overview: pre-received dictionary with open trades, returned by `Overview()` method.
2316                         This avoids unnecessary downloading data from the server.
2317        """
2318        if iType not in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
2319            uLogger.warning("Type of the instrument must be one of supported types: {}. Given: [{}]".format(", ".join(TKS_INSTRUMENTS), iType))
2320
2321        else:
2322            if overview is None or not overview:
2323                overview = self.Overview(showStatistics=False)
2324
2325            tickers = [item["ticker"] for item in overview["stat"][iType]]
2326            uLogger.debug("Instrument tickers with type [{}] that will be closed: {}".format(iType, tickers))
2327
2328            if tickers and overview:
2329                self.CloseTrades(tickers, overview)
2330
2331            else:
2332                uLogger.info("Instrument tickers with type [{}] not found, nothing to close.".format(iType))
2333
2334    def Order(self, operation: str, orderType: str, lots: int, targetPrice: float, limitPrice: float = 0., stopType: str = "Limit", expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2335        """
2336        Universal method to create market or limit orders with all available parameters.
2337        See more simple methods: `BuyLimit()`, `BuyStop()`, `SellLimit()`, `SellStop()`.
2338
2339        If orderType is "Limit" then create pending limit-order below current price if operation is "Buy" and above
2340        current price if operation is "Sell". A limit order has no expiration date, it lasts until the end of the trading day.
2341
2342        Warning! If you try to create limit-order above current price if "Buy" or below current price if "Sell"
2343        then broker immediately open market order as you can do simple --buy or --sell operations!
2344
2345        If orderType is "Stop" then creates stop-order with any direction "Buy" or "Sell".
2346        When current price will go up or down to target price value then broker opens a limit order.
2347        Stop-order is opened with unlimited expiration date by default, or you can define expiration date with expDate parameter.
2348
2349        Only one attempt and no retry for opens order. If network issue occurred you can create new request.
2350
2351        :param operation: string "Buy" or "Sell".
2352        :param orderType: string "Limit" or "Stop".
2353        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2354        :param targetPrice: target price > 0. This is open trade price for limit order.
2355        :param limitPrice: limit price >= 0. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order. If limitPrice = 0, then it set as targetPrice.
2356                           Broker will creates limit-order with price equal to limitPrice, when current price goes to target price of stop-order.
2357        :param stopType: string "Limit" by default. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order. There are 3 stop-order types
2358                         "SL", "TP", "Limit" for "Stop loss", "Take profit" and "Stop limit" types accordingly.
2359                         Stop loss order always executed by market price.
2360        :param expDate: string "Undefined" by default or local date in future.
2361                        String has a format like this: `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2362                        This date is converting to UTC format for server. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order.
2363                        A limit order has no expiration date, it lasts until the end of the trading day.
2364        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2365        """
2366        if operation is None or not operation or operation not in ("Buy", "Sell"):
2367            raise Exception("You must define operation type only one of them: `Buy` or `Sell`!")
2368
2369        if orderType is None or not orderType or orderType not in ("Limit", "Stop"):
2370            raise Exception("You must define order type only one of them: `Limit` or `Stop`!")
2371
2372        if lots is None or lots < 1:
2373            raise Exception("You must define trade volume > 0: integer count of lots!")
2374
2375        if targetPrice is None or targetPrice <= 0:
2376            raise Exception("Target price for limit-order must be greater than 0!")
2377
2378        if limitPrice is None or limitPrice <= 0:
2379            limitPrice = targetPrice
2380
2381        if stopType is None or not stopType or stopType not in ("SL", "TP", "Limit"):
2382            stopType = "Limit"
2383
2384        if expDate is None or not expDate:
2385            expDate = "Undefined"
2386
2387        if not (self.ticker or self.figi):
2388            raise Exception("`self.ticker` or `self.figi` variables must be defined!")
2389
2390        response = {}
2391        instrument = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=True, debug=False) if self.ticker else self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True, debug=False)
2392        self.ticker = instrument["ticker"]
2393        self.figi = instrument["figi"]
2394
2395        if orderType == "Limit":
2396            uLogger.debug(
2397                "Creating pending limit-order: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}] and the target price [{:.2f} {}]. Wait, please...".format(
2398                    self.ticker, self.figi,
2399                    operation, lots, targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2400                ))
2401
2402            openOrderURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OrdersService/PostOrder"
2403            self.body = str({
2404                "figi": self.figi,
2405                "quantity": str(lots),
2406                "price": FloatToNano(targetPrice),
2407                "direction": "ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY" if operation == "Buy" else "ORDER_DIRECTION_SELL",  # see: TKS_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
2408                "accountId": str(self.accountId),
2409                "orderType": "ORDER_TYPE_LIMIT",  # see: TKS_ORDER_TYPES
2410            })
2411            response = self.SendAPIRequest(openOrderURL, reqType="POST", retry=0, debug=False)
2412
2413            if "orderId" in response.keys():
2414                uLogger.info(
2415                    "Limit-order [{}] was created: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}], target price [{:.2f} {}]".format(
2416                        response["orderId"],
2417                        self.ticker, self.figi,
2418                        operation, lots, targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2419                    ))
2420
2421                if "lastPrice" in instrument["currentPrice"].keys() and instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2422                    if operation == "Buy" and targetPrice > instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2423                        uLogger.warning("Your order was executed as a market order, not as a limit order! Comment: because your target price [{:.2f} {}] was higher than current price [{:.2f} {}] broker immediately opened `Buy` market order, such as if you did simple `--buy` operation.".format(
2424                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2425                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2426                        ))
2427
2428                    if operation == "Sell" and targetPrice < instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2429                        uLogger.warning("Your order was executed as a market order, not as a limit order! Comment: because your target price [{:.2f} {}] was lower than current price [{:.2f} {}] broker immediately opened `Sell` market order, such as if you did simple `--sell` operation.".format(
2430                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2431                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2432                        ))
2433
2434            else:
2435                uLogger.warning("Not `oK` status received! Limit order not opened. See full debug log or try again and open order later.")
2436
2437        if orderType == "Stop":
2438            uLogger.debug(
2439                "Creating stop-order: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}], target price [{:.2f} {}], limit price [{:.2f} {}], stop-order type [{}] and local expiration date [{}]. Wait, please...".format(
2440                    self.ticker, self.figi,
2441                    operation, lots,
2442                    targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2443                    limitPrice, instrument["currency"],
2444                    stopType, expDate,
2445                ))
2446
2447            openOrderURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.StopOrdersService/PostStopOrder"
2448            expDateUTC = "" if expDate == "Undefined" else datetime.strptime(expDate, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S").replace(tzinfo=tzlocal()).astimezone(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%fZ")
2449            stopOrderType = "STOP_ORDER_TYPE_STOP_LOSS" if stopType == "SL" else "STOP_ORDER_TYPE_TAKE_PROFIT" if stopType == "TP" else "STOP_ORDER_TYPE_STOP_LIMIT"
2450
2451            body = {
2452                "figi": self.figi,
2453                "quantity": str(lots),
2454                "price": FloatToNano(limitPrice),
2455                "stopPrice": FloatToNano(targetPrice),
2456                "direction": "STOP_ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY" if operation == "Buy" else "STOP_ORDER_DIRECTION_SELL",  # see: TKS_STOP_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
2457                "accountId": str(self.accountId),
2458                "expirationType": "STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_GOOD_TILL_DATE" if expDateUTC else "STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_GOOD_TILL_CANCEL",  # see: TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES
2459                "stopOrderType": stopOrderType,  # see: TKS_STOP_ORDER_TYPES
2460            }
2461
2462            if expDateUTC:
2463                body["expireDate"] = expDateUTC
2464
2465            self.body = str(body)
2466            response = self.SendAPIRequest(openOrderURL, reqType="POST", retry=0, debug=False)
2467
2468            if "stopOrderId" in response.keys():
2469                uLogger.info(
2470                    "Stop-order [{}] was created: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}], target price [{:.2f} {}], limit price [{:.2f} {}], stop-order type [{}] and expiration date in UTC [{}]".format(
2471                    response["stopOrderId"],
2472                    self.ticker, self.figi,
2473                    operation, lots,
2474                    targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2475                    limitPrice, instrument["currency"],
2476                    TKS_STOP_ORDER_TYPES[stopOrderType],
2477                    datetime.strptime(expDateUTC, "%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%fZ").replace(tzinfo=tzutc()).astimezone(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S") if expDateUTC else TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES["STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED"],
2478                ))
2479
2480                if "lastPrice" in instrument["currentPrice"].keys() and instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2481                    if operation == "Buy" and targetPrice < instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] and stopType != "TP":
2482                        uLogger.warning("The broker will cancel this order after some time. Comment: you placed the wrong stop order because the target buy price [{:.2f} {}] is lower than the current price [{:.2f} {}]. Also try to set up order type as `TP` if you want to place stop order at that price.".format(
2483                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2484                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2485                        ))
2486
2487                    if operation == "Sell" and targetPrice > instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] and stopType != "TP":
2488                        uLogger.warning("The broker will cancel this order after some time. Comment: you placed the wrong stop order because the target sell price [{:.2f} {}] is higher than the current price [{:.2f} {}]. Also try to set up order type as `TP` if you want to place stop order at that price.".format(
2489                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2490                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2491                        ))
2492
2493            else:
2494                uLogger.warning("Not `oK` status received! Stop order not opened. See full debug log or try again and open order later.")
2495
2496        return response

2498    def BuyLimit(self, lots: int, targetPrice: float) -> dict:
2499        """
2500        Create pending `Buy` limit-order (below current price). You must specify only 2 parameters:
2501        `lots` and `target price` to open buy limit-order. If you try to create buy limit-order above current price then
2502        broker immediately open `Buy` market order, such as if you do simple `--buy` operation!
2503        See also: `Order()` docstring.
2504
2505        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2506        :param targetPrice: target price > 0. This is open trade price for limit order.
2507        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2508        """
2509        return self.Order(operation="Buy", orderType="Limit", lots=lots, targetPrice=targetPrice)
2510
2511    def BuyStop(self, lots: int, targetPrice: float, limitPrice: float = 0., stopType: str = "Limit", expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2512        """
2513        Create `Buy` stop-order. You must specify at least 2 parameters: `lots` `target price` to open buy stop-order.
2514        In additional you can specify 3 parameters for buy stop-order: `limit price` >=0, `stop type` = Limit|SL|TP,
2515        `expiration date` = Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`. When current price will go up or down to
2516        target price value then broker opens a limit order. See also: `Order()` docstring.
2517
2518        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2519        :param targetPrice: target price > 0. This is trigger price for buy stop-order.
2520        :param limitPrice: limit price >= 0 (limitPrice = targetPrice if limitPrice is 0). Broker will creates limit-order
2521                           with price equal to limitPrice, when current price goes to target price of buy stop-order.
2522        :param stopType: string "Limit" by default. There are 3 stop-order types "SL", "TP", "Limit"
2523                         for "Stop loss", "Take profit" and "Stop limit" types accordingly.
2524        :param expDate: string "Undefined" by default or local date in future.
2525                        String has a format like this: `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2526                        This date is converting to UTC format for server.
2527        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2528        """
2529        return self.Order(operation="Buy", orderType="Stop", lots=lots, targetPrice=targetPrice, limitPrice=limitPrice, stopType=stopType, expDate=expDate)

2564    def CloseOrders(self, orderIDs: list, allOrdersIDs: list = None, allStopOrdersIDs: list = None) -> None:
2565        """
2566        Cancel order or list of orders by its `orderId` or `stopOrderId`.
2567
2568        :param orderIDs: list of integers with `orderId` or `stopOrderId`.
2569        :param allOrdersIDs: pre-received lists of all active pending orders.
2570                             This avoids unnecessary downloading data from the server.
2571        :param allStopOrdersIDs: pre-received lists of all active stop orders.
2572        """
2573        if orderIDs:
2574            if allOrdersIDs is None or not allOrdersIDs:
2575                rawOrders = self.RequestPendingOrders()
2576                allOrdersIDs = [item["orderId"] for item in rawOrders]  # all pending orders ID
2577
2578            if allStopOrdersIDs is None or not allStopOrdersIDs:
2579                rawStopOrders = self.RequestStopOrders()
2580                allStopOrdersIDs = [item["stopOrderId"] for item in rawStopOrders]  # all stop orders ID
2581
2582            for orderID in orderIDs:
2583                idInPendingOrders = orderID in allOrdersIDs
2584                idInStopOrders = orderID in allStopOrdersIDs
2585
2586                if not (idInPendingOrders or idInStopOrders):
2587                    uLogger.warning("Order not found by ID: [{}]. Maybe cancelled already? Check it with `--overview` key.".format(orderID))
2588                    continue
2589
2590                else:
2591                    if idInPendingOrders:
2592                        uLogger.debug("Cancelling pending order with ID: [{}]. Wait, please...".format(orderID))
2593
2594                        # REST API for request: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/OrdersService/OrdersService_CancelOrder
2595                        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId, "orderId": orderID})
2596                        closeURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OrdersService/CancelOrder"
2597                        responseJSON = self.SendAPIRequest(closeURL, reqType="POST")
2598
2599                        if responseJSON and "time" in responseJSON.keys() and responseJSON["time"]:
2600                            uLogger.debug("Success time marker received from server: [{}] (UTC)".format(responseJSON["time"]))
2601                            uLogger.info("Pending order with ID [{}] successfully cancel".format(orderID))
2602
2603                        else:
2604                            uLogger.warning("Unknown issue occurred when cancelling pending order with ID: [{}]. Check ID and try again.".format(orderID))
2605
2606                    elif idInStopOrders:
2607                        uLogger.debug("Cancelling stop order with ID: [{}]. Wait, please...".format(orderID))
2608
2609                        # REST API for request: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/StopOrdersService/StopOrdersService_CancelStopOrder
2610                        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId, "stopOrderId": orderID})
2611                        closeURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.StopOrdersService/CancelStopOrder"
2612                        responseJSON = self.SendAPIRequest(closeURL, reqType="POST")
2613
2614                        if responseJSON and "time" in responseJSON.keys() and responseJSON["time"]:
2615                            uLogger.debug("Success time marker received from server: [{}] (UTC)".format(responseJSON["time"]))
2616                            uLogger.info("Stop order with ID [{}] successfully cancel".format(orderID))
2617
2618                        else:
2619                            uLogger.warning("Unknown issue occurred when cancelling stop order with ID: [{}]. Check ID and try again.".format(orderID))
2620
2621                    else:
2622                        continue
2623
2624    def CloseAllOrders(self) -> None:
2625        """
2626        Gets a list of open pending and stop orders and cancel it all.
2627        """
2628        rawOrders = self.RequestPendingOrders()
2629        allOrdersIDs = [item["orderId"] for item in rawOrders]  # all pending orders ID
2630        lenOrders = len(allOrdersIDs)
2631
2632        rawStopOrders = self.RequestStopOrders()
2633        allStopOrdersIDs = [item["stopOrderId"] for item in rawStopOrders]  # all stop orders ID
2634        lenSOrders = len(allStopOrdersIDs)
2635
2636        if lenOrders > 0 or lenSOrders > 0:
2637            uLogger.info("Found: [{}] opened pending and [{}] stop orders. Let's trying to cancel it all. Wait, please...".format(lenOrders, lenSOrders))
2638
2639            self.CloseOrders(allOrdersIDs + allStopOrdersIDs, allOrdersIDs, allStopOrdersIDs)
2640
2641        else:
2642            uLogger.info("Orders not found, nothing to cancel.")
2643
2644    def CloseAll(self, *args) -> None:
2645        """
2646        Close all available (not blocked) opened trades and orders.
2647
2648        Also you can select one or more keywords case insensitive:
2649        `orders`, `shares`, `bonds`, `etfs` and `futures` from `TKS_INSTRUMENTS` enum to specify trades type.
2650
2651        Currency positions you must closes manually using buy or sell operations, `CloseTrades()` or `CloseAllTrades()` methods.
2652        """
2653        overview = self.Overview(showStatistics=False)  # get all open trades info
2654
2655        if len(args) == 0:
2656            uLogger.debug("Closing all available (not blocked) opened trades and orders. Currency positions you must closes manually using buy or sell operations! Wait, please...")
2657            self.CloseAllOrders()  # close all pending and stop orders
2658
2659            for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
2660                if iType != "Currencies":
2661                    self.CloseAllTrades(iType, overview)  # close all positions of instruments with same type without currencies
2662
2663        else:
2664            uLogger.debug("Closing all available {}. Currency positions you must closes manually using buy or sell operations! Wait, please...".format(list(args)))
2665            lowerArgs = [x.lower() for x in args]
2666
2667            if "orders" in lowerArgs:
2668                self.CloseAllOrders()  # close all pending and stop orders
2669
2670            for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
2671                if iType.lower() in lowerArgs and iType != "Currencies":
2672                    self.CloseAllTrades(iType, overview)  # close all positions of instruments with same type without currencies
2673

2685        :return: list of dictionaries with all lots and prices to open orders that looks like this `[{"lot": lots_1, "price": price_1}, {...}, ...]`
2686        """

This class implements methods to work with Tinkoff broker server.

Examples to work with API: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/

Where is token: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/token/

TinkoffBrokerServer(token: str, iList: dict = None, accountId: str = None) 
187    def __init__(self, token: str, iList: dict = None, accountId: str = None) -> None:
188        """
189        Main class init.
190
191        :param token: Bearer token for Tinkoff Invest API. It can be set from environment variable `TKS_API_TOKEN`.
192        :param iList: dictionary of dictionaries with instrument's data.
193        :param accountId: string with user's numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker. It can be found in broker's reports.
194                          Also, this variable can be set from environment variable `TKS_ACCOUNT_ID`.
195        """
196        if token is None or not token:
197            try:
198                self.token = r"{}".format(os.environ["TKS_API_TOKEN"])
199                uLogger.debug("Bearer token for Tinkoff OpenApi set up from environment variable `TKS_API_TOKEN`. See https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/token/")
200
201            except KeyError:
202                raise Exception("`--token` key or environment variable `TKS_API_TOKEN` is required! See https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/token/")
203
204        else:
205            self.token = token  # highly priority than environment variable 'TKS_API_TOKEN'
206            uLogger.debug("Bearer token for Tinkoff OpenApi set up from class variable `token`")
207
208        if accountId is None or not accountId:
209            try:
210                self.accountId = r"{}".format(os.environ["TKS_ACCOUNT_ID"])
211                uLogger.debug("String with user's numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker set up from environment variable `TKS_ACCOUNT_ID`")
212
213            except KeyError:
214                uLogger.warning("`--account-id` key or environment variable `TKS_ACCOUNT_ID` undefined! Some of operations may be unavailable (overview, trading etc).")
215
216        else:
217            self.accountId = accountId  # highly priority than environment variable 'TKS_ACCOUNT_ID'
218            uLogger.debug("String with user's numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker set up from class variable `accountId`")
219
220        self.aliases = TKS_TICKER_ALIASES
221        """Some aliases instead official tickers. See `TKSEnums.TKS_TICKER_ALIASES`"""
222
223        self.aliasesKeys = self.aliases.keys()  # re-calc only first time at class init
224        self.exclude = TKS_TICKERS_OR_FIGI_EXCLUDED  # some of tickets or FIGIs raised exception earlier when it sends to server, that is why we exclude there
225
226        self.ticker = ""
227        """String with ticker, e.g. `GOOGL`. Use alias for `USD000UTSTOM` simple as `USD`, `EUR_RUB__TOM` as `EUR` etc. More tickers aliases here: `TKSEnums.TKS_TICKER_ALIASES`."""
228
229        self.figi = ""
230        """String with FIGI, e.g. ticker `GOOGL` has FIGI `BBG009S39JX6`"""
231
232        self.depth = 1
233        """Depth of Market (DOM) can be >= 1. Default: 1. It used with `--price` key to showing DOM with current prices for givens ticker or FIGI."""
234
235        self.server = r"https://invest-public-api.tinkoff.ru/rest"
236        """Tinkoff REST API server for real trade operations. Default: https://invest-public-api.tinkoff.ru/rest
237
238        See: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/#tinkoff-invest-api_1
239        """
240
241        uLogger.debug("Broker API server: {}".format(self.server))
242
243        self.timeout = 15
244        """Server operations timeout in seconds. Default: 15"""
245
246        self.headers = {"Content-Type": "application/json", "accept": "application/json", "Authorization": "Bearer {}".format(self.token)}
247        """Headers which send in every request to broker server. Default: `{"Content-Type": "application/json", "accept": "application/json", "Authorization": "Bearer {token}"}`"""
248
249        self.body = None
250        """Request body which send to broker server. Default: `None`"""
251
252        self.historyLength = 24
253        """How many candles returns if candles history request. For example, if `historyInterval="hour"` and `historyLength=24` it means: "give me last 24 hours". Must be >=1. Default: 24"""
254
255        self.historyInterval = "hour"
256        """Interval string for Tinkoff API (see: `TKSEnums.TKS_TIMEFRAMES`). Available values are `"1min"`, `"2min"`, `"3min"`, `"5min"`, `"10min"`, `"15min"`, `"30min"`, `"hour"`, `"day"`, `"week"`, `"month"`. Default: `"hour"`"""
257
258        self.iList = iList if iList is not None else self.Listing()
259        """Dictionary with raw data about stocks, currencies, bonds, etfs and futures from broker server.
260        At first time, when class init, `Listing()` method auto-update this variable.
261        For future use, you can save this variable and substitute it in the `iList` to avoid permanent downloads from the server.
262        """
263
264        self.pricesList = {}  # You can request all current prices with `ShowAllPrices()` method. WARNING! This is too long operation!
265
266        self.instrumentsFile = "instruments.md"
267        """Filename where full broker's instruments list will be saved. Default: `"instruments.md"`"""
268
269        self.pricesFile = "prices.md"
270        """Filename where prices of selected instruments will be saved. Default: `"prices.md"`"""
271
272        self.overviewFile = "overview.md"
273        """Filename where current portfolio, open trades and orders will be saved. Default: `"overview.md"`"""
274
275        self.reportFile = "report.md"
276        """Filename where history of deals and trade statistics will be saved. Default: `"report.md"`"""
277
278        self.historyFile = None
279        """Full path to .csv output file where history candles will be saved. Default: `None`, mean that returns only pandas dataframe."""

Main class init.

Parameters
  • token: Bearer token for Tinkoff Invest API. It can be set from environment variable TKS_API_TOKEN.
  • iList: dictionary of dictionaries with instrument's data.
  • accountId: string with user's numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker. It can be found in broker's reports. Also, this variable can be set from environment variable TKS_ACCOUNT_ID.
aliases

Some aliases instead official tickers. See TKSEnums.TKS_TICKER_ALIASES

ticker

String with ticker, e.g. GOOGL. Use alias for USD000UTSTOM simple as USD, EUR_RUB__TOM as EUR etc. More tickers aliases here: TKSEnums.TKS_TICKER_ALIASES.

figi

String with FIGI, e.g. ticker GOOGL has FIGI BBG009S39JX6

depth

Depth of Market (DOM) can be >= 1. Default: 1. It used with --price key to showing DOM with current prices for givens ticker or FIGI.

server

Tinkoff REST API server for real trade operations. Default: https://invest-public-api.tinkoff.ru/rest

See: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/#tinkoff-invest-api_1

timeout

Server operations timeout in seconds. Default: 15

headers

Headers which send in every request to broker server. Default: {"Content-Type": "application/json", "accept": "application/json", "Authorization": "Bearer {token}"}

body

Request body which send to broker server. Default: None

historyLength

How many candles returns if candles history request. For example, if historyInterval="hour" and historyLength=24 it means: "give me last 24 hours". Must be >=1. Default: 24

historyInterval

Interval string for Tinkoff API (see: TKSEnums.TKS_TIMEFRAMES). Available values are "1min", "2min", "3min", "5min", "10min", "15min", "30min", "hour", "day", "week", "month". Default: "hour"

iList

Dictionary with raw data about stocks, currencies, bonds, etfs and futures from broker server. At first time, when class init, Listing() method auto-update this variable. For future use, you can save this variable and substitute it in the iList to avoid permanent downloads from the server.

instrumentsFile

Filename where full broker's instruments list will be saved. Default: "instruments.md"

pricesFile

Filename where prices of selected instruments will be saved. Default: "prices.md"

overviewFile

Filename where current portfolio, open trades and orders will be saved. Default: "overview.md"

reportFile

Filename where history of deals and trade statistics will be saved. Default: "report.md"

historyFile

Full path to .csv output file where history candles will be saved. Default: None, mean that returns only pandas dataframe.

def SendAPIRequest( self, url: str, reqType: str = 'GET', retry: int = 3, pause: int = 5, debug: bool = False) -> dict: 
303    def SendAPIRequest(self, url: str, reqType: str = "GET", retry: int = 3, pause: int = 5, debug: bool = False) -> dict:
304        """
305        Send GET or POST request to broker server and receive JSON object.
306
307        self.header: must be define with dictionary of headers.
308        self.body: if define then used as request body. None by default.
309        self.timeout: global request timeout, 15 seconds by default.
310        :param url: url with REST request.
311        :param reqType: send "GET" or "POST" request. "GET" by default.
312        :param retry: how many times retry after first request if an error occurred.
313        :param pause: sleep time in seconds between retries.
314        :param debug: if `True` then print more debug information.
315        :return: response JSON (dictionary) from broker.
316        """
317        if reqType not in ("GET", "POST"):
318            raise Exception("You can define request type: 'GET' or 'POST'!")
319
320        if debug:
321            uLogger.debug("Request parameters:")
322            uLogger.debug("    - REST API URL: {}".format(url))
323            uLogger.debug("    - request type: {}".format(reqType))
324            uLogger.debug("    - headers: {}".format(str(self.headers).replace(self.token, "*** request token ***")))
325            uLogger.debug("    - body: {}".format(self.body))
326
327        # fast hack to avoid all operations with some tickers/FIGI
328        responseJSON = {}
329        oK = True
330        for item in self.exclude:
331            if item in url:
332                if debug:
333                    uLogger.warning("Do not execute operations with list of this tickers/FIGI: {}".format(str(self.exclude)))
334
335                oK = False
336                break
337
338        if oK:
339            counter = 0
340            response = None
341            errMsg = ""
342
343            while not response and counter <= retry:
344                if reqType == "GET":
345                    response = requests.get(url, headers=self.headers, data=self.body, timeout=self.timeout)
346
347                if reqType == "POST":
348                    response = requests.post(url, headers=self.headers, data=self.body, timeout=self.timeout)
349
350                if debug:
351                    uLogger.debug("Response:")
352                    uLogger.debug("    - status code: {}".format(response.status_code))
353                    uLogger.debug("    - reason: {}".format(response.reason))
354                    uLogger.debug("    - body length: {}".format(len(response.text)))
355
356                # Error status codes: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_HTTP_status_codes
357                if 400 <= response.status_code < 600:
358                    errMsg = "[{}] {}".format(response.status_code, response.text)
359                    uLogger.debug("    - not oK status code received: {}".format(errMsg))
360                    counter += 1
361
362                    if counter <= retry:
363                        uLogger.debug("Retry: [{}]. Wait until {} sec. and try again...".format(counter, pause))
364                        sleep(pause)
365
366            responseJSON = self._ParseJSON(response.text)
367
368            if errMsg:
369                uLogger.error("Not `oK` status received from broker server!")
370                uLogger.error("    - message: {}".format(errMsg))
371                # raise Exception("Server returned an error! See full debug log. Also you can set debug=True in SendAPIRequest() and _ParseJSON() methods.")
372
373        return responseJSON

Send GET or POST request to broker server and receive JSON object.

self.header: must be define with dictionary of headers. self.body: if define then used as request body. None by default. self.timeout: global request timeout, 15 seconds by default.

Parameters
  • url: url with REST request.
  • reqType: send "GET" or "POST" request. "GET" by default.
  • retry: how many times retry after first request if an error occurred.
  • pause: sleep time in seconds between retries.
  • debug: if True then print more debug information.
Returns

response JSON (dictionary) from broker.

def Listing(self) -> dict: 
406    def Listing(self) -> dict:
407        """
408        Gets JSON with raw data about stocks, currencies, bonds, etfs and futures from broker server.
409
410        :return: Dictionary with all available broker instruments: currencies, stocks, bonds, etfs and futures.
411        """
412        uLogger.debug("Requesting all available instruments from broker for current user token. Wait, please...")
413        uLogger.debug("CPU usages for parallel requests: [{}]".format(CPU_USAGES))
414
415        # this parameters insert to requests: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/InstrumentsService
416        # iType is type of instrument, it must be one of supported types in TKS_INSTRUMENTS list.
417        iParams = [{"iType": iType} for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS]
418
419        poolUpdater = ThreadPool(processes=CPU_USAGES)  # create pool for update instruments in parallel mode
420        listing = poolUpdater.map(self._IWrapper, iParams)  # execute update operations
421        poolUpdater.close()
422
423        # Dictionary with all broker instruments: stocks, currencies, bonds, etfs and futures.
424        # Next in this code: item[0] is "iType" and item[1] is list of available instruments from the result of _IUpdater() method
425        iList = {item[0]: {instrument["ticker"]: instrument for instrument in item[1]} for item in listing}
426
427        # calculate minimum price increment (step) for all instruments and set up instrument's type:
428        for iType in iList.keys():
429            for ticker in iList[iType]:
430                iList[iType][ticker]["type"] = iType
431
432                if "minPriceIncrement" in iList[iType][ticker].keys():
433                    iList[iType][ticker]["step"] = NanoToFloat(
434                        iList[iType][ticker]["minPriceIncrement"]["units"],
435                        iList[iType][ticker]["minPriceIncrement"]["nano"],
436                    )
437
438                else:
439                    iList[iType][ticker]["step"] = 0  # hack to avoid empty value in some instruments, e.g. futures
440
441        return iList

Gets JSON with raw data about stocks, currencies, bonds, etfs and futures from broker server.

Returns

Dictionary with all available broker instruments: currencies, stocks, bonds, etfs and futures.

445        """

468            ))

def SearchByTicker( self, requestPrice: bool = False, showInfo: bool = False, debug: bool = False) -> dict: 
615    def SearchByTicker(self, requestPrice: bool = False, showInfo: bool = False, debug: bool = False) -> dict:
616        """
617        Search and return raw broker's information about instrument by it's ticker.
618        `ticker` must be define! If debug=True then print all debug messages.
619
620        :param requestPrice: if `False` then do not request current price of instrument (because this is long operation).
621        :param showInfo: if `False` then do not run `ShowInstrumentInfo()` method and do not print info to the console.
622        :param debug: if `True` then print all debug console messages.
623        :return: JSON formatted data with information about instrument.
624        """
625        tickerJSON = {}
626        if debug:
627            uLogger.debug("Searching information about instrument by it's ticker [{}] ...".format(self.ticker))
628
629        if not self.ticker:
630            uLogger.warning("self.ticker variable is not be empty!")
631
632        else:
633            if not self.iList:
634                self.iList = self.Listing()
635
636            if self.ticker in self.iList["Shares"].keys():
637                tickerJSON = self.iList["Shares"][self.ticker]
638                if debug:
639                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in stocks list".format(self.ticker))
640
641            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Currencies"].keys():
642                tickerJSON = self.iList["Currencies"][self.ticker]
643                if debug:
644                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in currencies list".format(self.ticker))
645
646            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Bonds"].keys():
647                tickerJSON = self.iList["Bonds"][self.ticker]
648                if debug:
649                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in bonds list".format(self.ticker))
650
651            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Etfs"].keys():
652                tickerJSON = self.iList["Etfs"][self.ticker]
653                if debug:
654                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in etfs list".format(self.ticker))
655
656            elif self.ticker in self.iList["Futures"].keys():
657                tickerJSON = self.iList["Futures"][self.ticker]
658                if debug:
659                    uLogger.debug("Ticker [{}] found in futures list".format(self.ticker))
660
661        if tickerJSON:
662            self.figi = tickerJSON["figi"]
663
664            if requestPrice:
665                tickerJSON["currentPrice"] = self.GetCurrentPrices(showPrice=False)
666
667                if tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] is not None and tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] != 0 and tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] is not None:
668                    tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 100 * (tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] - tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]) / tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]
669
670                else:
671                    tickerJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 0
672
673            if showInfo:
674                self.ShowInstrumentInfo(iJSON=tickerJSON, printInfo=True)  # print info as Markdown text
675
676        else:
677            if showInfo:
678                uLogger.warning("Ticker [{}] not found in available broker instrument's list!".format(self.ticker))
679
680        return tickerJSON

Search and return raw broker's information about instrument by it's ticker. ticker must be define! If debug=True then print all debug messages.

Parameters
  • requestPrice: if False then do not request current price of instrument (because this is long operation).
  • showInfo: if False then do not run ShowInstrumentInfo() method and do not print info to the console.
  • debug: if True then print all debug console messages.
Returns

JSON formatted data with information about instrument.

def SearchByFIGI( self, requestPrice: bool = False, showInfo: bool = False, debug: bool = False) -> dict: 
682    def SearchByFIGI(self, requestPrice: bool = False, showInfo: bool = False, debug: bool = False) -> dict:
683        """
684        Search and return raw broker's information about instrument by it's FIGI.
685        `figi` must be define! If debug=True then print all debug messages.
686
687        :param requestPrice: if `False` then do not request current price of instrument (it's long operation).
688        :param showInfo: if `False` then do not run `ShowInstrumentInfo()` method and do not print info to the console.
689        :param debug: if `True` then print all debug console messages.
690        :return: JSON formatted data with information about instrument.
691        """
692        figiJSON = {}
693        if debug:
694            uLogger.debug("Searching information about instrument by it's FIGI [{}] ...".format(self.figi))
695
696        if not self.figi:
697            uLogger.warning("self.figi variable is not be empty!")
698
699        else:
700            if not self.iList:
701                self.iList = self.Listing()
702
703            for item in self.iList["Shares"].keys():
704                if self.figi == self.iList["Shares"][item]["figi"]:
705                    figiJSON = self.iList["Shares"][item]
706
707                    if debug:
708                        uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in stocks list".format(self.figi))
709
710                    break
711
712            if not figiJSON:
713                for item in self.iList["Currencies"].keys():
714                    if self.figi == self.iList["Currencies"][item]["figi"]:
715                        figiJSON = self.iList["Currencies"][item]
716
717                        if debug:
718                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in currencies list".format(self.figi))
719
720                        break
721
722            if not figiJSON:
723                for item in self.iList["Bonds"].keys():
724                    if self.figi == self.iList["Bonds"][item]["figi"]:
725                        figiJSON = self.iList["Bonds"][item]
726
727                        if debug:
728                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in bonds list".format(self.figi))
729
730                        break
731
732            if not figiJSON:
733                for item in self.iList["Etfs"].keys():
734                    if self.figi == self.iList["Etfs"][item]["figi"]:
735                        figiJSON = self.iList["Etfs"][item]
736
737                        if debug:
738                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in etfs list".format(self.figi))
739
740                        break
741
742            if not figiJSON:
743                for item in self.iList["Futures"].keys():
744                    if self.figi == self.iList["Futures"][item]["figi"]:
745                        figiJSON = self.iList["Futures"][item]
746
747                        if debug:
748                            uLogger.debug("FIGI [{}] found in futures list".format(self.figi))
749
750                        break
751
752        if figiJSON:
753            self.figi = figiJSON["figi"]
754            self.ticker = figiJSON["ticker"]
755
756            if requestPrice:
757                figiJSON["currentPrice"] = self.GetCurrentPrices(showPrice=False)
758
759                if figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] is not None and figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"] != 0 and figiJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] is not None:
760                    figiJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 100 * (figiJSON["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] - figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]) / figiJSON["currentPrice"]["closePrice"]
761
762                else:
763                    figiJSON["currentPrice"]["changes"] = 0
764
765            if showInfo:
766                self.ShowInstrumentInfo(iJSON=figiJSON, printInfo=True)  # print info as Markdown text
767
768        else:
769            if showInfo:
770                uLogger.warning("FIGI [{}] not found in available broker instrument's list!".format(self.figi))
771
772        return figiJSON

Search and return raw broker's information about instrument by it's FIGI. figi must be define! If debug=True then print all debug messages.

Parameters
  • requestPrice: if False then do not request current price of instrument (it's long operation).
  • showInfo: if False then do not run ShowInstrumentInfo() method and do not print info to the console.
  • debug: if True then print all debug console messages.
Returns

JSON formatted data with information about instrument.

def GetCurrentPrices(self, showPrice: bool = False) -> dict: 
774    def GetCurrentPrices(self, showPrice: bool = False) -> dict:
775        """
776        Get and show Depth of Market with current prices of the instrument. If an error occurred then returns an empty record:
777        `{"buy": [], "sell": [], "limitUp": None, "limitDown": None, "lastPrice": None, "closePrice": None}`.
778
779        :param showPrice: if `True` then print DOM.
780        :return: dict with Depth of Market (DOM): `{"buy": [{"price": x1, "quantity": y1, ...}], "sell": [....]}` with list of current prices.
781        """
782        prices = {"buy": [], "sell": [], "limitUp": 0, "limitDown": 0, "lastPrice": 0, "closePrice": 0}
783
784        if self.depth < 1:
785            raise Exception("Depth of Market (DOM) must be >=1!")
786
787        if not (self.ticker or self.figi):
788            raise Exception("self.ticker or self.figi variables must be defined!")
789
790        if self.ticker and not self.figi:
791            instrumentByTicker = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=False)  # WARNING! requestPrice=False to avoid recursion!
792            self.figi = instrumentByTicker["figi"] if instrumentByTicker else ""
793
794        if not self.ticker and self.figi:
795            instrumentByFigi = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=False)  # WARNING! requestPrice=False to avoid recursion!
796            self.ticker = instrumentByFigi["ticker"] if instrumentByFigi else ""
797
798        if self.figi:
799            uLogger.debug("Requesting current prices for instrument with ticker [{}] and FIGI [{}]...".format(self.ticker, self.figi))
800
801            # REST API for request: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/MarketDataService/MarketDataService_GetOrderBook
802            priceURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.MarketDataService/GetOrderBook"
803            self.body = str({"figi": self.figi, "depth": self.depth})
804            pricesResponse = self.SendAPIRequest(priceURL, reqType="POST")
805
806            if pricesResponse:
807                # list of dicts with sellers orders:
808                prices["buy"] = [{"price": NanoToFloat(item["price"]["units"], item["price"]["nano"]), "quantity": int(item["quantity"])} for item in pricesResponse["asks"]]
809
810                # list of dicts with buyers orders:
811                prices["sell"] = [{"price": NanoToFloat(item["price"]["units"], item["price"]["nano"]), "quantity": int(item["quantity"])} for item in pricesResponse["bids"]]
812
813                # max price of instrument at this time:
814                prices["limitUp"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["limitUp"]["units"], pricesResponse["limitUp"]["nano"]) if "limitUp" in pricesResponse.keys() else None
815
816                # min price of instrument at this time:
817                prices["limitDown"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["limitDown"]["units"], pricesResponse["limitDown"]["nano"]) if "limitDown" in pricesResponse.keys() else None
818
819                # last price of deal with instrument:
820                prices["lastPrice"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["lastPrice"]["units"], pricesResponse["lastPrice"]["nano"]) if "lastPrice" in pricesResponse.keys() else 0
821
822                # last close price of instrument:
823                prices["closePrice"] = NanoToFloat(pricesResponse["closePrice"]["units"], pricesResponse["closePrice"]["nano"]) if "closePrice" in pricesResponse.keys() else 0
824
825            else:
826                uLogger.warning("Server return an empty or error response! See full log. Instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}]".format(self.ticker, self.figi))
827                uLogger.debug("Server response: {}".format(pricesResponse))
828
829            if showPrice:
830                if prices["buy"] or prices["sell"]:
831                    info = [
832                        "Orders book actual at [{}] (UTC)\nTicker: [{}], FIGI: [{}], Depth of Market: [{}]\n".format(
833                            datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"),
834                            self.ticker,
835                            self.figi,
836                            self.depth,
837                        ),
838                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
839                        " Orders of Buyers   | Orders of Sellers\n",
840                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
841                        " Sell prices (vol.) | Buy prices (vol.)\n",
842                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
843                    ]
844
845                    if not prices["buy"]:
846                        info.append("                    | No orders!\n")
847                        sumBuy = 0
848
849                    else:
850                        sumBuy = sum([x["quantity"] for x in prices["buy"]])
851                        maxMinSorted = sorted(prices["buy"], key=lambda k: k["price"], reverse=True)
852                        for item in maxMinSorted:
853                            info.append("                    | {} ({})\n".format(item["price"], item["quantity"]))
854
855                    if not prices["sell"]:
856                        info.append("No orders!          |\n")
857                        sumSell = 0
858
859                    else:
860                        sumSell = sum([x["quantity"] for x in prices["sell"]])
861                        for item in prices["sell"]:
862                            info.append("{:>19} |\n".format("{} ({})".format(item["price"], item["quantity"])))
863
864                    info.extend([
865                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
866                        "{:>19} | {}\n".format("Total sell: {}".format(sumSell), "Total buy: {}".format(sumBuy)),
867                        uLog.sepShort, "\n",
868                    ])
869
870                    infoText = "".join(info)
871
872                    uLogger.info("Current prices in order book:\n\n{}".format(infoText))
873
874                else:
875                    uLogger.warning("Orders book is empty at this time! Instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}]".format(self.ticker, self.figi))
876
877        else:
878            uLogger.error("FIGI is not defined!")
879
880        return prices

Get and show Depth of Market with current prices of the instrument. If an error occurred then returns an empty record: {"buy": [], "sell": [], "limitUp": None, "limitDown": None, "lastPrice": None, "closePrice": None}.

Parameters
  • showPrice: if True then print DOM.
Returns

dict with Depth of Market (DOM): {"buy": [{"price": x1, "quantity": y1, ...}], "sell": [....]} with list of current prices.

def ShowInstrumentsInfo(self, showInstruments: bool = False) -> str: 
882    def ShowInstrumentsInfo(self, showInstruments: bool = False) -> str:
883        """
884        This method get and show information about all available broker instruments.
885        If `instrumentsFile` string is not empty then also save information to this file.
886
887        :param showInstruments: if `True` then print to console, if `False` - print only to file.
888        :return: multi-string with all available broker instruments
889        """
890        if not self.iList:
891            self.iList = self.Listing()
892
893        info = [
894            "# All available instruments from Tinkoff Broker server for current user token\n\n",
895            "* **Actual on date:** [{}] (UTC)\n".format(datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")),
896        ]
897
898        # add instruments count by type:
899        for iType in self.iList.keys():
900            info.append("* **{}:** [{}]\n".format(iType, len(self.iList[iType])))
901
902        headerLine = "| Ticker       | Full name                                                      | FIGI         | Cur | Lot    | Step\n"
903        splitLine = "|--------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|--------------|-----|--------|---------\n"
904
905        # generate info tables with all instruments by type:
906        for iType in self.iList.keys():
907            info.extend(["\n\n## {} available. Total: [{}]\n\n".format(iType, len(self.iList[iType])), headerLine, splitLine])
908
909            for instrument in self.iList[iType].keys():
910                iName = self.iList[iType][instrument]["name"]  # instrument's name
911                if len(iName) > 63:
912                    iName = "{}...".format(iName[:60])  # right trim for a long string
913    
914                info.append("| {:<12} | {:<63}| {:<13}| {:<4}| {:<7}| {}\n".format(
915                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["ticker"],
916                    iName,
917                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["figi"],
918                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["currency"],
919                    self.iList[iType][instrument]["lot"],
920                    str(self.iList[iType][instrument]["step"]).rstrip("0"),
921                ))
922
923        infoText = "".join(info)
924
925        if showInstruments:
926            uLogger.info(infoText)
927
928        if self.instrumentsFile:
929            with open(self.instrumentsFile, "w", encoding="UTF-8") as fH:
930                fH.write(infoText)
931
932            uLogger.info("All available instruments are saved to file: [{}]".format(os.path.abspath(self.instrumentsFile)))
933
934        return infoText

This method get and show information about all available broker instruments. If instrumentsFile string is not empty then also save information to this file.

Parameters
  • showInstruments: if True then print to console, if False - print only to file.
Returns

multi-string with all available broker instruments

def GetListOfPrices(self, instruments: list = None, showPrices: bool = False) -> list: 
 936    def GetListOfPrices(self, instruments: list = None, showPrices: bool = False) -> list:
 937        """
 938        This method get, maybe show and return prices of list of instruments. WARNING! This is potential long operation!
 939        See limits: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/limits/
 940        If `pricesFile` string is not empty then also save information to this file.
 941
 942        :param instruments: list of tickers or FIGIs.
 943        :param showPrices: if `True` then print to console, if `False` - print only to file.
 944        :return: list of instruments looks like this: `iList = [{some ticker info, "currentPrice": {current prices}}, {...}, ...]`
 945                 One item is dict returned by `SearchByTicker()` or `SearchByFIGI()` methods.
 946        """
 947        if instruments is None or not instruments:
 948            raise Exception("You must define some of tickers or FIGIs to request it's actual prices!")
 949
 950        uLogger.debug("Requesting current prices of list of instruments from Tinkoff Broker server...")
 951
 952        iList = []
 953        for iName in instruments:
 954            if iName not in self.aliases.keys():
 955                iList.append(iName)
 956
 957            else:
 958                iList.append(self.aliases[iName])
 959
 960        unique = set()  # create list with every figi only one time with the same order position:
 961        tempNames = [item for item in iList if not (item in unique or unique.add(item))]
 962
 963        uLogger.debug("Ordered input list of instruments without duplicates of names: {}".format(tempNames))
 964
 965        iList = []  # try to get info about all unique instruments:
 966        for iName in tempNames:
 967            self.ticker = iName
 968            iData = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=True)
 969
 970            if not iData:
 971                self.ticker = ""
 972                self.figi = iName
 973
 974                iData = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True)
 975
 976                if not iData:
 977                    self.figi = ""
 978                    uLogger.warning("Instrument [{}] not in list of available instruments for current token!".format(iName))
 979
 980            if iData:
 981                isUnique = True
 982                for item in iList:
 983                    if item["figi"] == iData["figi"] or item["ticker"] == iData["ticker"]:
 984                        isUnique = False
 985                        break
 986
 987                if isUnique:
 988                    iList.append(iData)
 989
 990        if showPrices:
 991            info = [
 992                "# Actual prices at: [{} UTC]\n\n".format(datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M")),
 993                "| Ticker       | FIGI         | Type       | Prev. close | Last price  | Chg. %   | Day limits min/max  | Actual sell / buy   | Curr.\n",
 994                "|--------------|--------------|------------|-------------|-------------|----------|---------------------|---------------------|------\n",
 995            ]
 996
 997            for item in iList:
 998                info.append("| {:<12} | {:<12} | {:<10} | {:>11} | {:>11} | {:>7}% | {:>19} | {:>19} | {}\n".format(
 999                    item["ticker"],
1000                    item["figi"],
1001                    item["type"],
1002                    "{:.2f}".format(float(item["currentPrice"]["closePrice"])),
1003                    "{:.2f}".format(float(item["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"])),
1004                    "{}{:.2f}".format("+" if item["currentPrice"]["changes"] > 0 else "", float(item["currentPrice"]["changes"])),
1005                    "{} / {}".format(
1006                        item["currentPrice"]["limitDown"] if item["currentPrice"]["limitDown"] is not None else "N/A",
1007                        item["currentPrice"]["limitUp"] if item["currentPrice"]["limitUp"] is not None else "N/A",
1008                    ),
1009                    "{} / {}".format(
1010                        item["currentPrice"]["sell"][0]["price"] if item["currentPrice"]["sell"] else "N/A",
1011                        item["currentPrice"]["buy"][0]["price"] if item["currentPrice"]["buy"] else "N/A",
1012                    ),
1013                    item["currency"],
1014                ))
1015
1016            infoText = "".join(info)
1017
1018            if showPrices:
1019                uLogger.info("Only unique instruments are shown:\n{}".format(infoText))
1020
1021            if self.pricesFile:
1022                with open(self.pricesFile, "w", encoding="UTF-8") as fH:
1023                    fH.write(infoText)
1024
1025                uLogger.info("Price list for all instruments saved to file: [{}]".format(os.path.abspath(self.pricesFile)))
1026
1027        return iList

This method get, maybe show and return prices of list of instruments. WARNING! This is potential long operation! See limits: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/limits/ If pricesFile string is not empty then also save information to this file.

Parameters
  • instruments: list of tickers or FIGIs.
  • showPrices: if True then print to console, if False - print only to file.
Returns

list of instruments looks like this: iList = [{some ticker info, "currentPrice": {current prices}}, {...}, ...] One item is dict returned by SearchByTicker() or SearchByFIGI() methods.
