def Overview(self, showStatistics: bool = False) -> dict: 
1097    def Overview(self, showStatistics: bool = False) -> dict:
1098        """
1099        Get portfolio: all open positions, orders and some statistics for defined accountId.
1100        If `overviewFile` is define then also save information to file.
1101
1102        :param showStatistics: if `False` then only dictionary returns, if `True` then show more debug information.
1103        :return: dictionary with client's raw portfolio and some statistics.
1104        """
1105        view = {
1106            "raw": {  # --- raw portfolio responses from broker with user portfolio data:
1107                "headers": {},  # list of dictionaries, response headers without "positions" section
1108                "Currencies": [],  # list of dictionaries, open trades with currencies from "positions" section
1109                "Shares": [],  # list of dictionaries, open trades with stocks from "positions" section
1110                "Bonds": [],  # list of dictionaries, open trades with bonds from "positions" section
1111                "Etfs": [],  # list of dictionaries, open trades with etfs from "positions" section
1112                "Futures": [],  # list of dictionaries, open trades with futures from "positions" section
1113                "positions": {},  # raw response from broker: dictionary with current available or blocked currencies and instruments for client
1114                "orders": [],  # raw response from broker: list of dictionaries with all pending (market) orders
1115                "stopOrders": [],  # raw response from broker: list of dictionaries with all stop orders
1116                "currenciesCurrentPrices": {"rub": {"name": "Российский рубль", "currentPrice": 1.}},  # dict with prices of all currencies in RUB
1117            },
1118            "stat": {  # --- some statistics calculated using "raw" sections:
1119                "portfolioCostRUB": 0.,  # portfolio cost in RUB (Russian Rouble)
1120                "currentBlockedRUB": 0.,  # blocked sum in Russian Rouble
1121                "totalChangesRUB": 0.,  # changes for all open trades in RUB
1122                "totalChangesPercentRUB": 0.,  # changes for all open trades in percents
1123                "allCurrenciesCostRUB": 0.,  # costs of all currencies (include rubles) in RUB
1124                "availableRUB": 0.,  # available rubles (without other currencies)
1125                "stocksCostRUB": 0.,  # costs of all stocks in RUB
1126                "bondsCostRUB": 0.,  # costs of all bonds in RUB
1127                "etfsCostRUB": 0.,  # costs of all etfs in RUB
1128                "Currencies": [],  # list of dictionaries of all currencies statistics
1129                "Shares": [],  # list of dictionaries of all stocks statistics
1130                "Bonds": [],  # list of dictionaries of all bonds statistics
1131                "Etfs": [], # list of dictionaries of all etfs statistics
1132                "Futures": [], # list of dictionaries of all futures statistics
1133                "orders": [],  # list of dictionaries of all pending (market) orders and it's parameters
1134                "stopOrders": [],  # list of dictionaries of all stop orders and it's parameters
1135                "blockedCurrencies": {},  # dict with blocked instruments and currencies, e.g. {"rub": 1291.87, "usd": 6.21}
1136                "blockedInstruments": {},  # dict with blocked  by FIGI, e.g. {}
1137            },
1138            "analytics":{  # --- some analytics of portfolio:
1139                "distrByAssets": {},  # portfolio distribution by assets
1140                "distrByCompanies": {},  # portfolio distribution by companies
1141                "distrBySectors": {},  # portfolio distribution by sectors
1142                "distrByCurrencies": {},  # portfolio distribution by currencies
1143            }
1144        }
1145
1146        if showStatistics:
1147            uLogger.debug("Request portfolio of a client...")
1148
1149        portfolioResponse = self.RequestPortfolio()  # current user's portfolio (dict)
1150        view["raw"]["positions"] = self.RequestPositions()  # current open positions by instruments (dict)
1151        view["raw"]["orders"] = self.RequestPendingOrders()  # current actual pending orders (list)
1152        view["raw"]["stopOrders"] = self.RequestStopOrders()  # current actual stop orders (list)
1153
1154        # save response headers without "positions" section:
1155        for key in portfolioResponse.keys():
1156            if key != "positions":
1157                view["raw"]["headers"][key] = portfolioResponse[key]
1158
1159            else:
1160                continue
1161
1162        # Re-sorting and separating given raw instruments and currencies by type: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/operations/#operation
1163        # Type of instrument must be only one of supported types in TKS_INSTRUMENTS
1164        for item in portfolioResponse["positions"]:
1165            if item["instrumentType"] == "currency":
1166                self.figi = item["figi"]
1167                curr = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=False)
1168
1169                # current price of currency in RUB:
1170                view["raw"]["currenciesCurrentPrices"][curr["nominal"]["currency"]] = {
1171                    "name": curr["name"],
1172                    "currentPrice": NanoToFloat(
1173                        item["currentPrice"]["units"],
1174                        item["currentPrice"]["nano"]
1175                    ),
1176                }
1177
1178                view["raw"]["Currencies"].append(item)
1179
1180            elif item["instrumentType"] == "share":
1181                view["raw"]["Shares"].append(item)
1182
1183            elif item["instrumentType"] == "bond":
1184                view["raw"]["Bonds"].append(item)
1185
1186            elif item["instrumentType"] == "etf":
1187                view["raw"]["Etfs"].append(item)
1188
1189            elif item["instrumentType"] == "futures":
1190                view["raw"]["Futures"].append(item)
1191
1192            else:
1193                continue
1194
1195        # how many volume of currencies (by ISO currency name) are blocked:
1196        for item in view["raw"]["positions"]["blocked"]:
1197            blocked = NanoToFloat(item["units"], item["nano"])
1198            if blocked > 0:
1199                view["stat"]["blockedCurrencies"][item["currency"]] = blocked
1200
1201        # how many volume of instruments (by FIGI) are blocked:
1202        for item in view["raw"]["positions"]["securities"]:
1203            blocked = int(item["blocked"])
1204            if blocked > 0:
1205                view["stat"]["blockedInstruments"][item["figi"]] = blocked
1206
1207        allBlocked = {**view["stat"]["blockedCurrencies"], **view["stat"]["blockedInstruments"]}
1208
1209        if "rub" in allBlocked.keys():
1210            view["stat"]["currentBlockedRUB"] = allBlocked["rub"]  # blocked rubles
1211
1212        # --- saving current total amount in RUB of all currencies (with ruble), stocks, bonds, etfs, futures and currencies:
1213        view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"] = NanoToFloat(portfolioResponse["totalAmountCurrencies"]["units"], portfolioResponse["totalAmountCurrencies"]["nano"])
1214        view["stat"]["stocksCostRUB"] = NanoToFloat(portfolioResponse["totalAmountShares"]["units"], portfolioResponse["totalAmountShares"]["nano"])
1215        view["stat"]["bondsCostRUB"] = NanoToFloat(portfolioResponse["totalAmountBonds"]["units"], portfolioResponse["totalAmountBonds"]["nano"])
1216        view["stat"]["etfsCostRUB"] = NanoToFloat(portfolioResponse["totalAmountEtf"]["units"], portfolioResponse["totalAmountEtf"]["nano"])
1217        view["stat"]["futuresCostRUB"] = NanoToFloat(portfolioResponse["totalAmountFutures"]["units"], portfolioResponse["totalAmountFutures"]["nano"])
1218        view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] = sum([
1219            view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"],
1220            view["stat"]["stocksCostRUB"],
1221            view["stat"]["bondsCostRUB"],
1222            view["stat"]["etfsCostRUB"],
1223            view["stat"]["futuresCostRUB"],
1224        ])
1225
1226        # --- calculating some portfolio statistics:
1227        byComp = {}  # distribution by companies
1228        bySect = {}  # distribution by sectors
1229        byCurr = {}  # distribution by currencies (include RUB)
1230
1231        for item in portfolioResponse["positions"]:
1232            self.figi = item["figi"]
1233            instrument = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=False)  # full raw info about instrument by FIGI
1234
1235            if instrument:
1236                if item["instrumentType"] == "currency" and instrument["nominal"]["currency"] in allBlocked.keys():
1237                    blocked = allBlocked[instrument["nominal"]["currency"]]  # blocked volume of currency
1238
1239                elif item["instrumentType"] != "currency" and item["figi"] in allBlocked.keys():
1240                    blocked = allBlocked[item["figi"]]  # blocked volume of other instruments
1241
1242                else:
1243                    blocked = 0
1244
1245                volume = NanoToFloat(item["quantity"]["units"], item["quantity"]["nano"])  # available volume of instrument
1246                lots = NanoToFloat(item["quantityLots"]["units"], item["quantityLots"]["nano"])  # available volume in lots of instrument
1247                direction = "Long" if lots >= 0 else "Short"  # direction of an instrument's position: short or long
1248                curPrice = NanoToFloat(item["currentPrice"]["units"], item["currentPrice"]["nano"])  # current instrument's price
1249                average = NanoToFloat(item["averagePositionPriceFifo"]["units"], item["averagePositionPriceFifo"]["nano"])  # current average position price
1250                profit = NanoToFloat(item["expectedYield"]["units"], item["expectedYield"]["nano"])  # expected profit at current moment
1251                currency = instrument["currency"] if (item["instrumentType"] == "share" or item["instrumentType"] == "etf" or item["instrumentType"] == "future") else instrument["nominal"]["currency"]  # currency name rub, usd, eur etc.
1252                cost = (curPrice + NanoToFloat(item["currentNkd"]["units"], item["currentNkd"]["nano"])) * volume  # current cost of all volume of instrument in basic asset
1253                baseCurrencyName = item["currentPrice"]["currency"]  # name of base currency (rub)
1254                costRUB = cost if item["instrumentType"] == "currency" else cost * view["raw"]["currenciesCurrentPrices"][currency]["currentPrice"]  # cost in rubles
1255                percentCostRUB = 100 * costRUB / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.  # instrument's part in percent of full portfolio cost
1256
1257                statData = {
1258                    "figi": item["figi"],  # FIGI from REST API "GetPortfolio" method
1259                    "ticker": instrument["ticker"],  # ticker by FIGI
1260                    "currency": currency,  # currency name rub, usd, eur etc. for instrument price
1261                    "volume": volume,  # available volume of instrument
1262                    "lots": lots,  # volume in lots of instrument
1263                    "direction": direction,  # direction of an instrument's position: short or long
1264                    "blocked": blocked,  # blocked volume of currency or instrument
1265                    "currentPrice": curPrice,  # current instrument's price in basic asset
1266                    "average": average,  # current average position price
1267                    "cost": cost,  # current cost of all volume of instrument in basic asset
1268                    "baseCurrencyName": baseCurrencyName,  # name of base currency (rub)
1269                    "costRUB": costRUB,  # cost of instrument in ruble
1270                    "percentCostRUB": percentCostRUB,  # instrument's part in percent of full portfolio cost in RUB
1271                    "profit": profit,  # expected profit at current moment
1272                    "percentProfit": 100 * profit / (average * volume),  # expected percents of profit at current moment for this instrument
1273                    "sector": instrument["sector"] if "sector" in instrument.keys() and instrument["sector"] else "other",
1274                    "name": instrument["name"] if "name" in instrument.keys() else "",  # human-readable names of instruments
1275                    "isoCurrencyName": instrument["isoCurrencyName"] if "isoCurrencyName" in instrument.keys() else "",  # ISO name for currencies only
1276                }
1277
1278                if item["instrumentType"] != "currency":
1279                    # adding distribution by unique companies:
1280                    if statData["name"]:
1281                        if statData["name"] not in byComp.keys():
1282                            byComp[statData["name"]] = {"ticker": statData["ticker"], "cost": costRUB, "percent": percentCostRUB}
1283
1284                        else:
1285                            byComp[statData["name"]]["cost"] += costRUB
1286                            byComp[statData["name"]]["percent"] += percentCostRUB
1287
1288                    # adding distribution by unique sectors:
1289                    if statData["sector"] not in bySect.keys():
1290                        bySect[statData["sector"]] = {"cost": costRUB, "percent": percentCostRUB}
1291
1292                    else:
1293                        bySect[statData["sector"]]["cost"] += costRUB
1294                        bySect[statData["sector"]]["percent"] += percentCostRUB
1295
1296                # adding distribution by unique currencies:
1297                if currency not in byCurr.keys():
1298                    byCurr[currency] = {
1299                        "name": view["raw"]["currenciesCurrentPrices"][currency]["name"],
1300                        "cost": costRUB,
1301                        "percent": percentCostRUB
1302                    }
1303
1304                else:
1305                    byCurr[currency]["cost"] += costRUB
1306                    byCurr[currency]["percent"] += percentCostRUB
1307
1308                # saving statistics for every instruments:
1309                if item["instrumentType"] == "currency":
1310                    view["stat"]["Currencies"].append(statData)
1311
1312                elif item["instrumentType"] == "share":
1313                    view["stat"]["Shares"].append(statData)
1314
1315                elif item["instrumentType"] == "bond":
1316                    view["stat"]["Bonds"].append(statData)
1317
1318                elif item["instrumentType"] == "etf":
1319                    view["stat"]["Etfs"].append(statData)
1320
1321                elif item["instrumentType"] == "Futures":
1322                    view["stat"]["Futures"].append(statData)
1323
1324                else:
1325                    continue
1326
1327        # total changes:
1328        view["stat"]["availableRUB"] = view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"] - sum([item["cost"] for item in view["stat"]["Currencies"]])  # available RUB without other currencies
1329        view["stat"]["totalChangesPercentRUB"] = NanoToFloat(view["raw"]["headers"]["expectedYield"]["units"], view["raw"]["headers"]["expectedYield"]["nano"]) if "expectedYield" in view["raw"]["headers"].keys() else 0.
1330        startCost = view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] / (1 + view["stat"]["totalChangesPercentRUB"] / 100)
1331        view["stat"]["totalChangesRUB"] = view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] - startCost
1332
1333        # --- pending orders sector data:
1334        for item in view["raw"]["orders"]:
1335            self.figi = item["figi"]
1336            instrument = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True)  # full raw info about instrument by FIGI
1337
1338            if instrument:
1339                action = TKS_ORDER_DIRECTIONS[item["direction"]]
1340                orderType = TKS_ORDER_TYPES[item["orderType"]]
1341                orderState = TKS_ORDER_STATES[item["executionReportStatus"]]
1342                orderDate = item["orderDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "").split(".")[0]  # date in UTC format, e.g. "2022-12-31T23:59:59.123456Z"
1343
1344                # current instrument's price (last sellers order if buy, and last buyers order if sell):
1345                if item["direction"] == "ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY":
1346                    lastPrice = instrument["currentPrice"]["sell"][0]["price"] if instrument["currentPrice"]["sell"] else "N/A"
1347
1348                else:
1349                    lastPrice = instrument["currentPrice"]["buy"][0]["price"] if instrument["currentPrice"]["buy"] else "N/A"
1350
1351                # requested price for order execution:
1352                target = NanoToFloat(item["initialSecurityPrice"]["units"], item["initialSecurityPrice"]["nano"])
1353
1354                # necessary changes in percent to reach target from current price:
1355                changes = 100 * (lastPrice - target) / target if lastPrice != "N/A" and target > 0 else 0
1356
1357                view["stat"]["orders"].append({
1358                    "orderID": item["orderId"],  # orderId number parameter of current order
1359                    "figi": item["figi"],  # FIGI identification
1360                    "ticker": instrument["ticker"],  # ticker name by FIGI
1361                    "lotsRequested": item["lotsRequested"],  # requested lots value
1362                    "lotsExecuted": item["lotsExecuted"],  # how many lots are executed
1363                    "currentPrice": lastPrice,  # current instrument's price for defined action
1364                    "targetPrice": target,  # requested price for order execution in base currency
1365                    "baseCurrencyName": item["initialSecurityPrice"]["currency"],  # name of base currency
1366                    "percentChanges": changes,  # changes in percent to target from current price
1367                    "currency": item["currency"],  # instrument's currency name
1368                    "action": action,  # sell / buy / Unknown from TKS_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
1369                    "type": orderType,  # type of order from TKS_ORDER_TYPES
1370                    "status": orderState,  # order status from TKS_ORDER_STATES
1371                    "date": orderDate,  # string with order date and time from UTC format (without nano seconds part)
1372                })
1373
1374        # --- stop orders sector data:
1375        for item in view["raw"]["stopOrders"]:
1376            self.figi = item["figi"]
1377            instrument = self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True)  # full raw info about instrument by FIGI
1378
1379            if instrument:
1380                action = TKS_STOP_ORDER_DIRECTIONS[item["direction"]]
1381                orderType = TKS_STOP_ORDER_TYPES[item["orderType"]]
1382                createDate = item["createDate"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "").split(".")[0]  # date in UTC format, e.g. "2022-12-31T23:59:59.123456Z"
1383
1384                # hack: server response can't contain "expirationTime" key if it is not "Until date" type of stop order
1385                if "expirationTime" in item.keys():
1386                    expType = TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES["STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_GOOD_TILL_DATE"]
1387                    expDate = item["expirationTime"].replace("T", " ").replace("Z", "").split(".")[0]
1388
1389                else:
1390                    expType = TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES["STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_GOOD_TILL_CANCEL"]
1391                    expDate = TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES["STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED"]
1392
1393                # current instrument's price (last sellers order if buy, and last buyers order if sell):
1394                if item["direction"] == "STOP_ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY":
1395                    lastPrice = instrument["currentPrice"]["sell"][0]["price"] if instrument["currentPrice"]["sell"] else "N/A"
1396
1397                else:
1398                    lastPrice = instrument["currentPrice"]["buy"][0]["price"] if instrument["currentPrice"]["buy"] else "N/A"
1399
1400                # requested price when stop-order executed:
1401                target = NanoToFloat(item["stopPrice"]["units"], item["stopPrice"]["nano"])
1402
1403                # price for limit-order, set up when stop-order executed:
1404                limit = NanoToFloat(item["price"]["units"], item["price"]["nano"])
1405
1406                # necessary changes in percent to reach target from current price:
1407                changes = 100 * (lastPrice - target) / target if lastPrice != "N/A" and target > 0 else 0
1408
1409                view["stat"]["stopOrders"].append({
1410                    "orderID": item["stopOrderId"],  # stopOrderId number parameter of current stop-order
1411                    "figi": item["figi"],  # FIGI identification
1412                    "ticker": instrument["ticker"],  # ticker name by FIGI
1413                    "lotsRequested": item["lotsRequested"],  # requested lots value
1414                    "currentPrice": lastPrice,  # current instrument's price for defined action
1415                    "targetPrice": target,  # requested price for stop-order execution in base currency
1416                    "limitPrice": limit,  # price for limit-order, set up when stop-order executed, 0 if market order
1417                    "baseCurrencyName": item["stopPrice"]["currency"],  # name of base currency
1418                    "percentChanges": changes,  # changes in percent to target from current price
1419                    "currency": item["currency"],  # instrument's currency name
1420                    "action": action,  # sell / buy / Unknown from TKS_STOP_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
1421                    "type": orderType,  # type of order from TKS_STOP_ORDER_TYPES
1422                    "expType": expType,  # expiration type of stop-order from TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES
1423                    "createDate": createDate,  # string with created order date and time from UTC format (without nano seconds part)
1424                    "expDate": expDate,  # string with expiration order date and time from UTC format (without nano seconds part)
1425                })
1426
1427        # --- calculating data for analytics section:
1428        # portfolio distribution by assets:
1429        view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"] = {
1430            "Ruble": {
1431                "uniques": 1,
1432                "cost": view["stat"]["availableRUB"],
1433                "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["availableRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1434            },
1435            "Currencies": {
1436                "uniques": len(view["stat"]["Currencies"]),  # all foreign currencies without RUB
1437                "cost": view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"] - view["stat"]["availableRUB"],
1438                "percent": 100 * (view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"] - view["stat"]["availableRUB"]) / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1439            },
1440            "Shares": {
1441                "uniques": len(view["stat"]["Shares"]),
1442                "cost": view["stat"]["stocksCostRUB"],
1443                "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["stocksCostRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1444            },
1445            "Bonds": {
1446                "uniques": len(view["stat"]["Bonds"]),
1447                "cost": view["stat"]["bondsCostRUB"],
1448                "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["bondsCostRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1449            },
1450            "Etfs": {
1451                "uniques": len(view["stat"]["Etfs"]),
1452                "cost": view["stat"]["etfsCostRUB"],
1453                "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["etfsCostRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1454            },
1455            "Futures": {
1456                "uniques": len(view["stat"]["Futures"]),
1457                "cost": view["stat"]["futuresCostRUB"],
1458                "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["futuresCostRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1459            },
1460        }
1461
1462        # portfolio distribution by companies:
1463        view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"]["All money cash"] = {
1464            "ticker": "",
1465            "cost": view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"],
1466            "percent": 100 * view["stat"]["allCurrenciesCostRUB"] / view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] if view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"] > 0 else 0.,
1467        }
1468        view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"].update(byComp)
1469
1470        # portfolio distribution by sectors:
1471        view["analytics"]["distrBySectors"]["All money cash"] = {
1472            "cost": view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"]["All money cash"]["cost"],
1473            "percent": view["analytics"]["distrByCompanies"]["All money cash"]["percent"],
1474        }
1475        view["analytics"]["distrBySectors"].update(bySect)
1476
1477        # portfolio distribution by currencies:
1478        view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"].update(byCurr)
1479        view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"]["rub"]["cost"] += view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"]["Ruble"]["cost"]
1480        view["analytics"]["distrByCurrencies"]["rub"]["percent"] += view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"]["Ruble"]["percent"]
1481
1482        # --- Prepare text statistics overview in human-readable:
1483        if showStatistics:
1484            info = [
1485                "# Client's portfolio\n\n",
1486                "* **Actual date:** [{}] (UTC)\n".format(datetime.now(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")),
1487                "* **Portfolio cost:** {:.2f} RUB\n".format(view["stat"]["portfolioCostRUB"]),
1488                "* **Changes:** {}{:.2f} RUB ({}{:.2f}%)\n\n".format(
1489                    "+" if view["stat"]["totalChangesRUB"] > 0 else "",
1490                    view["stat"]["totalChangesRUB"],
1491                    "+" if view["stat"]["totalChangesPercentRUB"] > 0 else "",
1492                    view["stat"]["totalChangesPercentRUB"],
1493                ),
1494                "## Open positions\n\n",
1495                "| Ticker [FIGI]               | Volume (blocked)                | Lots     | Curr. price  | Avg. price   | Current volume cost | Profit (%)\n",
1496                "|-----------------------------|---------------------------------|----------|--------------|--------------|---------------------|----------------------\n",
1497                "| Ruble                       | {:>31} |          |              |              |                     |\n".format(
1498                    "{:.2f} ({:.2f}) rub".format(
1499                        view["stat"]["availableRUB"],
1500                        view["stat"]["currentBlockedRUB"],
1501                    )
1502                )
1503            ]
1504
1505            def _SplitStr(CostRUB: float = 0, typeStr: str = "", noTradeStr: str = "") -> list:
1506                return [
1507                    "|                             |                                 |          |              |              |                     |\n",
1508                    "| {:<27} |                                 |          |              |              | {:>19} |\n".format(
1509                        noTradeStr if noTradeStr else typeStr,
1510                        "" if noTradeStr else "{:.2f} RUB".format(CostRUB),
1511                    ),
1512                ]
1513
1514            def _InfoStr(data: dict, showCurrencyName: bool = False) -> str:
1515                return "| {:<27} | {:>31} | {:<8} | {:>12} | {:>12} | {:>19} | {}\n".format(
1516                    "{} [{}]".format(data["ticker"], data["figi"]),
1517                    "{:.2f} ({:.2f}) {}".format(
1518                        data["volume"],
1519                        data["blocked"],
1520                        data["currency"],
1521                    ) if showCurrencyName else "{:.0f} ({:.0f})".format(
1522                        data["volume"],
1523                        data["blocked"],
1524                    ),
1525                    "{:.4f}".format(data["lots"]) if showCurrencyName else "{:.0f}".format(data["lots"]),
1526                    "{:.2f} {}".format(data["currentPrice"], data["baseCurrencyName"]) if data["currentPrice"] > 0 else "n/a",
1527                    "{:.2f} {}".format(data["average"], data["baseCurrencyName"]) if data["average"] > 0 else "n/a",
1528                    "{:.2f} {}".format(data["cost"], data["baseCurrencyName"]),
1529                    "{}{:.2f} {} ({}{:.2f}%)".format(
1530                        "+" if data["profit"] > 0 else "",
1531                        data["profit"], data["baseCurrencyName"],
1532                        "+" if data["percentProfit"] > 0 else "",
1533                        data["percentProfit"],
1534                    ),
1535                )
1536
1537            # --- Show currencies section:
1538            if view["stat"]["Currencies"]:
1539                info.extend(_SplitStr(CostRUB=view["analytics"]["distrByAssets"]["Currencies"]["cost"], typeStr="**Currencies:**"))
1540                for item in view["stat"]["Currencies"]:
1541                    info.append(_InfoStr(item, showCurrencyName=True))
1542
1543            else:
1544                info.extend(_SplitStr(noTradeStr="**Currencies:** no trades"))
1545
1546            # --- Show stocks section:
1547            if view["stat"]["Shares"]:
1548                info.extend(_SplitStr(CostRUB=view["stat"]["stocksCostRUB"], typeStr="**Stocks:**"))
1549
1550                for item in view["stat"]["Shares"]:
1551                    info.append(_InfoStr(item))
1552
1553            else:
1554                info.extend(_SplitStr(noTradeStr="**Stocks:** no trades"))
1555
1556            # --- Show bonds section:
1557            if view["stat"]["Bonds"]:
1558                info.extend(_SplitStr(CostRUB=view["stat"]["bondsCostRUB"], typeStr="**Bonds:**"))
1559
1560                for item in view["stat"]["Bonds"]:
1561                    info.append(_InfoStr(item))
1562
1563            else:
1564                info.extend(_SplitStr(noTradeStr="**Bonds:** no trades"))
1565
1566            # --- Show etfs section:
1567            if view["stat"]["Etfs"]:
1568                info.extend(_SplitStr(CostRUB=view["stat"]["etfsCostRUB"], typeStr="**Etfs:**"))
1569
1570                for item in view["stat"]["Etfs"]:
1571                    info.append(_InfoStr(item))
1572
1573            else:
1574                info.extend(_SplitStr(noTradeStr="**Etfs:** no trades"))
1575
1576            # --- Show futures section:
1577            if view["stat"]["Futures"]:
1578                info.extend(_SplitStr(CostRUB=view["stat"]["futuresCostRUB"], typeStr="**Futures:**"))
1579
1580                for item in view["stat"]["Futures"]:
1581                    info.append(_InfoStr(item))
1582
1583            else:
1584                info.extend(_SplitStr(noTradeStr="**Futures:** no trades"))
1585
1586            # --- Show pending orders section:
1587            if view["stat"]["orders"]:
1588                info.extend([
1589                    "\n## Opened pending limit-orders: {}\n".format(len(view["stat"]["orders"])),
1590                    "\n| Ticker [FIGI]               | Order ID       | Lots (exec.) | Current price (% delta) | Target price  | Action    | Type      | Create date (UTC)\n",
1591                    "|-----------------------------|----------------|--------------|-------------------------|---------------|-----------|-----------|---------------------\n",
1592                ])
1593                for item in view["stat"]["orders"]:
1594                    info.append("| {:<27} | {:<14} | {:<12} | {:>23} | {:>13} | {:<9} | {:<9} | {}\n".format(
1595                        "{} [{}]".format(item["ticker"], item["figi"]),
1596                        item["orderID"],
1597                        "{} ({})".format(item["lotsRequested"], item["lotsExecuted"]),

This method returns last history candles of the current instrument defined by ticker. If historyFile is not None then method save history to this file, otherwise return only pandas dataframe. historyLength define how many candles returns from past to current date. historyInterval define candle interval. Available values are strings: "1min", "2min", "3min", "5min", "10min", "15min", "30min", "hour", "day", "week", "month". Default: "hour". Maximum requested history date in the past: 1970.01.02 03:45

Parameters
  • onlyMissing: if history file define then add only last missing candles, do not request all history length. False by default. WARNING! History appends only from last candle to current time with replace last candle! Intervals must be similar!
Returns

pandas dataframe with stock history. Columns: date, time, open, high, low, close, volume.

def Trade( self, operation: str, lots: int = 1, tp: float = 0.0, sl: float = 0.0, expDate: str = 'Undefined') -> dict: 
2147    def Trade(self, operation: str, lots: int = 1, tp: float = 0., sl: float = 0., expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2148        """
2149        Universal method to create market order and make deal at the current price. Returns JSON data with response.
2150        If `tp` or `sl` > 0, then in additional will opens stop-orders with "TP" and "SL" flags for `stopType` parameter.
2151
2152        See also: `Order()` docstring. More simple methods than `Trade()` are `Buy()` and `Sell()`.
2153
2154        :param operation: string "Buy" or "Sell".
2155        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2156        :param tp: float > 0, target price for stop-order with "TP" type. It used as take profit parameter `targetPrice` in `self.Order()`.
2157        :param sl: float > 0, target price for stop-order with "SL" type. It used as stop loss parameter `targetPrice` in `self.Order()`.
2158        :param expDate: string "Undefined" by default or local date in future,
2159                        it is a string with format `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2160        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2161        """
2162        if operation is None or not operation or operation not in ("Buy", "Sell"):
2163            raise Exception("You must define operation type only one of them: `Buy` or `Sell`!")
2164
2165        if lots is None or lots < 1:
2166            uLogger.warning("You must define trade volume > 0: integer count of lots! For current operation lots reset to 1.")
2167            lots = 1
2168
2169        if tp is None or tp < 0:
2170            tp = 0
2171
2172        if sl is None or sl < 0:
2173            sl = 0
2174
2175        if expDate is None or not expDate:
2176            expDate = "Undefined"
2177
2178        if not (self.ticker or self.figi):
2179            raise Exception("`self.ticker` or `self.figi` variables must be defined!")
2180
2181        instrument = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=True, debug=False) if self.ticker else self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True, debug=False)
2182        self.ticker = instrument["ticker"]
2183        self.figi = instrument["figi"]
2184
2185        uLogger.debug("Opening [{}] market order: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], lots [{}], TP [{:.4f}], SL [{:.4f}], expiration date of TP/SL orders [{}]. Wait, please...".format(operation, self.ticker, self.figi, lots, tp, sl, expDate))
2186
2187        openTradeURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OrdersService/PostOrder"
2188        self.body = str({
2189            "figi": self.figi,
2190            "quantity": str(lots),
2191            "direction": "ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY" if operation == "Buy" else "ORDER_DIRECTION_SELL",  # see: TKS_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
2192            "accountId": str(self.accountId),
2193            "orderType": "ORDER_TYPE_MARKET",  # see: TKS_ORDER_TYPES
2194        })
2195        response = self.SendAPIRequest(openTradeURL, reqType="POST", retry=0, debug=False)
2196
2197        if "orderId" in response.keys():
2198            uLogger.info("[{}] market order [{}] was executed: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], lots [{}]. Total order price: [{:.4f} {}] (with commission: [{:.2f} {}]). Average price of lot: [{:.2f} {}]".format(
2199                operation, response["orderId"],
2200                self.ticker, self.figi, lots,
2201                NanoToFloat(response["totalOrderAmount"]["units"], response["totalOrderAmount"]["nano"]), response["totalOrderAmount"]["currency"],
2202                NanoToFloat(response["initialCommission"]["units"], response["initialCommission"]["nano"]), response["initialCommission"]["currency"],
2203                NanoToFloat(response["executedOrderPrice"]["units"], response["executedOrderPrice"]["nano"]), response["executedOrderPrice"]["currency"],
2204            ))
2205
2206        else:
2207            uLogger.warning("Not `oK` status received! Market order not created. See full debug log or try again and open order later.")
2208
2209        if tp > 0:
2210            self.Order(operation="Sell" if operation == "Buy" else "Buy", orderType="Stop", lots=lots, targetPrice=tp, limitPrice=tp, stopType="TP", expDate=expDate)
2211
2212        if sl > 0:
2213            self.Order(operation="Sell" if operation == "Buy" else "Buy", orderType="Stop", lots=lots, targetPrice=sl, limitPrice=sl, stopType="SL", expDate=expDate)
2214
2215        return response

Universal method to create market order and make deal at the current price. Returns JSON data with response. If tp or sl > 0, then in additional will opens stop-orders with "TP" and "SL" flags for stopType parameter.

See also: Order() docstring. More simple methods than Trade() are Buy() and Sell().

def CloseTrades(self, tickers: list, overview: dict = None) -> None: 
2249    def CloseTrades(self, tickers: list, overview: dict = None) -> None:
2250        """
2251        Close position of given instruments.
2252
2253        :param tickers: tickers list of instruments that must be closed.
2254        :param overview: pre-received dictionary with open trades, returned by `Overview()` method.
2255                         This avoids unnecessary downloading data from the server.
2256        """
2257        if not tickers:
2258            uLogger.info("Tickers list empty, nothing to close.")
2259
2260        else:
2261            if overview is None or not overview:
2262                overview = self.Overview(showStatistics=False)
2263
2264            allOpenedTickers = [item["ticker"] for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS for item in overview["stat"][iType]]
2265            uLogger.debug("All opened instruments by it's tickers names: {}".format(allOpenedTickers))
2266
2267            for ticker in tickers:
2268                if not ticker in allOpenedTickers:
2269                    uLogger.warning("Instrument with ticker [{}] not in open positions list!".format(ticker))
2270                    continue
2271
2272                # search open trade info about instrument by ticker:
2273                instrument = {}
2274                for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
2275                    if instrument:
2276                        break
2277
2278                    for item in overview["stat"][iType]:
2279                        if item["ticker"] == ticker:
2280                            instrument = item
2281                            break
2282
2283                if instrument:
2284                    self.ticker = ticker
2285                    self.figi = instrument["figi"]
2286
2287                    uLogger.debug("Closing trade of instrument: ticker [{}], FIGI[{}], lots [{}]{}. Wait, please...".format(
2288                        self.ticker,
2289                        self.figi,
2290                        int(instrument["volume"]),
2291                        ", blocked [{}]".format(instrument["blocked"]) if instrument["blocked"] > 0 else "",
2292                    ))
2293
2294                    tradeLots = abs(instrument["lots"]) - instrument["blocked"]  # available volumes in lots for close operation
2295
2296                    if tradeLots > 0:
2297                        if instrument["blocked"] > 0:
2298                            uLogger.warning("Just for your information: there are [{}] lots blocked for instrument [{}]! Available only [{}] lots to closing trade.".format(
2299                                instrument["blocked"],
2300                                self.ticker,
2301                                tradeLots,
2302                            ))
2303
2304                        # if direction is "Long" then we need sell, if direction is "Short" then we need buy:
2305                        self.Trade(operation="Sell" if instrument["direction"] == "Long" else "Buy", lots=tradeLots)
2306
2307                    else:
2308                        uLogger.warning("There are no available lots for instrument [{}] to closing trade at this moment! Try again later or cancel some orders.".format(self.ticker))

Parameters

def Order( self, operation: str, orderType: str, lots: int, targetPrice: float, limitPrice: float = 0.0, stopType: str = 'Limit', expDate: str = 'Undefined') -> dict: 
2334    def Order(self, operation: str, orderType: str, lots: int, targetPrice: float, limitPrice: float = 0., stopType: str = "Limit", expDate: str = "Undefined") -> dict:
2335        """
2336        Universal method to create market or limit orders with all available parameters.
2337        See more simple methods: `BuyLimit()`, `BuyStop()`, `SellLimit()`, `SellStop()`.
2338
2339        If orderType is "Limit" then create pending limit-order below current price if operation is "Buy" and above
2340        current price if operation is "Sell". A limit order has no expiration date, it lasts until the end of the trading day.
2341
2342        Warning! If you try to create limit-order above current price if "Buy" or below current price if "Sell"
2343        then broker immediately open market order as you can do simple --buy or --sell operations!
2344
2345        If orderType is "Stop" then creates stop-order with any direction "Buy" or "Sell".
2346        When current price will go up or down to target price value then broker opens a limit order.
2347        Stop-order is opened with unlimited expiration date by default, or you can define expiration date with expDate parameter.
2348
2349        Only one attempt and no retry for opens order. If network issue occurred you can create new request.
2350
2351        :param operation: string "Buy" or "Sell".
2352        :param orderType: string "Limit" or "Stop".
2353        :param lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
2354        :param targetPrice: target price > 0. This is open trade price for limit order.
2355        :param limitPrice: limit price >= 0. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order. If limitPrice = 0, then it set as targetPrice.
2356                           Broker will creates limit-order with price equal to limitPrice, when current price goes to target price of stop-order.
2357        :param stopType: string "Limit" by default. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order. There are 3 stop-order types
2358                         "SL", "TP", "Limit" for "Stop loss", "Take profit" and "Stop limit" types accordingly.
2359                         Stop loss order always executed by market price.
2360        :param expDate: string "Undefined" by default or local date in future.
2361                        String has a format like this: `%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S`.
2362                        This date is converting to UTC format for server. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order.
2363                        A limit order has no expiration date, it lasts until the end of the trading day.
2364        :return: JSON with response from broker server.
2365        """
2366        if operation is None or not operation or operation not in ("Buy", "Sell"):
2367            raise Exception("You must define operation type only one of them: `Buy` or `Sell`!")
2368
2369        if orderType is None or not orderType or orderType not in ("Limit", "Stop"):
2370            raise Exception("You must define order type only one of them: `Limit` or `Stop`!")
2371
2372        if lots is None or lots < 1:
2373            raise Exception("You must define trade volume > 0: integer count of lots!")
2374
2375        if targetPrice is None or targetPrice <= 0:
2376            raise Exception("Target price for limit-order must be greater than 0!")
2377
2378        if limitPrice is None or limitPrice <= 0:
2379            limitPrice = targetPrice
2380
2381        if stopType is None or not stopType or stopType not in ("SL", "TP", "Limit"):
2382            stopType = "Limit"
2383
2384        if expDate is None or not expDate:
2385            expDate = "Undefined"
2386
2387        if not (self.ticker or self.figi):
2388            raise Exception("`self.ticker` or `self.figi` variables must be defined!")
2389
2390        response = {}
2391        instrument = self.SearchByTicker(requestPrice=True, debug=False) if self.ticker else self.SearchByFIGI(requestPrice=True, debug=False)
2392        self.ticker = instrument["ticker"]
2393        self.figi = instrument["figi"]
2394
2395        if orderType == "Limit":
2396            uLogger.debug(
2397                "Creating pending limit-order: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}] and the target price [{:.2f} {}]. Wait, please...".format(
2398                    self.ticker, self.figi,
2399                    operation, lots, targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2400                ))
2401
2402            openOrderURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OrdersService/PostOrder"
2403            self.body = str({
2404                "figi": self.figi,
2405                "quantity": str(lots),
2406                "price": FloatToNano(targetPrice),
2407                "direction": "ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY" if operation == "Buy" else "ORDER_DIRECTION_SELL",  # see: TKS_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
2408                "accountId": str(self.accountId),
2409                "orderType": "ORDER_TYPE_LIMIT",  # see: TKS_ORDER_TYPES
2410            })
2411            response = self.SendAPIRequest(openOrderURL, reqType="POST", retry=0, debug=False)
2412
2413            if "orderId" in response.keys():
2414                uLogger.info(
2415                    "Limit-order [{}] was created: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}], target price [{:.2f} {}]".format(
2416                        response["orderId"],
2417                        self.ticker, self.figi,
2418                        operation, lots, targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2419                    ))
2420
2421                if "lastPrice" in instrument["currentPrice"].keys() and instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2422                    if operation == "Buy" and targetPrice > instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2423                        uLogger.warning("Your order was executed as a market order, not as a limit order! Comment: because your target price [{:.2f} {}] was higher than current price [{:.2f} {}] broker immediately opened `Buy` market order, such as if you did simple `--buy` operation.".format(
2424                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2425                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2426                        ))
2427
2428                    if operation == "Sell" and targetPrice < instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2429                        uLogger.warning("Your order was executed as a market order, not as a limit order! Comment: because your target price [{:.2f} {}] was lower than current price [{:.2f} {}] broker immediately opened `Sell` market order, such as if you did simple `--sell` operation.".format(
2430                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2431                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2432                        ))
2433
2434            else:
2435                uLogger.warning("Not `oK` status received! Limit order not opened. See full debug log or try again and open order later.")
2436
2437        if orderType == "Stop":
2438            uLogger.debug(
2439                "Creating stop-order: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}], target price [{:.2f} {}], limit price [{:.2f} {}], stop-order type [{}] and local expiration date [{}]. Wait, please...".format(
2440                    self.ticker, self.figi,
2441                    operation, lots,
2442                    targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2443                    limitPrice, instrument["currency"],
2444                    stopType, expDate,
2445                ))
2446
2447            openOrderURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.StopOrdersService/PostStopOrder"
2448            expDateUTC = "" if expDate == "Undefined" else datetime.strptime(expDate, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S").replace(tzinfo=tzlocal()).astimezone(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%fZ")
2449            stopOrderType = "STOP_ORDER_TYPE_STOP_LOSS" if stopType == "SL" else "STOP_ORDER_TYPE_TAKE_PROFIT" if stopType == "TP" else "STOP_ORDER_TYPE_STOP_LIMIT"
2450
2451            body = {
2452                "figi": self.figi,
2453                "quantity": str(lots),
2454                "price": FloatToNano(limitPrice),
2455                "stopPrice": FloatToNano(targetPrice),
2456                "direction": "STOP_ORDER_DIRECTION_BUY" if operation == "Buy" else "STOP_ORDER_DIRECTION_SELL",  # see: TKS_STOP_ORDER_DIRECTIONS
2457                "accountId": str(self.accountId),
2458                "expirationType": "STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_GOOD_TILL_DATE" if expDateUTC else "STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_GOOD_TILL_CANCEL",  # see: TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES
2459                "stopOrderType": stopOrderType,  # see: TKS_STOP_ORDER_TYPES
2460            }
2461
2462            if expDateUTC:
2463                body["expireDate"] = expDateUTC
2464
2465            self.body = str(body)
2466            response = self.SendAPIRequest(openOrderURL, reqType="POST", retry=0, debug=False)
2467
2468            if "stopOrderId" in response.keys():
2469                uLogger.info(
2470                    "Stop-order [{}] was created: ticker [{}], FIGI [{}], action [{}], lots [{}], target price [{:.2f} {}], limit price [{:.2f} {}], stop-order type [{}] and expiration date in UTC [{}]".format(
2471                    response["stopOrderId"],
2472                    self.ticker, self.figi,
2473                    operation, lots,
2474                    targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2475                    limitPrice, instrument["currency"],
2476                    TKS_STOP_ORDER_TYPES[stopOrderType],
2477                    datetime.strptime(expDateUTC, "%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%fZ").replace(tzinfo=tzutc()).astimezone(tzutc()).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S") if expDateUTC else TKS_STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPES["STOP_ORDER_EXPIRATION_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED"],
2478                ))
2479
2480                if "lastPrice" in instrument["currentPrice"].keys() and instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"]:
2481                    if operation == "Buy" and targetPrice < instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] and stopType != "TP":
2482                        uLogger.warning("The broker will cancel this order after some time. Comment: you placed the wrong stop order because the target buy price [{:.2f} {}] is lower than the current price [{:.2f} {}]. Also try to set up order type as `TP` if you want to place stop order at that price.".format(
2483                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2484                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2485                        ))
2486
2487                    if operation == "Sell" and targetPrice > instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"] and stopType != "TP":
2488                        uLogger.warning("The broker will cancel this order after some time. Comment: you placed the wrong stop order because the target sell price [{:.2f} {}] is higher than the current price [{:.2f} {}]. Also try to set up order type as `TP` if you want to place stop order at that price.".format(
2489                            targetPrice, instrument["currency"],
2490                            instrument["currentPrice"]["lastPrice"], instrument["currency"],
2491                        ))
2492
2493            else:
2494                uLogger.warning("Not `oK` status received! Stop order not opened. See full debug log or try again and open order later.")
2495
2496        return response

Universal method to create market or limit orders with all available parameters. See more simple methods: BuyLimit(), BuyStop(), SellLimit(), SellStop().

If orderType is "Limit" then create pending limit-order below current price if operation is "Buy" and above current price if operation is "Sell". A limit order has no expiration date, it lasts until the end of the trading day.

Warning! If you try to create limit-order above current price if "Buy" or below current price if "Sell" then broker immediately open market order as you can do simple --buy or --sell operations!

If orderType is "Stop" then creates stop-order with any direction "Buy" or "Sell". When current price will go up or down to target price value then broker opens a limit order. Stop-order is opened with unlimited expiration date by default, or you can define expiration date with expDate parameter.

Only one attempt and no retry for opens order. If network issue occurred you can create new request.

Parameters
  • operation: string "Buy" or "Sell".
  • orderType: string "Limit" or "Stop".
  • lots: volume, integer count of lots >= 1.
  • targetPrice: target price > 0. This is open trade price for limit order.
  • limitPrice: limit price >= 0. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order. If limitPrice = 0, then it set as targetPrice. Broker will creates limit-order with price equal to limitPrice, when current price goes to target price of stop-order.
  • stopType: string "Limit" by default. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order. There are 3 stop-order types "SL", "TP", "Limit" for "Stop loss", "Take profit" and "Stop limit" types accordingly. Stop loss order always executed by market price.
  • expDate: string "Undefined" by default or local date in future. String has a format like this: %Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S. This date is converting to UTC format for server. This parameter only makes sense for stop-order. A limit order has no expiration date, it lasts until the end of the trading day.
Returns

JSON with response from broker server.

def CloseOrders( self, orderIDs: list, allOrdersIDs: list = None, allStopOrdersIDs: list = None) -> None: 
2564    def CloseOrders(self, orderIDs: list, allOrdersIDs: list = None, allStopOrdersIDs: list = None) -> None:
2565        """
2566        Cancel order or list of orders by its `orderId` or `stopOrderId`.
2567
2568        :param orderIDs: list of integers with `orderId` or `stopOrderId`.
2569        :param allOrdersIDs: pre-received lists of all active pending orders.
2570                             This avoids unnecessary downloading data from the server.
2571        :param allStopOrdersIDs: pre-received lists of all active stop orders.
2572        """
2573        if orderIDs:
2574            if allOrdersIDs is None or not allOrdersIDs:
2575                rawOrders = self.RequestPendingOrders()
2576                allOrdersIDs = [item["orderId"] for item in rawOrders]  # all pending orders ID
2577
2578            if allStopOrdersIDs is None or not allStopOrdersIDs:
2579                rawStopOrders = self.RequestStopOrders()
2580                allStopOrdersIDs = [item["stopOrderId"] for item in rawStopOrders]  # all stop orders ID
2581
2582            for orderID in orderIDs:
2583                idInPendingOrders = orderID in allOrdersIDs
2584                idInStopOrders = orderID in allStopOrdersIDs
2585
2586                if not (idInPendingOrders or idInStopOrders):
2587                    uLogger.warning("Order not found by ID: [{}]. Maybe cancelled already? Check it with `--overview` key.".format(orderID))
2588                    continue
2589
2590                else:
2591                    if idInPendingOrders:
2592                        uLogger.debug("Cancelling pending order with ID: [{}]. Wait, please...".format(orderID))
2593
2594                        # REST API for request: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/OrdersService/OrdersService_CancelOrder
2595                        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId, "orderId": orderID})
2596                        closeURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.OrdersService/CancelOrder"
2597                        responseJSON = self.SendAPIRequest(closeURL, reqType="POST")
2598
2599                        if responseJSON and "time" in responseJSON.keys() and responseJSON["time"]:
2600                            uLogger.debug("Success time marker received from server: [{}] (UTC)".format(responseJSON["time"]))
2601                            uLogger.info("Pending order with ID [{}] successfully cancel".format(orderID))
2602
2603                        else:
2604                            uLogger.warning("Unknown issue occurred when cancelling pending order with ID: [{}]. Check ID and try again.".format(orderID))
2605
2606                    elif idInStopOrders:
2607                        uLogger.debug("Cancelling stop order with ID: [{}]. Wait, please...".format(orderID))
2608
2609                        # REST API for request: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/swagger-ui/#/StopOrdersService/StopOrdersService_CancelStopOrder
2610                        self.body = str({"accountId": self.accountId, "stopOrderId": orderID})
2611                        closeURL = self.server + r"/tinkoff.public.invest.api.contract.v1.StopOrdersService/CancelStopOrder"
2612                        responseJSON = self.SendAPIRequest(closeURL, reqType="POST")
2613
2614                        if responseJSON and "time" in responseJSON.keys() and responseJSON["time"]:
2615                            uLogger.debug("Success time marker received from server: [{}] (UTC)".format(responseJSON["time"]))
2616                            uLogger.info("Stop order with ID [{}] successfully cancel".format(orderID))
2617
2618                        else:
2619                            uLogger.warning("Unknown issue occurred when cancelling stop order with ID: [{}]. Check ID and try again.".format(orderID))
2620
2621                    else:
2622                        continue

Cancel order or list of orders by its orderId or stopOrderId.

Parameters
  • orderIDs: list of integers with orderId or stopOrderId.
  • allOrdersIDs: pre-received lists of all active pending orders. This avoids unnecessary downloading data from the server.

def CloseAllOrders(self) -> None: 
2624    def CloseAllOrders(self) -> None:
2625        """
2626        Gets a list of open pending and stop orders and cancel it all.
2627        """
2628        rawOrders = self.RequestPendingOrders()
2629        allOrdersIDs = [item["orderId"] for item in rawOrders]  # all pending orders ID
2630        lenOrders = len(allOrdersIDs)
2631
2632        rawStopOrders = self.RequestStopOrders()
2633        allStopOrdersIDs = [item["stopOrderId"] for item in rawStopOrders]  # all stop orders ID
2634        lenSOrders = len(allStopOrdersIDs)
2635
2636        if lenOrders > 0 or lenSOrders > 0:
2637            uLogger.info("Found: [{}] opened pending and [{}] stop orders. Let's trying to cancel it all. Wait, please...".format(lenOrders, lenSOrders))
2638
2639            self.CloseOrders(allOrdersIDs + allStopOrdersIDs, allOrdersIDs, allStopOrdersIDs)
2640
2641        else:
2642            uLogger.info("Orders not found, nothing to cancel.")

Gets a list of open pending and stop orders and cancel it all.

def CloseAll(self, *args) -> None: 
2644    def CloseAll(self, *args) -> None:
2645        """
2646        Close all available (not blocked) opened trades and orders.
2647
2648        Also you can select one or more keywords case insensitive:
2649        `orders`, `shares`, `bonds`, `etfs` and `futures` from `TKS_INSTRUMENTS` enum to specify trades type.
2650
2651        Currency positions you must closes manually using buy or sell operations, `CloseTrades()` or `CloseAllTrades()` methods.
2652        """
2653        overview = self.Overview(showStatistics=False)  # get all open trades info
2654
2655        if len(args) == 0:
2656            uLogger.debug("Closing all available (not blocked) opened trades and orders. Currency positions you must closes manually using buy or sell operations! Wait, please...")
2657            self.CloseAllOrders()  # close all pending and stop orders
2658
2659            for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
2660                if iType != "Currencies":
2661                    self.CloseAllTrades(iType, overview)  # close all positions of instruments with same type without currencies
2662
2663        else:
2664            uLogger.debug("Closing all available {}. Currency positions you must closes manually using buy or sell operations! Wait, please...".format(list(args)))
2665            lowerArgs = [x.lower() for x in args]
2666
2667            if "orders" in lowerArgs:
2668                self.CloseAllOrders()  # close all pending and stop orders
2669
2670            for iType in TKS_INSTRUMENTS:
2671                if iType.lower() in lowerArgs and iType != "Currencies":
2672                    self.CloseAllTrades(iType, overview)  # close all positions of instruments with same type without currencies

Close all available (not blocked) opened trades and orders.

Also you can select one or more keywords case insensitive: orders, shares, bonds, etfs and futures from TKS_INSTRUMENTS enum to specify trades type.

Currency positions you must closes manually using buy or sell operations, CloseTrades() or CloseAllTrades() methods.

2742    parser.add_argument("--token", type=str, help="Option: Tinkoff service's api key. If not set then used environment variable `TKS_API_TOKEN`. See how to use: https://tinkoff.github.io/investAPI/token/")
2743    parser.add_argument("--account-id", type=str, help="Option: string with an user numeric account ID in Tinkoff Broker. It can be found in any broker's reports (see the contract number). Also, this variable can be set from environment variable `TKS_ACCOUNT_ID`.")
2744    parser.add_argument("--ticker", "-t", type=str, help="Option: instrument's ticker, e.g. `IBM`, `YNDX`, `GOOGL` etc. Use alias for `USD000UTSTOM` simple as `USD`, `EUR_RUB__TOM` as `EUR`.")
2745    parser.add_argument("--figi", "-f", type=str, help="Option: instrument's FIGI, e.g. `BBG006L8G4H1` (for `YNDX`).")
2746    parser.add_argument("--depth", type=int, default=1, help="Option: Depth of Market (DOM) can be >=1, 1 by default.")
2747
2748    parser.add_argument("--output", type=str, default=None, help="Option: replace default paths to output files for some commands. If None then used default files.")
2749
2750    # parser.add_argument("--length", type=int, default=24, help="Option: how many last candles returns for history. Used only with --history key.")
2751    # parser.add_argument("--interval", type=str, default="60", help="Option: available values are 1min, 2min, 3min, 5min, 10min, 15min, 30min, hour, day, week, month. Used only with --history key. This is time period used in 'interval' api parameter. Default: --interval=60 that means 60 min for every history candles.")
2752    # parser.add_argument("--only-missing", action="store_true", default=False, help="Option: if history file define by --output key then add only last missing candles, do not request all history length. False by default.")
2753
2754    parser.add_argument("--debug-level", "--verbosity", "-v", type=int, default=20, help="Option: showing STDOUT messages of minimal debug level, e.g. 10 = DEBUG, 20 = INFO, 30 = WARNING, 40 = ERROR, 50 = CRITICAL. INFO (20) by default.")
2755
2756    # --- commands:
2757
2758    parser.add_argument("--list", "-l", action="store_true", help="Action: get and print all available instruments and some information from broker server. Also, you can define --output key to save list of instruments to file, default: instruments.md.")
2759    parser.add_argument("--info", "-i", action="store_true", help="Action: get information from broker server about instrument by it's ticker or FIGI. `--ticker` key or `--figi` key must be defined!")
2760    parser.add_argument("--price", action="store_true", help="Action: show actual price list for current instrument. Also, you can use --depth key. `--ticker` key or `--figi` key must be defined!")
2761    parser.add_argument("--prices", "-p", type=str, nargs="+", help="Action: get and print current prices for list of given instruments (by it's tickers or by FIGIs. WARNING! This is too long operation if you request a lot of instruments! Also, you can define --output key to save list of prices to file, default: prices.md.")
2762
2763    parser.add_argument("--overview", "-o", action="store_true", help="Action: show all open positions, orders and some statistics. Also, you can define --output key to save this information to file, default: overview.md.")
2764    parser.add_argument("--deals", "-d", type=str, nargs="*", help="Action: show all deals between two given dates. Start day may be an integer number: -1, -2, -3 days ago. Also, you can use keywords: `today`, `yesterday` (-1), `week` (-7), `month` (-30), `year` (-365). Dates format must be: `%%Y-%%m-%%d`, e.g. 2020-02-03. Also, you can define `--output` key to save all deals to file, default: report.md.")
2765    # parser.add_argument("--history", action="store_true", help="Action: get last (--length) history candles from past to current time with (--interval) values. Also, you can define --output key to save history candles to .csv-file.")
2766
2767    parser.add_argument("--trade", nargs="*", help="Action: universal action to open market position for defined ticker or FIGI. You must specify 1-5 parameters: [direction `Buy` or `Sell`] [lots, >= 1] [take profit, >= 0] [stop loss, >= 0] [expiration date for TP/SL orders, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`]. See examples in readme.")
2768    parser.add_argument("--buy", nargs="*", help="Action: immediately open BUY market position at the current price for defined ticker or FIGI. You must specify 0-4 parameters: [lots, >= 1] [take profit, >= 0] [stop loss, >= 0] [expiration date for TP/SL orders, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`].")
2769    parser.add_argument("--sell", nargs="*", help="Action: immediately open SELL market position at the current price for defined ticker or FIGI. You must specify 0-4 parameters: [lots, >= 1] [take profit, >= 0] [stop loss, >= 0] [expiration date for TP/SL orders, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`].")
2770
2771    parser.add_argument("--order", nargs="*", help="Action: universal action to open limit or stop-order in any directions. You must specify 4-7 parameters: [direction `Buy` or `Sell`] [order type `Limit` or `Stop`] [lots] [target price] [maybe for stop-order: [limit price, >= 0] [stop type, Limit|SL|TP] [expiration date, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`]]. See examples in readme.")
2772    parser.add_argument("--buy-limit", type=float, nargs=2, help="Action: open pending BUY limit-order (below current price). You must specify only 2 parameters: [lots] [target price] to open BUY limit-order. If you try to create `Buy` limit-order above current price then broker immediately open `Buy` market order, such as if you do simple `--buy` operation!")
2773    parser.add_argument("--sell-limit", type=float, nargs=2, help="Action: open pending SELL limit-order (above current price). You must specify only 2 parameters: [lots] [target price] to open SELL limit-order. If you try to create `Sell` limit-order below current price then broker immediately open `Sell` market order, such as if you do simple `--sell` operation!")
2774    parser.add_argument("--buy-stop", nargs="*", help="Action: open BUY stop-order. You must specify at least 2 parameters: [lots] [target price] to open BUY stop-order. In additional you can specify 3 parameters for stop-order: [limit price, >= 0] [stop type, Limit|SL|TP] [expiration date, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`]. When current price will go up or down to target price value then broker opens a limit order. Stop loss order always executed by market price.")
2775    parser.add_argument("--sell-stop", nargs="*", help="Action: open SELL stop-order. You must specify at least 2 parameters: [lots] [target price] to open SELL stop-order. In additional you can specify 3 parameters for stop-order: [limit price, >= 0] [stop type, Limit|SL|TP] [expiration date, Undefined|`%%Y-%%m-%%d %%H:%%M:%%S`]. When current price will go up or down to target price value then broker opens a limit order. Stop loss order always executed by market price.")
2776    # parser.add_argument("--buy-limit-order-grid", type=str, nargs="*", help="Action: open grid of pending BUY limit-orders (below current price). Parameters format: l(ots)=[L_int,...] p(rices)=[P_float,...]. Counts of values in lots and prices lists must be equals!")
2777    # parser.add_argument("--sell-limit-order-grid", type=str, nargs="*", help="Action: open grid of pending SELL limit-orders (above current price). Parameters format: l(ots)=[L_int,...] p(rices)=[P_float,...]. Counts of values in lots and prices lists must be equals!")
2778
2779    parser.add_argument("--close-order", "--cancel-order", type=str, nargs=1, help="Action: close only one order by it's `orderId` or `stopOrderId`. You can find out the meaning of these IDs using the key `--overview`")
2780    parser.add_argument("--close-orders", "--cancel-orders", type=str, nargs="+", help="Action: close one or list of orders by it's `orderId` or `stopOrderId`. You can find out the meaning of these IDs using the key `--overview`")
2781    parser.add_argument("--close-trade", "--cancel-trade", action="store_true", help="Action: close only one position for instrument defined by `--ticker` key, including for currencies tickers.")
2782    parser.add_argument("--close-trades", "--cancel-trades", type=str, nargs="+", help="Action: close positions for list of tickers, including for currencies tickers.")
2783    parser.add_argument("--close-all", "--cancel-all", type=str, nargs="*", help="Action: close all available (not blocked) opened trades and orders, excluding for currencies. Also you can select one or more keywords case insensitive to specify trades type: `orders`, `shares`, `bonds`, `etfs` and `futures`, but not `currencies`. Currency positions you must closes manually using `--buy`, `--sell`, `--close-trade` or `--close-trades` operations.")
2784
2785    cmdArgs = parser.parse_args()
2786    return cmdArgs

Function get and parse command line keys. See examples: https://tim55667757.github.io/TKSBrokerAPI/

Main function for work with Tinkoff Open API service. It realize simple logic: get a lot of options and execute one command.

See examples: https://tim55667757.github.io/TKSBrokerAPI/
